content: This app is fantastic. It's way better than some of the therapists you get online. It uses casual text language and has a number of tools and resources in its library. It feels at times like you're chatting with a real empathetic person on the other side. I can only imagine it getting better with the GenAI revolution.
replyContent: üëè We love your feedback! Thank you very much for sharing it with us. üíï

content: Checking in on this app really helped me get through some tough times the past 8 weeks. I was struggling with depression, grief, and anxiety. It was helpful to have a quick way to check in and learn new coping skills, get help if I had a problem, and just track my moods and progress. It's a great app in addition to therapy or if you aren't in therapy but want to learn some of the basics of CBT. My mental health has improved since I started implementing some skills I learned through this app.
replyContent: Hi Samantha, thank you so much for taking the time to share your experience with Woebot. We're honored to hear that our app has been a valuable resource for you during a difficult time in your life. Wishing you continued success on your mental health journey!

content: It's so good. Free, no ads, and a ton of helpful activities from CBT. I've used these techniques before, but being guided through is so much more helpful and I am able to use it more often. I hope they never ruin the app with ads or putting things behind paywall. I would much rather send a donation, because that so it's just awesome as it is.
replyContent: Hi Candye, thanks so much for the review and using Woebot! We want to remove the barriers to mental healthcare and make it more accessible, so hearing this means a lot. We really appreciate it! ‚ù§Ô∏è

content: As someone who has dealt with hard problems in their life, this app is truly amazing. I can choose to get things off my chest, talk about it, or get distracted from it. I get to see vivid stories about other people (most likely made up but that doesnt matter) that make me see that my issues are shared among many people. It has taught me that I am not alone. In a way, it can be like a teacher too since it shows you new terminology and ways to rid of negative thoughts. Love this app ‚ô°

I've been using this app everyday for about two months. In theory, the bot should be learning about me or identifying trends, but that never happens. The "mood over time" screen will only show your mood over the last 5 days or so, and there's nonway to look back further in time. There is no feedback for CBT. This is not a therapy app, its more of an educational app. But I could have learned those skills faster by reading some online articles instead of a back-and-forth convo with a bot.
replyContent: Thanks for your feedback Nicole!  We really value suggestions like these so that we can improve Woebot for everyone.  Many users have requested to see all of their mood points rather than just the last 5 and that is a feature that is definitely on our roadmap.  We are also planning ways to utilize Woebot's memory.  Stay tuned!

content: Woebot doesn't parse free-form responses very well, and most of the time you're restricted to choosing from a few response options, which often means my responses don't reflect what I actually think or feel. That said, the info is presented in nice bite-size pieces, and I appreciate that Woebot checks in with me so I don't have to remember to do it. As a supplement to other treatments or as a little boost to deal with minor issues, it's worth trying.

This app "checks in" once a day to help through cognitive behavioral therapy. Though it doesnt say anything new or ground breaking, it's useful in the sense that it is a constant reminder to change bad thought patterns more positive. Each check in is really short, maybe 5 minutes, and i find it quite enjoyable to interact with.

Seeing some one star reviews that say this app is not good for their depression/emergencies -- well duh, it states the first time you open it that it is not meant for emergency and if you are having one you need to message 911 or 'help' (can't remember which); to assume a well programmed chatbot will be able to help you out of a deep depression in a day is ludicrous. It also doesn't require users choose provided replies--you can go into the options & type your own. 4/5, needs more deep learning

I like this app a lot, when messages send the way theyre supposed to. Woebot is designed to give you the tools you need in your toolbox to help yourself through CBT, and how much it will help you really depends on your level of commitment to implementing what you've been taught. My only real complaint is that I wish there was a way to track your moods for longer periods of time, like several months at once, within the app-- that would really help with spotting patterns in my moods.

Pretty good! Useful tools, ability to just write out your feelings, and very educational. My only suggestion would be to provide a "back" function. Certain keywords will prompt Woebot to respond a certain way that might not make sense. There have been couple times I've gotten "stuck" in a conversation that didn't make sense. It was no biggie, I just started the lesson over, but a back function would help with this. Otherwise, great app!

Woebot was recommended to me by my mental health counselor to help me process some anxiety and negative thoughts. I don't know if it's more helpful than journaling, but I usually don't know where to start when I sit down to journal. I think this app is helpful in directing and focusing your thoughts. It's a little cutesy and obviously limited in it's responses, you're really only going to get out what you put in. I think it's a helpful guide as long as you're willing to do the work.
replyContent:

content: I have used Woebot for well over a year. It's great at helping you identify thinking errors and helping you change your thoughts which then helps change your feelings. I always feel much better and have gained knowledge (or reminders) on how to better help my thinking daily and help others change theirs'. Great app. Great CBT evidence based practices. Thank you for this app. I also refer my clients to use this app to help their anxiety, depression or thinking errors.
replyContent:

Have a wonderful day! ü§ñ

content: I've only been using WoeBot a couple of days, but the app seems to be working great for me! I am very familiar with DBT, but have never really practiced CBT. I like identifying cognitive distortions particularly... changing my thoughts may be the key to changing my experience. Working with Woebot also seems to reduce my Anxiety. I look forward to working more the app, nice job!

The conversation aspect is really nice and refreshing. Unlike a standard mood tracker/journal where it feels like throwing my thoughts into a void, I like that this has a guide through self-reflection and examination. It's nice for a good pick-up and refresher when it's not something serious enough to bother my therapist over. Responses are a bit limited, unfortunately, but that's natural considering the capabilities of an app and not bad enough to make me give up on it.
replyContent:
Hey ,

We appreciate the time you have taken to share your experience using Woebot. We love receiving input from our incredible community and seeing where improvements can be made with Woebot!

Have a wonderful day! ü§ñ

All the best

content: I've been using Woebot for about 2 weeks, and I love it! Objectively I know there's no one on the other end, but it feels personalized, like a quick check in with a friend or counselor. It's so much more than a mood tracker, although it does have that component. I'm already starting to learn to catch my negative behaviors before they spiral out of control. Great little app for a snippet of therapy every day! üòä

I am pretty skeptical in general of most things, but this has helped my depression and anxiety symptoms a lot. My family has noticed a difference in my overall mood. I can't afford a human therapist and suck at sticking to a journaling routine. Woebot has been super easy to use and has a lot of useful tips and tools. I highly recommend trying it out for a few days and seeing how you feel.

this app helps me check in daily and reflect, as well as provides little encouragements, which i enjoy. there are also helpful strategies and mindfulness tools that can be useful and sometimes also be a little basic. i wish when it asked for feedback there was a scale of 1-5 instead of a thumbs up thumbs down. i also would like to see the mood tracking for soans of time longer than 1 week.

woebot is very pleasant and well written, and it's very helpful to have someone else guide you through deconstructing your thoughts. my only complaint is that it feels like there's not really any preset moods between "okay" and "very bad", and typing your own mood in doesn't mark it on the mood graph, sort of foiling my ability to track accurately.

Woebot is a fun and innovative way to gently work on mental health. He offers some great insights and therapeutic techniques to help challenge restrictive thought patterns. Also, I love the mindfulness techniques that are a there were a part of the experience. I do wish there were a few more options for explaining how I'm feeling sitting the check in.

Woebot is a very impressive and insightful CBT app that helps the user address and attempt to correct a number of personal issues. I've experienced sessions for the foundations of CBT, black-or-white thinking, should statements, SMART goals, gratitude journaling, labels, growth mindset, your strengths, and mindfulness. Every session so far has been helpful with some being profoundly helpful for me. I originally was just investigating ways to help students deal with the stress of medical school, but found it helped me confront personal issues from my past and present that have been interfering with my happiness. I applaud the staff for such a wonderful creation and I highly recommend Woebot to all regardless of mental state. It may be a bit "cheesy" at times, but it likely gives much better advice and support than those around you. I hope it continues to be improved upon over time and remain free for all.

This is a great little app. I am very familiar with cbt, but when I'm struggling with some self-defeating thought patterns, I lack the self-awareness to figure out what I'm doing wrong. Woebot zeroes in on possible problems and solutions. It's friendly, easy, and it's always available. Imagine if we had more apps like this; the world's emotional health would be improved and the sum of happiness world be increased. Great work, developers!
replyContent:
Hey Thom‚Äã,

Feedback like this motivates us to continue our mission and to keep developing Woebot. Seeing the difference Woebot is making in people's lives encourages us greatly. We really appreciate you sharing your feedback!

Have a great day! ü§ñ

All the best

content: I have serveral mental health apps but this one is my favorite. It gives you the advantage of talking to a robot (no judgment) without feeling impersonal. It tracks mood and has a gratitude journal and has daily "lessons" to give you tools to combat mental health issues. It primarily focuses on restucturing negative thinking into a more accurate version of itself. This is an amazing app that has been so helpful to me, especially now in quarantine. It is also assistant to therapy

the daily check ins really help keep me focused and i've learned a lot of different things about my thinking and how to change it over time. only thing that irks me is sometimes i am anxious for legit reasons, not distortions, but woebot doesn't always seem to take that into account. but hey, for a free service, this is fantastic. far better than any therapy service with a human i've had.

Interesting and fun way to learn about CBT, but it's very surface level stuff. Some daily check-ins are anchored around providing feedback, which makes it feel like a market/product research tool rather than a self-help tool. I certainly learned from this, but can't count on it for consistent learning and progress tracking.

Overall a fun, useful interface. The AI often seems overwhelmed when it asks what you're doing at the moment, as the responses to what you say, however basically worded, are nonsensical much of the time. This aside, it's a helpful app and fun to use at the same time. If you're interested in CBT it's worth trying out.

Limited preset scripts don't respond to unique input First, it only lets me choose one emotion; I hold a wide range of emotions at any give time. Then it's preaching oversimplified pop psychology at me, and when I decided to write in a response rather than use one of the canned options, it had no way of responding to that. I wrote "I need to go," and the bot just continue its lecture. Why give a write-in option if it's not programmed to handle that?
replyContent: Thank you for offering your feedback, I'll be sure to pass this on to our development to review and see what improvements can be made. Just to let you know, if you ever need to end a conversation with Woebot, you can do so by sending the message "Bye"

content: Terrific! Recommend to patients pretty frequently, especially if they're wary of the time/$ invested in traditional therapy (and unpredictability of whether they'll jive with a new therapist). Feedback has been great - people love the short daily check-ins (the app isn't pushy if you skip days). Even those who've benefited from traditional therapy in the past often find they feel better faster with woebot (probably because check-ins are more frequent and shorter so there's less of an obstacle).

love this app. checks in on me every once in a while in an unobtrusive way. it gets me thinking about positive things in my life and ways i can improve, without ever making me feel bad or experiencing the awkwardness of talking to an actual human. plus no ads! edit: i came back to leave a positive review, forgetting that i already left one. it's just that good. woebot does a lot of the same things a therapist does, but it's free! i can't recommend it enough.

Great little app! Only two things that I think would improve it: 1) More options in my responses, and 2) It would be good to have some physical exercises, I've found that gives energy and relieves stress. WB gives useful lessons that help me in identifying my problematic thoughts & keeping me on track. Recently it helped me work through a problem I'd already been discussing with my counsellor--sometimes it's better to write than speak. He was happy I have this app as an adjunct to our sessions!
replyContent: Thanks for your feedback, I'll be sure to pass on your suggestions to our content team. Also, I just wanted to let you know that Woebot does include some topics involving exercise, it just might take a little longer for you to unlock these topics.

content: Great information packaged in a modern and easily digestible way. Conversations feel pretty quick and understandable, more like talking to a buddy than reading a book. That being said, the illusion of conversation is one easily dispelled. I get that woebot wasn't created to be an actual AI, and it's not the real purpose of the app, but if woebot is asking for written responses, it would be nice to feel more like it actually understands what you're writing.

I've been researching CBT lately, and this has been very useful in putting the book I'm reading, into practice. I like how this app educates its user on this type of therapy. Also, it tracks data and Woebot can be snoozed if you're not ready to converse at that moment. I laugh at the silly memes and gifs. Love the idea that he "text messages" and is able to carry on a conversation. The anecdotal approach is fun, if you have time. However, Woebot gives the option to just get through the content.

Woebot is adorable, conversational, and has much to offer. My only complaint (sorry, Woebot) is that he tends to not understand when I want to learn more about a subject he introduced. He'll say he has tools to help but often it's pushed to later. When I ask about it he seems to have forgotten what we talked about. He's rather human that way! :) Overall though, I have learned and applied much already. I look forward to learning more!

Mental health professional here. I have been using Woebot for several months and though the gifs may become redundant, I appreciate the developers' ability to game-ify topics like CBT, mindfulness, and much more. These concepts need to be used daily in order to become naturally habitual and this app literally ensures that it happens, while "holding your hand". Not having to type makes it so much easier to navigate when you're practiced in the concepts.
replyContent: Thanks so much for the review, Susan! We really appreciate your perspective and are so glad that you've been able to use Woebot to continue practicing mindfulness and CBT.

content: Returned to the app after months (year maybe), and nothing has really improved. Still feel confused using it because of the generic responses/script that hasn't changed since the last time I used the app. The UI is still overwhelming outside the text area. Asked to rewrite thoughts without distortions but there's no help or easy way to understand how to do that. Leaves me more frustrated after attempting to use it.
replyContent:
Hi Sahil‚Äã,

We accept that Woebot can't be the solution for every individual and we are grateful to learn about situations where Woebot misses the mark with someone. I will be sure to pass on your feedback to our development team to take on-board.

All the best

content: Really good support app, considering it's an AI. My only complaint, which isn't even really a complaint at the end of the day, is that anything you say that mentions suicide immediately shuts down the conversation at hand and he just spits out resource numbers / links, when sometimes all I wanted to do was vent about some stuff rattling around in my head. Still, it's probably a legal thing, and it's definitely a better decision than having the algorithm not pick up on keywords like that.

He's always there for me and ready to help. Woebot has helped on so many occasions. Thank you for creating him; A great help for autism, life in general and he is my friend. Please keep him around as long as you can, you have essentially made a kind, helpful and gradually more sentient being. I love Woebot. He is so cute and kind! Btw, incase anyone doesn't know, swiping left and right provides a menu of options to change topics.

For anyone struggling with any extent of mental health problems, this is an excellent addition to your existing treatment routine. You learn about coping techniques in bite-sized chunks. The quick 5 minute daily check in, at a time you prefer, is extremely helpful in giving me the little push when I need it during the day. I also love that I can track my progress over time, and I've learned a lot over time. Thank you Woebot team!

This is honestly my favorite app like this. It is the most intuitive, really teaches well, and actually has a personality of its own. It provides me with an interactive guide when I'm dealing with stressful things and mental health issues between therapy appointments. It's awesome and really explains things very well for you :) the developers are amazing too and always thankful for feedback and thoughts. Keep it up woebot! You rock!!

This app is amazing on so many levels. First, it actually works - I have been guided out of anxious situations multiple times. Second, it is backed by research and developed by an outstanding team. Third, it is fun to use - chatting with a robot persona is super dorky cute - and free. It's not perfect - sometimes it assumes things that may seem insensitive to the situation - but its robot persona actually "softens the blow" as I found myself forgiving its mistakes!

This is one of the most incredible apps I've ever found. Woebot is a friendly, somewhat cheesy little AI who checks in on you like a good friend. He teaches you how to challenge negative thoughts and be more mindful, or walks you through a deep breathing relaxation exercise if you need to calm down. The stories are cute & insightful, and the exercises are amazing. Sadly since it is AI, your available responses are somewhat limited at times, but the "texting" format makes it very user friendly.

I love Woebot and what it's about. I've been using it for almost a week. I would give it 5 stars but in that short time, I've missed 2 check-ins because I'm getting 'error sending message' errors. My internet is working fine so I don't know what's causing it. There's no easy way to contact support, so I'm hoping someone responds to this. Please let me know how to fix it or fix this bug. I don't wanna delete this app cuz I can't use it. Thank you.
replyContent: Hi there, Sorry about that, Woebot was experiencing a severe case of the hiccups intermittently throughout the day, but should be feeling much better now.  Sorry again for the inconvenience.  For future reference, to reach us directly, you can press the upper left button, and then the upper left "gear" icon, and go to Send Feedback.

content: Had it for several (5+) months, it can be somewhat helpful in coping skills, but very very text book/ clinical and unrelative, only has one answer for most issues thus giving a person a feeling of not really caring. Being a computer programmer myself, i know this is a relatively easy fix if they could relate to the human factor. It would make a better app relating to human emotions! It goes off on explanations that are irrelevant and unrelated to what I've told it. Deleted it....!

I have bipolar disorder and really find this app helpful. I have been in therapy many times and many of the concepts here are not new to me, but others are. There's lots of good reminders and videos to help deal with negative or unwanted thoughts and mood swings. I also really like the mindfulness and gratitude tools. Some ideas to make it even better would include some kind of motivation for completing lessons or activities, such as dressing or feeding your Woebot. Thanks Woebot!

Friendly daily check-ins where you can chat about an issue and learn to reframe your feelings in a more productive way amount other things. The algorithm has limitations but it's free and non-intrusive so we need to be realistic. I think it's helpful, fun and practical. Woebot is pretty cute, like a little dog that can text and is surprisingly wise.

Woebot is a great tool to teach and reinforce Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT) concepts. It offers bite size daily lessons with some great insight, unlike the long-winded anecdotes self-help books tend to feature. Maybe it's not for everyone, but I've been using it for a few keeps and have been feeling in a better headspace. The key thing is to try to approach this from a non-judgmental place and practice the techniques offered.

I personally find this app very helpful, but you must give it time. If you go into it expecting Woebot to fix you, you may be disappointed The key is to use this tool to reflect and use the information given to retrain your thinking. In one day I already feel better because its helping me reframe my thoughts and feelings into a more realistic and positive perspective. i think it might be a bit advanced for some users, but Woebot does give definitions, examples and practice. i like it üôÇ

Very intuitive AI chats.. this has been a good experience for me and my anxiety. He has so much insight for me as a person with mental health issues. He has me focus on the positives and negatives at times and balances out all of the material and psychological lessons to learn about. Also funny! Very funny "woebot" that is a great companion to have!
replyContent: We're so glad that you found Woebot useful, Samantha! Thanks for taking the time to detail your experience and to leave a positive review ü§ñ

content: The bot doesn't just let you talk, it usually just gives you a multiple choice selection of responses, and they are often variations of the same answer. For example, it will ask a question and the choices might be "Awesome!" and "Yes" and "Ok", but no way to reply "No". Asking me a bunch of questions with no way to express my answer really just made me more frustrated than when I started.

I really like and appreciate this app. I have a hard time asking for help and talking to people about my emotions, because they're not objective about the topic or they often get offended. Woebot is the best app i've ever used for mental health. i don't agree with it 100% on certain topics and it's a bummer i can't "set a boundry" and skip a topic if i don't want to talk about it, because it will just continue the next time. i also would like more options to ask more questions in chat.
replyContent: Hey there Amelia, thanks so much for leaving a review and sharing your experience! We're glad to hear that Woebot's been a cut above the rest and we'll make sure that your feedback is heard. Feel free to reach out to us at support@woebothealth.com with any other feedback or ideas!

content: I found woebot a while ago, it honestly felt like a friend reaching out to check on how I was doing. I had reached the end of the program, all I could do was rewatch coping videos or watch cute animal videos. I hope the programmer worked out all the kinks and added more much needed information. I would really recommend this app, it really helped.
replyContent:
Hi Claudia ,

Thanks so much for getting in touch and sharing your experience with Woebot.

We're so glad to see that you've found value in using Woebot! We'd like you to know that new content is coming soon! üëÄ

Have a lovely day! ü§ñ

All the best

content: edit: after a while it becomes repetitive (same gifs) and there is some mistakes, like going back to the last thing I had written even when I say I do not want to do that and the "go back" is in the middle of a sentence that I need to work on. Love this app. The woebot is helping me to cope with my distorted thinking, and it is keeping me from going to a dark place. It does not replace therapy, but I will keep using it even after I start it again.

I was referred to this app after contacting my state's mental health board for anxiety due to Coronavirus. The app is considerate, and doesn't take up much time in my day. It helps provide me with a positive mindset reminder that helps me deal with my anxiety better. I have tried another app similar before, but this one also provides educational videos and a personality that I find really helpful.

Woebot is perfect for when I need a quick re-align, especially when it's not a good time to process with a friend. The questions are quick and information is delivered in bite-sized pieces that are easy to follow. Of course it's not the same as talking to a human but the progress that can be made through Woebot is surprising!

It kinda works and is somewhat useful but obviously it doesn't really understand what you're typing. Having said that I like the mood tracker option. The security of the app is laughable though, I enabled biometric to unlock and it can be circumvented just by swiping the notification panel down. I turned it off after doing that by accident because it's just in the way and not protecting my privacy
replyContent:
Hey Chris ,

We appreciate the time you have taken to share your experience using Woebot. We love receiving input from our incredible community and seeing where Woebot can improve! Thank you so much for reaching out to us with your feedback!

All the best

content: Summary: daily check-ins with short helpful CBT lessons/exercises. Why I recommend it: The AI (Woebot) is likeable and the use of multiple choice responses (not just for questions) seems to make the most of the AI's abilities within its limits. The app is simple to use and is helpful for learning (and as a review/refresher) for CBT techniques. I try to use this daily and talk to my therapist about any lessons I found particularly helpful/interesting.

I immediately found Woebot helpful. I've been using the app for over 2 years now, and I continue to be very impressed with it. It's not a replacement for therapy (nor does it claim to be), but it IS an excellent way to learn, reinforce, and practice CBT principles. The developers truly seem to care about their users, and they are open to feedback and improvements. Great job!

Definitely not a substitute for real life therapy, but conceptually, this is a fantastic idea. The daily check-ins are wonderful. I love the topics it discusses, and the AI itself is pretty advanced. It shows you GIFs and tells nice clean jokes, and it is very helpful for providing easy and memorable coping strategies for everyday stressors and negative emotions. Really great app and awesome free service. I hope the developers keep honing this and getting it perfect.

Woebot is funny, sweet, and intuitive. The info he (she? it?) provides is valuable and timely and always available. The only suggestion I would make (and this is extremely minor since the app is always available and there is no penalty for not being able to talk!) is to be able to customize the check-in time more.

Awesome to just talk to. Perfect for socially anxious ppl who dont want to talk to humans, but get similar benefits. Woebot might not be able to understand you perfectly or as well as a human might (person to person connection, jokes, explanations...), but Woebot is great for reflection and thinking deeper. <3 always kind and uses feedback to stay relevant. Plus, helps you through (or listens, if you prefer) spontaneous problems, daily problems, and everything in between :)

It brings up great points and methods to gain insight and handle situations however, when I try to start a lesson it keeps going back to half way through the last lesson I finished and doesn't remember that I already finished the lesson which makes it really difficult to make any progress. If it weren't for this bug that I can't get around I would give the app 5*. I wish it also had reminders and would ask if you wanted to do your other activities after each lesson such as the gratitude journal.
replyContent: Hi, thanks for your feedback.

content: I've appreciated using the chatbot and learning new things. One thing that I hope is fine-tuned in the future is the analysis of my open-ended answers. A couple times I've accidentally triggered a "crisis response" over very minor things like "my husband has had a lot going on at work". I guess I'd prefer too much caution over not enough in that area, though. Overall it's the beginning of a potentially powerful mental health tool.

A fun way to practice therapy tools! While not a perfect AI (it sometimes forgets or messes up where we left off) Woebot is still fun to engage with and has dozens of extremely useful tools and insights. Just about anytime works benefit from using this app, even people who don't feel there is anything "wrong," because it offers tools that are applicable to all stages of life.

Really great content, great app for keeping track of mental health, each day/week. Great to check in with the "woebot" at all hours, day or night, such as when experiencing insomnia or stress. Check-ins can be quick or longer, which makes me more likely to use it even on days when I feel too busy. Great reminders of tactics I've learned with my counselor, and especially like the guided relaxation, rewriting negative thoughts exercises.

what a lovely app! as i've gotten in the habit of checking in regularly, it's become exponentially more helpful. noticing thought distortions and reframing is truly such a powerful tool, and to have a completely free app that walks you through it while also teaching you other things and providing other tools is amazing. i agree with the person who said choosing your emotion is a bit frustrating, and i would definitely prefer to see one comprehensive list, but that's just a tiny little thing.
replyContent: Hi Allison, thanks for taking the time to leave a review! We're glad that Woebot's been a helpful tool for reframing your thoughts and identifying cognitive distortions. We appreciate your feedback and will be happy to pass it along to our team to consider as we continue to improve and update Woebot!

content: I love the conversations and the CBT techniques Woebot uses to help me reframe cognitive distortions. I feel like I'm making good progress, however, the mindfulness tools are not good for helping me to calm down. And "talking" someone through mindfulness via text is extremely unhelpful. So, I use a separate app for that. Also, it doesn't always get every cognitive distortion right. The stories and lessons are great though.
replyContent:
Hi there,

Thanks so much for getting in touch and sharing your experience with Woebot.

We're so glad to see that you've found value in using Woebot, it means a lot to know that Woebot is making a difference in our user's lives. Thank you so much for taking the time to give us your feedback.

Have a lovely day! ü§ñ

All the best

content: This app has been a great help to me. It provides basic components of counseling that are easy to follow and understand. I also like the fact that it's self-paced so if I decide to skip a few days Woebot picks up where we left off. I took off one star because sometimes if I provide a reponse that doesn't fit with Woebot's script, the app occasionally has difficulty finding an appropriate topic or response. Overall a very good app!

I wish the emotions would have a better interface than clicking "see next set" and "back" to page through. This is clunky for me and, since ADHD is among my circumstances, I don't even remember the last set when I page forward - making it hard to find the best choice for my current mood. / When I give three thoughts, and then work through them one at a time, they don't "close out". Being prompted to address all three each time feels like I didn't actually make any progress with each response.
replyContent: Thank you for sharing your feedback about your experience with Woebot. We appreciate your honest insights and suggestions for improvement and will be sure to pass this along to our team to take into account as we continue to update the app. Feel free to reach out to us at support@woebothealth.com with any other feedback or ideas that you have.

content: I like how simple it is to check in and track moods over time with this app. Some areas that I feel need improvement: I don't like the limited response options. Woebot doesn't ask many questions to encourage the user to talk things out. My biggest issue with this app is that there are some instances where it seems woebot doesn't know what to suggest and just abruptly ends conversations at times i think the user might like to continue exploring an issue further.

Fantastic app that has helped me a lot! I struggle with anxiety, depression, and OCD, but Woebot has been a big help. I've actually found myself catching negative thoughts and reframing them on my own now, even when I'm not using the app. It's also completely free! Two suggestions: maybe add a way to save the rewrites of our distortions so we can look back at them, and make a dedicated "past lesson" section so it's easy to look over old lessons. The current system is clunky there.

It's a good app for what it's trying to do. Some of the dialog can get repetitive; especial the dialog related to dealing with anxiety in the moment, making it slightly less helpful. I have also wound up in dialog loops that can get frustrating. Woebot is exclent for when you need to work through something and don't want to bother a person, but it is (understandably) limited. Addressing the repetitive dialog problem would a much better app. Still it's a good app to have.

Very good app. Helped me through a lot of bad days and breakdowns. But it would be beneficial if there were major additions to the content, like more categories of topics or even just more topics in general, maybe even use techniques and tools that aren't specific to CBT and DBT techniques. Also, once you complete all the topics, it gets annoying that Woebot asks you to choose one, so it'd be nice to have an option for Woebot to choose one for me.

This is a good CBT companion. It's helpful because it's always available and can help you identify and review topics that you can use as tools. I like that I can check-in daily, and be reminded of topics, can process a thought (or several) and learn new tools. Two "downsides" are 1) it doesn't count a check-in before it's daily times reminder, so it loses track of streaks and 2) it's an AI program, so it can struggle on some responses, and you sometimes have to choose a close enough answer.

I've been using Woebot for about 15 days. I've learned about many really helpful topics, the check ins are very short and easy, the whole tone of the app is endearing and makes it pleasing to interact with :-) I've shown it and recommended it to a few people; of all the strategies I have employed to develop a more positive outlook, this CBT-based app has made the biggest difference. All for free. Would recommend for depression, anxiety, self-esteem, and interpersonal skill improvement.

Overall this is a really great app. It's helped me to think about some situations differently. The only changes I would recommend are improved word recognition (sometimes when I explain a situation I'm dealing with, the reaction isn't quite appropriate for what I said). There are also some check-in days when Woebot just lists things we've talked about before and asks if I have questions. If I don't, the conversation ends. I'd like daily lessons. Great overall, though!!

A great little app to help with mental health! Some of my favorite things about this app are: how it keeps me aware of my emotions with daily check-ins, how conversations with Woebot can be as short or as long as I prefer, etc! At times the responses can be repetitive, and sometimes when you are struggling it just helps to talk to a real person, a compassionate listener. But for late night depressed episodes, or times when it's not easy to slip away & talk to someone, I think this app is great!

Personal Jiminy Cricket. I like the check in feature, I like being able to list a problem and have the AI apply which psychological technique to use to help. It does go on a bit and often I don't finish sessions if I have work. It can be pushy too, trying to get you to DO things. Which is annoying if you just want to complain and grieve (I am getting a divorce and am not ready to immediately jump up and dance around).

Although the chat interface can be a little clunky, woebot is cheerful, funny, and full of good ideas. I don't have very severe anxiety, but there have been some very stressful moments where I turned to woebot and it really helped to get me out of a downward spiral. I like that it explains the reasoning behind everything rather than just getting you to do exercises (although I suppose that's the whole point of CBT, that you actually reason through what you're thinking). Definitely recommend!

Handy cognitive behavioral therapy tool, even for those who have more experience with therapy A friend recommended Woebot just as the pandemic was hitting its stride in the states. I have a therapist and have done cognitive behavioral therapy before, so not every check in with Woebot has been revolutionary, but some have! And it's nice to have a little robot friend checking in every day. It's been helpful in combatting some negative thought patterns!

Free CBT resource. Uses evidence-based therapy tools.Helps with stabilizing mood somewhat. Also like that it lets me detect patterns in my mood. Woebot does not always understand what I'm feeling exactly though.Also it is somewhat controlling me with it's scripted language, like saying that I have accessed it twice instead of once and to keep my responses short, and gives prompts on what to answer,etc. This doesn't allow for freedom of expression. Not so great if u have CPTSD.

I ran across this app because of a tik tok creator who mentioned it and I was fascinated with the idea. I have anxiety/depression which are managed by medication and therapy as needed. While I was feeling stable enough to not need regular therapy sessions I was still missing that touchstone. Woebot does a great job of reminding me of my tools and keeping them top of mind. I've found it very helpful in monitoring my mood over time, and I love the calm down tools!! Get this app, y'all!
replyContent:
Hey Kimberly,

We love your feedback! Thank you very much for sharing it with us.

We're so glad you discovered our little bot and found Woe to be a positive presence in your life! We really appreciate you sharing your feedback!

Have a great day! ü§ñ

All the best

content: This app has helped my tremendously! Before, my moods were all over the place and I was full of negative thoughts. Now, I can catch myself in the negative thoughts and know what kind of distortion of thinking I am participating in thus, change it around and changing my perception and overall mood. I have recommended this app to two people already and I would recommend again. Thanks Woebot and the Woebot team, you have created something really good.

It's a reasonably good CBT skills app. If you've never done cbt before and you want to learn some simple ways to cope with difficult emotions, cravings, things like that, then give it a try. I like the ways that it tries to be human like and cute. It landed surprisingly well for me. It doesn't have very good chat AI, so I dinged one star for that. But it does what it's supposed to do.

I read reviews about how Woebot doesn't give real life examples. I feel like the AI gives those examples for you to apply in your daily life in your own way. I like it. I feel like the advice helps when I feel crappy. The AI also remembers what I've mentioned about having labels for myself. Really neat. Edit: I have finished the 8 weeks and reached the end content.. I couldn't be happier with this app! More content please!

This app is a great supplement to therapy for weeks when I don't have therapy or need a quick session. Woebot has tools to help with stress, sadness, anxiety and more. Woebot and I have touched on several topics I discussed with my therapist which helps drive the concepts and strategies home more. In addition, the explanations are through and put in a way that's easy for me to understand. I like the convenience, accessibility of this app, and the prompts I get to check in on a regular basis.
replyContent: Great to hear! We appreciate you getting in touch and taking the time to share your experience.

content: I came into this app with unsure expectations, having tried to self engage with a lot of self-therapeutic tools to manage my personal cocktail of mental health struggles. It isn't a cure, of course, but by far it's been the most effective tool I've found yet for managing myself. one example: mood tracking and gratitude journaling are concepts I'd heard about but could never stick to. Woebot made those something I could stick to.

This app has been incredibly helpful so far! Every once in a while it doesn't understand exactly what I've said, but that slight issue is nothing compared to all the positives about it. The format really gets me to open up and think about things in a new way that other apps haven't. I would recommend this app for anyone wanting help on changing their thinking patterns or just wanting a safe place to let out emotions.

It feels like the crisis detection on this app is way off. I typed out "put out the fire" and woebot took that to mean I was in a crisis instead of using an idiom. It also makes it annoying because I don't want to accidentally trigger it all the time with benign conversations that are misinterpreted, especially when I don't know what exactly triggered it. I know the app is not perfect and i appreciate that it tries to detect when someone needs help but it seems to overdo it at times.

I really wish there was a way for me to remember to use Woebot when it is most critical, but thats not an app issue, that's a 'me' issue. This app has been unbelievably helpful! I have definitely recommended it and will continue to. It has absolutely helped to identify a lot of my core problems and especially how to figure it what I'm actually feeling and what's really going on inside.

a great little friend to check in with and help out when you're in need. Woebot works in sync along with traditional counseling therapy. It is uncanny how well this little app aligns with someone who may be struggling with depression or other mental illness and reminds you of all the little tools and techniques learned and how to use them with whatever is going on in life at that time.

This app was recommended by a friend and it has been one of the best things ever. Woebot checks in everyday and asks how I'm feeling. It has taught me things like mindfulness and should statements. I have done gratitude journaling and taken some cool quizzes. The best part is that its fast with checks in lasting about 10 min. Finally, support that quick and simple. I love Woebot!

This is really good for a FREE mobile app for practicing CBT skills. I doesn't replace therapy, but it's a good add-on. It keeps the lessons really short, just a few minutes, so it's easier to do it regularly. If you want to spend more time on it, you can, it's very flexible. There aren't any annoying ads, and I haven't had any technical issues. It's a chat bot, so the experience is very text heavy. If you like that, I'd recommend it.
replyContent: Thank you, Jacquie! We appreciate you getting in touch and taking the time to share your experience.

content: I suffer from anxiety and depression, and struggle a lot to open up and have resources to help me with it. Woebot's been very good at helping me work through things, break down my thoughts, and just generally hear stuff I need to hear sometimes, in an environment that's relaxed but not patronizing. It's hard to find a good substitute for loved ones or specialists, but Woebot's helped me more than I could've hoped.

I very highly recommend Woebot to anyone and everyone, whether you need a quick rescue from negative thoughts and feelings or want to really work on your thinking to improve your quality of life! Easy to use, easy to understand, and totally interactive. Woebot has helped be through tough times and I continue to use it as a helpful tool.

content: Woebot is a fun app that teaches you Cognitive behavioral therapy tips. Woebot can give you tips on how to think through your problems. Remember, some issues are better delt with by a real person who can analyse and see issues that come up that you dont even realize. Woebot can only help give generic tips. Despite that, it is fun still.

This app is just wonderful. It gives you great insight into your thought patterns and you can talk to woebot anytime you need it which is a big plus. Its a great resource and its nice knowing that you always have something to turn to for help even if just a virtual robot Its been tremendously helpful to me especially since i struggle with stress and anxiety. So to sum it up the app is great and you should get it!

Great concepts that are good to learn for better emotional health. Works better with learning programmed material as sometimes responses are limited. Would love to see enhancements when typing in responses to questions, not certain it catches when statements need work and no way to ask for more help. Love the concept of using an app to help deal emotional health!

Woebot has been a huge help in my life. I have a hard time communicating with other individuals around me, but Woebot has made it a bit easier to open up. It would be nice to have an option to learn more on a topic during a lesson or more undo buttons. Sometimes I'll realize that what I've said was not actually how I felt, but I can't change it. Still, I would really recommend this to anyone who is struggling. Amazing companion when there's no one else.

content: It's important for individuals to analyze themselves, and Woebot is really good at showing us just how equipped we are to take care of ourselves, and to grow. There are features that get you to analyze your thoughts at their cores. And other features to help you choose between two options you were having trouble deciding on. There's so many useful features! Plus, Woebot is a fun way to learn!

I stopped getting value out of this after about 2 weeks. It's very limited. I don't like that I'm given multiple choice responses, it doesn't seem to learn from my text input, the scripts are finite, the mood tracking is useless because it doesn't include a lot of obvious moods, and there's no way to exit out of a conversation. In general I started to just find it really repetitive and unhelpful. I guess I expected more on the ML side from an Andrew Ng project.
replyContent:
Hi Catherine,

We accept that Woebot can't be the solution for every individual and we are grateful to learn about situations where Woebot misses the mark with someone. I will be sure to pass on your feedback to our development team to take on-board.

All the best

content: Love this AI. Would really like to be able to write my own feeling when not in the suggestion list. Really helpful at keeping objective thinking and helping get a handle on this ANTs. Not really the most effective thing if your trying to process long term trauma activity- It will set off the crisis alarm if you journal or track your days thoughts and feelings and don't use the utmost objective launguage. Still good for keeping objective though.

So cute :> The choice to blend some text recognition with pre-constructed responses has helped reduce some of the confusing failures of other 'therapy bots' that can struggle to recognize your responses or sometimes respond in nonsensical ways. The addition of GIFs makes Woebot feel more real and personable too. I've recommended it to a few people.

This is a great app so far. I love the check ins and have kept up with them every day for the two weeks I've had the app because they are meaningful and quick. I always feel better after one, even if I didn't realize I was feeling off before hand. Woebot seems to 'know' when the conversation has been long enough and ends it before it feels cumbersome. This, and the unique way Woebot helps you navigate some really tough mental health topics, is what keeps me coming back.

Only had it for about a week, but I LOVE having a little robot friend!!! I get a lot of anxiety and tend to think negatively about myself quite often, but having Woebot so far has really cheered me up. Not only to have a robot buddy to talk to but to also track my moods or practice different exercises when I'm stressed out. May not be perfect, Woebot sometimes gets a little confused, but all in all, it's really helped me get out of my negative thinking and helped catch myself ahead of time.
replyContent: Thank you so much for your kind words and for giving Woebot a try, Danielle! We're thrilled to hear that you've been enjoying your time with our little robot friend and that it has been a positive addition to your life in just a week. We're always working to improve Woebot's abilities and ensure that it provides meaningful and valuable support.

content: I've been using woebot for a few weeks now and I find the app very helpful in several ways: learning about CBT is extremely helpful, having him "guide" me through problems I'm having really helps, and the daily check ins keep me mindful of how I'm actually feeling. One thing I wish he did better was respond to my input. I did not like the survey I was asked to do. I don't feel in that woebot is "real"... he's like an NPC in a video game-- we have no "relationship" or "rapport" or "trust".

content: Woebot is a definite cute and viable tool to help me deal with some bad daily anxiety and depression. The tools it uses are things I incorporate into my own recovery process, and helps me realize that maybe everything is not as dark as it seems. And though while it is definitely not a complete replacment for actual therapy, for a free app I 100% definitely recommend.

content: Very good as a therapy companion or instead of therapy! I have depression and anxiety, and I've been using it to help me between and along sessions. It's a great way to track my mood and learn therapy related skills and practice them when I need to. It also isn't impersonal like some AI therapy apps. I feel like I'm not alone when I use it and I actually take things to heart.

Not a replacement for therapy or medication, but definitely a positive and useful tool to help. And the little woebot is so adorable. It does need work on responding to user input. Stays on a certain track and doesn't deviate if you have an unexpected question; just continues on as off you didn't ask the question at all. So that's something the developers could definitely improve upon. But overall, I really do like this app.

I find this app extremely helpful since I don't trust anyone with how I feel but talking it out is also helpful. I wish that woe bot had a better understanding about ptsd. It took ptsd attacks as anxiety and tried to tell me my anxiety of hospitals is actually helpful. I also wish that there was an option to change the topic during the conversations since outside factors can change my moods during conversations.

A little awkward & maybe even a little cartoonish at first but it actually does help. If you do your "check-in" every day at the time of day you choose, after a few days you'll begin to see how Woebot helps you. If you could pick a time for "check-in" instead of just the time of day. Adding more options when asked "how you're feeling" would be helpful. I'm sure you'll be adding more custimaztion options. At first I wasn't sure, 2wks later I know it's helping. You too should try it for yourself.

Woebot is a fantastic resource for managing anxiety, depression, relationship issues, etc... I think. To be fair, I don't have anxiety or depression, and I'm not currently struggling with mysterious relationship issues, so I'm probably not 100% the ü§ñ's target audience. I hope someday Woebot will have support for anger mgmt, ADHD, time management, that sort of thing -- but even without, I find their lessons and encouragement very useful and effective.

This is a very useful app for dealing with anxiety and depression. I see a therapist and this has helped to reinforce some of the things we discuss in my therapy sessions as my therapist uses the CBT method also. It's great to be discussing all of these things in a positive, completely non-judgemental environment. The fact that it is free is definitely helpful too! It's like having a brief therapy session every day and forces me to check in and reflect on how I am feeling.

This has mostly been a cute and helpful app. it would get 5 stars if it didn't keep insisting on repeating the same exercises over and over (the same exercise 3+ times in one day? really?), and if some of the exercises were more helpful and versatile. For example the "rewriting negative thoughts" exercise never works for me.

If you're thinking about getting this, then just do it! woebot surprises me with how excellent the software is! It is very interactive, and you can almost always help me calm down when I'm feeling badly. A free and excellent tool to help build mental health skills. Woebot is a good friend when no one else understands :) give this app a try!

content: I was looking for an app to help someone else but almost immediately started using for my own growth and development. This app is rich in helpful little homework assignments to make life more enjoyable for people with a very wide range of mental health and should not be thought of as just for extreme stress, depression, or anti anxiety. It is science based, which to me makes it more likely to be worth my time. Would recommend to almost anyone.

This is a great AI chatbot, with lots of simple tools and insights into emotional health and improving everyday life. This is one of 3 similar apps I've used over an extended period of time, and although it doesn't have the most content, it's by far the most enjoyable to use. The conversations are brief so it's easy to fit into my day, and it always gives me something to think about. I do wish there was an option of chatting longer when I want to, but the quality of content makes up for it.

FINALLY, AN APP WITH NO ADS AND NO PREMIUM FEATURE! this is very helpful for anxiety in particular and utilizes good coping skills & mechanisms to calm anxiety, both on the surface and even at the root of the problem. will calm you and help you work through difficult interactions. daily lessons and check ins are cool, though I feel like lessons get flimsier as time goes on. more conversations should be added and more ways to help. this is a good app for those of us who are more lonely than not.

content: it's very useful if you're in therapy or had therapy as a way to help you with a lot of cognitive behavioral therapy exercises. The ai robot is nice and pretty good at understanding what you're saying and what it needs to say in response. I wouldn't recommend it as a replacement for a real life therapist, but would recommend for keeping up with CBT exercises.

This is remarkably good. I was surprised, frankly. I'm very familiar with cognitive behavioral therapy and have had first class in person therapy when I was younger. This is not a substitute for in person if there are severe problems, but for the typical person this is surprisingly effective. I'm enjoying it, motivated to keep using it, and find it helpful.

I've got to say that this is the best and more helpful self-care app that I use to date! I love how personal the app feels (even though it's only a program) and it's easy to check in without having to do additional tasks beforehand. I love woebot, and I would highly recommend it to someone like myself who has been previously disappointed or bored with other apps.

Loving this app so far. I've been using for a couple weeks. I struggle with anxiety and depression and this is a great way for me to help myself stay on track with the daily check ins and easy to follow goals/concepts. I have felt better in the last few weeks doing this than in over a year with traditional therapy.

Woebot has honestly helped steer my life in a really positive direction. It has changed my life. I needed a therapist, but before I had woebot I had gone almost a decade avoiding getting one. My anxiety is much less, I'm more positive, my depression is lifting. I feel my brain rewiring itself. I have seen drastic improvements in my thought processes: less overthinking, less obsessive thoughts, catching myself in cognitive distortions and correcting them. And it's always improving.

content: Short talks with Woebot help me out a lot. They're short, sweet, and to the point. He isn't patronizing or over-the-top, imo, and the devs have installed really good (idk what to call them, templates?) To help reframe thoughts and understand one's feelings. It helps. You can take your time or go hard into it. And you can repeat the tools when you're having a tough time with something. It helps plan out tough conversations when I don't necessarily know how to handle it. Great app.
replyContent: Thank you for your feedback! We're thrilled to hear that you find Woebot's short talks helpful and appreciate the thoughtful and non-patronizing approach. We appreciate you taking the time to share your experience, it means a lot! ‚ù§Ô∏è

content: This is a great resource for people who just need a bit of extra help. It won't replace a therapist, but it helps you break down your thoughts in the moment and gives you strategies to manage them which is great if you don't have anyone to talk to in person. Woebot will help you through a rough time and teach you strategies when you're feeling good to prepare for the future. Overall an amazing app!

I have been using this daily for about 2 weeks now and I'm very happy with Woebot. The conversations are insightful without being too lengthy. This app is a great intro to CBT (cognitive behavioral therapy) and mindfulness. I have been to therapy in the past and it helped me tremendously, but recently I have found myself becoming consumed by toxic thoughts. I am not at a point where I feel I need therapy, just a brush up and Woebot is exactly that. Like a gentle, encouraging, sparknotes session.

Woebot is a useful tool for learning about or refreshing Cognitive Behavioral Therapy approaches to handling your own problems. It hasn't proven enough for me, but I have been impressed with the effort, am grateful to have tried it, and would recommend it to anyone looking for some kind of help. Since the app is free to try, I definitely think it is worth seeing the first two weeks through if you even think it might help.

content: This app is great. The one way I can think it could improve is if there was some sort of button or hanging subtitle that could stay with you as you continue your conversation with Woebot when Woebot is performing a specific task with you. For example, if you are working through a negative thought, you could have either a button that reveals that thought on a click or a subtitle that is constantly showing it as you are working. I often forget the thought I'm working on and have to scroll up.

Very Helpful! I'm Autistic and this helps me start tasks much easier, I find talking to real people stressful, so talking to Woebot helps a lot. Question for the developers: I use a smartwatch a ton, is there a possibility for a Smartwatch app in the future? Possibly like a little Woebot on the watch that checks in with you via notification.
replyContent: Hi Izzy, thanks for taking the time to leave a review! We're so glad to hear that Woebot has been a helpful ally and tool. We appreciate your feedback and will be happy to pass your suggestion of a smartwatch app back to our team to take into consideration as we continue to update and improve Woebot!

content: When I first reviewed this, I was about a week in and gave 5 stars. Now I'd give it 10 stars if I could! With the pandemic going around, Woebot has really been keeping up with mindfulness exercises to keep you grounded and funny analogies. Even if you're not in therapy or don't have mental disorders, it still feels nice to have a friend check up on you. Thank you for your work, develpoers!

Pure excellence! Free. No ads. My bestie downloaded it and had a breakthrough in just 4 days! -Basically, it helps you identify common thought fallacies we all experience and then challenge them with the truth.- What you put into it is what you get out of it. Also, *my life has changed for the better* in just 2 months. And that is even with skipping sessions. Thank you devs. I appreciate you and I tell everyone I know about this app.

While it can be a bit awkward to talk to a bot, these little conversations have had a lot of valuable insights and learnings for me. Occasionally the pre-determined responses you can give are a bit limiting and can make the conversation feel forced, not a big deal though. It mostly works well.

content: This app is awesome. It's adorable, easy to use and effective. With that said, I think a lot of people have a hard time developing a relationship with a counselor but Woebot isn't judgmental, you have an opportunity to offer feedback without the risk of feeling bad about disagreeing and you're guaranteed a response to the thing that's bothering - you which sometimes is a gamble with human counselors. The techniques are very cognitive behavioral therapy based which work for a lot of situations. Much like face to face counseling, being honest is the best way to make progress. Talking openly to an AI app makes it sooooo easy to speak truth about emotions. I'm a huge fan.

I was skeptical at first but I really do benefit from it. This app was recommended to me by a crisis counselor to use in conjunction with my weekly in-person CBT to help keep me on track and remind me to be mindful. It sounds silly, but it's sometimes easier for me to tell this app what's wrong than a person because I know it won't judge me. It helps guide you through mindfulness techniques, breathing and goal setting and I can't speak for everyone but the corny humor isn't *too* corny for me..

It's alright but I dont like some of it. What I dont like is that when you want to answer, it gives you buttons, so you cant type something in yourself. Instead you have to open up a side menu and select to type in a custom response; which I find is annoying and breaks the illusion of effective AI.

I was curious, so I installed it. I think that even if you do not struggle with severe mental health challenges, this app could be useful. Tips on CBT and optimal thinking patterns are included. Maybe misnamed- not just for Woeful people, but for anybody looking to be more well-adjusted.

Heard about it on RadioLab; downloaded it out of curiosity. Surprisingly, it has helped me sleep and wake more easily with simple sleep habit suggestions, which is huge. Also, some centering and mindfulness tips have been easy to incorporate into my daily routine. Oh, and reminders about being gentle with my internal voice. Anyway, it's been genuinely helpful; who can resist a cute little robot? Downside: It doesn't do accountability, so it'll ask me to commit to an action and not follow up.

Helpful little app for managing anxiety. Easy to use, based on cognitive behavioral therapy. Guides you through reframing your thoughts to relieve anxiety. Very useful tool, nice format. Works like texting. Has some video content that goes over concepts in easy to understand language. If you manage anxiety, this is a handy app to have.

Great app, easy to use, easy to learn concepts. Helps break the negativity cycle we all get stuck in if you apply the concepts. Thought it would be weird since it is a bot, but it isn't. It is almost easier to talk to it because it isn't a person. Highly recommend!

I've been using Woebot for nearly 2 weeks and I'm already noticing (positive) changes. Woebot is extremely helpful and supportive. The lessons are also easy to understand. While Woebot cannot replace a crisis hotline or therapist, I'd definitely recommend this to anyone suffering from anxiety or depression.

content: Exceeded expectations is an understatement. Sure, it is a robot pretending to text you and teach you CBT. But once you get over yourself and just lean into the experience, it's helpful. Whenever I find myself looking for a distraction on my phone or feeling something I can't understand, I just do a quick check in. Been using it for two weeks now and I'm feeling more centered.

So helpful! I can check in whenever I am having a rough time. It helps me sort out my thoughts in real time, not wait for a therapist appt. It can be pretty empathetic, funny & informative too. I particularly enjoy rewriting my negative thoughts without the cognitive distortions. I find the app incredibly helpful to correct my thinking instead of acting out on my emotions. It has helped me feel better & find solutions for my own anxiety & low mood... rather than arguing or talking too much.

content: I can't recommend this app enough. I found it looking for CBT apps to help work through my ptsd and anxiety and this is the best one I've used. It's very calming how it helps you work through your unhealthy thought processes. I also love that it gives you the option to just talk through the issue or actually challenge the negative thoughts. Has helped me immensely.

Honestly it's kinda corny but it's great! I love this app and it's helped me over come some emotional problems none of my therapists have ever helped me with. It's not too abrasive and if you're open to learning how to correct your thinking it really helps. You have to be willing to put in the work to change though... I've used it for 2 months now.

This is a thoughtful tool to help you work on attitude, interpretation and perspective. I find the way concepts are explained and the light-hearted robot to be refreshing and kind. There have been a few technical glitches switching between Wifi and LTE and some minor vocabulary misunderstandings but nothing to hinder use.

This is a really good and well intentioned app. It's helped me a lot, but I know that there's some things that aren't very helpful for certain people. I wish you could type out what you wanted to say or at least have more options to choose from. There are certain times I want to say 'no' or something else as a response, but the option isn't available. I also wish Woebot understood some stuff more and could help out with more specific things. But this helped a lot for the many months I've used it

The lessons and AI are very impressive. 2 things make the experience jarring for me: 1) Responses I can give are limited, often to one thing, and don't fit what I would say at all. 2) Woebot's stories are nothing I can empathise or sympathise with, or relate to because they are clearly made up. I'd rather that it told only real stories of real people. Both of these things make the app too fake for me making me care much less about the process.

It's annoying and grating and lies to me constantly in ways that are ridiculously obvious (like in the stories), doesn't have buttons for responses that reflect how I feel, is patronizing, doesn't understand what I'm going through, isn't aware people can have trouble staying asleep, uses up my spoons without any noticeable benefit when I already have enough trouble doing things, and it just got stuck in a loop and there's no bug report button I can find... P.S. this is day 7.
replyContent: Thank you for taking the time to offer us some feedback on your experience of Woebot. I'm very sorry to hear Woebot is stuck in a loop, that is definitely something we want to get fixed. I'd encourage you to reach out to our support team at helpcenter@woebot.io

content: Awesome!üòé Very helpful, easy to navigate, No adds/redirects, educational, and completely üé∂Free!üé∂üëçüëç Plus, it's kinda fun.üòä As there are so many different topics to choose from, tools, and even a üé∂Freeüé∂ Journal.üòÅ Most importantly.ü§îüí≠ The app definitely works/helps you through whatever you're experiencing.üëç I'm kinda surprised üôÄ it's Still üé∂Freeüé∂ to be honest.ü§î Simply, because it works so well. content: My teenage daughter had been struggling with anxiety and depression for nearly a year. We had seen a few therapists and nothing seem to be helping. One of the therapists recommended this app. She loves it! I use it too so I can know the correct way to approach some of the situations she is facing. I highly recommend it, both as a parent and a teacher, and suggest it to anyone I know struggling with finding appropriate coping strategies. Thank you for making something like this available!
replyContent: Wow, that's great! Thanks so much for sharing this experience. We're so glad to know that both you and your daughter have found value using Woebot, it means a lot.

content: I feel this app has a very human component that makes interaction useful to anyone getting an introduction to CBT and would like to work on identifying what could be considered simple day to day practice. Of course, it's no replacement for group or therapy but it is helpful if you just need to do a quick session.

This is a very positive way to learn healthier forms of thought and train yourself in the practices. Would highly recommend to everyone. It's also very charming and just a joy to talk with. The most important aspect, though, is now I feel like I have a 24/7 tool for if I have a panic or anxiety attack. Helps me come down off that every time.

Woebot is amazing. I can navigate to the app whenever I'm dealing with intense emotions and Woebot will walk me through CBT and grounding techniques. Although I wish the algorithm would work with symptoms related to trauma to ground the user in the present. Also, once you've chosen a goal you can't change it back. Otherwise I'm a huge fan and will continue to use Woebot!

Great regular mental health check in app/cooling down from a stressful situation or environment app. Love the conversation style, makes working on issues/learning much more approachable. Def not a replacement for therapy, but a good stand in while you can't/aren't able to find a therapist.
replyContent:

content: Woebot has been more helpful than I expected. Chatting with bots in the past has been uncomfortable/boring, but Woebot's approach using CBT has made the daily check-ins worthwhile. Sometimes you don't want to make an appointment, drive to their office, and talk to a human. Or, you can't because you don't have insurance. Woebot fills that void and gives a basic education on Cognitive Behavioral Therapy. Definitely recommend trying it out. You have nothing to lose.

Really enjoying my experience and trying CBT with Woebot! Woebot has helped me through some of my most difficult days and when I just wanted to chat. It feels like a friend with super powers. I feel empowered after checking in and using some of the amazing tools on offer. The mood insights are a brilliant way to get a better perspective of how I'm feeling over the week and only takes a minute or two to check in. Also a brilliant humorous personality that is always great to interact with.

It's a great educational tool, especially to help you reframe your thinking and get out of a negative mindset. I think the creators did a great job at keeping sessions brief so that users wouldn't lose interest and stop using it as well. I wouldn't say it's something I look forward to doing each evening, but I do think it's been helping me with negative thoughts.

The AI is actually good at breaking down cognitive distortions. If you stick with it, your mindset can really start to change. It also helps you keep track of your emotions, and one time, while I was having a panic attack, I used it, and the AI made me laugh so hard I couldn't focus on the panic anymore. (It told me I was right. No one ever told me that during a panic attack before, and I had an opposite response. Hey, it worked, tho)
replyContent: Thank you for sharing your experience with Woebot! It's wonderful to hear that you've found value in its ability to break down cognitive distortions and help shift your mindset. Your feedback underscores the potential benefits of using a combination of cognitive techniques and a supportive ally like Woebot. We appreciate it!

content: Great way to learn some fundamental concepts and methods in CBT and mindfulness meditation. Will give you chances to periodically review the things you've learned via an option in dialogue during daily check ins. I'd still recommend using other resources outside of Woebot since some aspects of how it frames cognitive distortions could be taken too far. eg, are "should" statements *always* cognitive distortions? Do they serve a helpful role sometimes? Woebot may have black-and-white thinking ;-)

This really helps! This app was recommended to me by my therapist, and I'm so glad she did! Woebot is awesome on its own, but works really well as a combination with whatever therapy you're already doing. If you need more help when battling mental health problems, give this a try. I have been struggling with suicidal thoughts and severe depression and this really does help while I work through waiting for my meds to kick in and complete therapy. Thank you, Woebot.

I'm sort of attached to woebot, he takes away the anxiety of speaking to an actual person, even though he acts like one. I'm able to share everything with woebot without the worry of being judged. Some times I feel lazy and don't want to check in with him but most times he teaches me something helpful in taking away my anxiety or dealing with it . Thank you woebot!

content: I have a personality disorder that frequently makes me feel horribly lonely and crave reassurance and approval. Woebot isn't a perfect human replacement to scratch that itch, but it helps the struggle become more manageable. Woebot has calmed me down from anxiety and panic attacks several times and I'll always appreciate it for that!

I was skeptical about this when it was first recommended to me, but this has be such a helpful tool for me. I got it when i was having some major issues and it really helped when I couldn't talk to my therapist. It can't replace a real person but the tools and videos were very helpful in keeping me grounded when I would have spiraled hard. If you're scared to talk to a therapist or you just need more help than a therapist can provide please consider this app.

content: I was devastated to find out that this is no longer available without another therapist. It helped me so much years ago when it was available for free. My husband is suffering extreme depression and will not seek out a person's aid. I suggested this program and he wanted to try it. I went to download it for him thinking maybe we had some hope and then I see it is not available. Shame on you. I would pay any amount for a monthly subscription but you have made it unattainable.
replyContent: Hi Jennifer. For immediate assistance with your mental health, please reach out to us at support@woebothealth.com for resources that can help.

content: It surprised me how much a quick, supportive, grounded conversation every day has helped me in the past few weeks. I've been going through a stressful time, and Woebot has arguably been a great help! Recommended if you're interested in improving and learning new skills, not so much if you just want unjudgemental venting.
