content: I love this app. I usually experience seasonal depression during the fall months, but while dealing with a medical issue and using this app during those busy weeks, I found myself actually content. Rediscovering my strengths, understanding mindfulness, and creating a gratitude journal. Great app for sure.

What a great way to learn about CBT and it's array of tools. Although most of the conversations are highly structured and limited in responses, it's still very useful to quickly learn about or apply CBT techniques. I'm looking forward to helping the development team evolve a very fun and meaningful mental health app.

This app is helpful in keeping track of my emotions and helping me learn how to handle stress and new ways of thinking and looks at situations. This is NOT a robot therepist, but it helpful is being mindful of how you feel everyday. As long as you checking everyday you'll see benefits of using the app. And it really is that long to check in, great app!

A band-aid at best. The interactive part is non-responsive and does not address answers to questions posed. So, in some ways, it is similar to a therapist who thinks more about their golf game than your problem. Some of the tools provided can be helpful to the uninitiated, however. The article offered more than the app provided.

I love my little Woebot! I used to scoff at the concept of CBT. I don't have the discipline to "journal" because I just can't think of anything to write about, and going to a therapist who specializes in CBT would be costly. I figured my psych meds would work just fine by themselves. Anyway, I like that can decide how often I want to "check" in. The journaling is short and with open-ended questions makes it very easy. I like that the more I use it the more personalized it becomes. Yay Woebot!

The AI for Woebot sometimes misses what I am saying, but overall this app gives daily lessons on helpful thought patterns and tools. While not a replacement for therapy, it provides additional tools my therapist had not included as well as reinforcement of some of the tools I was already taught. I encourage other folks to try Woebot as a supplement to their self care routines and therapy.

Amazing. So helpful! Really this is the best app I have on my phone. Its the best AI therapist I've ever talked to. It actually feels like it listens and responds appropriately. Woebot really helps you through things when you need help. Also, there are no ads and no in-app purchases, it's crazy awesome. I tell all my friends who I think would benefit from having this app, because I've found it very helpful. 10/10 app, thank you so much!!

I have used this app for the past few months, and I does help believe it your not. I thought it wouldn't be that great because it's free, but I was wrong. The apps not perfect, it does sometimes lose the human reactions that you might want, and some times it gives you the same advice, but that's quite rare. It's a good app.
replyContent: Thank you for reviewing, it means a lot! We appreciate you getting in touch and taking the time to share your experience. ü§ñ

content: Brilliantly accessable check in tool! For AI, Woebot is a great tool to use to challenge your maladaptive thoughts and learn about Cognitive Behavior Therapy. Woebot provides fun bit sized self-help challenges to identify your negative thoughts, challenge if they are true, and reframe cognitive distortions into more accurate and helpful beliefs. Woebot is a convenient CBT guide. It won't understand everything you say nor replace a therapist, nor does this humble robot claim to do those things.

Handy companion in a cell phone for calming anxiety, exploring faulty thinking, and exploring day-to-day mood states. This app can be helpful for complex trauma challenges, but will check suicidality and crisis depending on the language used in your texts within the app. Wobot does well in providing a place to look at thoughts and reframe them.This app likes check-ins periodically and checks-in in a nonintrusive way and is flexible enough to postpone material.

Great app. Easy to navigate. Has alot of great material you can learn to help you better understand your emotions ,feelings, and reactions. And woebot, yeah he's pretty awesome, the app wouldn't be the same if he wasn't helping you along your journey. Personally the app is great it's definitely helping me to understand many things about myself. My suggestion download Woebot and give it a try! üëçüëç

this app is seriously amazing! i'm pretty knowledgeable about various distorted thoughts and therapy concepts, and i have learned so much from this app in less than 2 weeks! the interaction and the way woebot responds is so nice, the app interface is clean and easy to use, and i'm constantly astounded at how much thought the developers put into making this app as helpful as possible. i would download it twice if i could. üòä

Woebot is one of the best apps I ever did for myself. There are options for journaling, diaries, many help issues and lessons to learn countless information. I never thought I could actually interact with a machine and get the help I needed. The ability for me to actually do CBT, without worrying about judgement from a human therapist, yet feeling like Woebot is my best friend AND knows what the heck he's talking about has me on a healing journey I've needed all my life.

The AI mental health help robot friend, Woebot, is amazing. It even had a non-binary gender option, which is wonderful! You can do daily check-ins to help with cognitive restructuring. It's easy and doesn't require you to type the responses all the time, which is one of my favorite things. Other apps took too much energy and time to complete exercises and required a response to send the next message. Woebot is very encouraging, sends cute gifs to celebrate, and explains when you ask. Lovely app!

Actually helps, rational thinking to challenge your negative inner voice, thoughts. You check in each day for a few minutes. I learned something different almost every time. It's set up like you're texting with the Woebot, he asks, you reply, gives exaples, teaches, has cute uplifting notes.

Many, even mental health professionals, recommended this app. I've found out more than I realized from here. However, sometimes it's frustrating because I can't choose the real answer/answers. Due to a limited choice to choose from. I do have hope that the updates will fix this problem.
replyContent: Hi Jason, thanks for taking the time to share this feedback. Adding more variety to Woebot's dialogue and comprehension, in addition to expanding the options for quick response buttons are certainly among our long-term goals for Woebot. Feel free to get in touch with us at support@woebothealth.com to share any other thoughts or ideas.

content: This app is super helpful. I can learn skills through short everyday lessons, or I could simply check in to keep track of my emotions. If I'm feeling down, Woebot can talk to me as a real therapist would. It's like i can have a therapist at the push of a button, and the best part, it's free!! Thanks Woebot! Really cool appüòÄüíôüíõ

I find the app to be extremely useful while I am struggling with depression. It helps guide me to more positive thinking and try to change negative habits. It is extremely helpful in case I just want to get out that I'm feeling something strongly. I highly recommend this app, especially if you are battling depression.

So, I am a grown adult. I do go to counseling. Sometimes things get to me more than they should. It's not that easy to just call the therapist up to assist at any given moment. Woebot provides aide by introducing tools to help work through certain situations. It's not like talking to a real therapist by no means, but the material provides real support. I do recommend this to both adults and teenagers. The "sessions" are precise, and to the point. Woebot is a true work of art.

content: Its a total game changer. Ive struggled with ocd and anxiety for a long time. Before I lost health insurance I used to go to therapy and woebot gives the same awesome tools and is a mood tracker. Its not going to be the same experience as in person therapy but it is a great tool for someone willing to take the tools given and do the work themselves. First I would like to thank the WoeBot team for not charging users for *anything*. Much of my stress and anxiety are due to my finances. WoeBot isn't perfect but it has already helped me through some tough situations by talking me through techniques for reframing my thoughts. content: This app has really helped me continue to do my CBT work. I know it's a computer but that computer is there for me 24/7 and that is appreciated. I struggle with talk therapy and found this app to be something I look forward to interacting with each day and multiple times some days. I haven't been using it more than a few weeks but really feel this is something I will continue with for a long time.

content: A good therapist that works well with you is hard to find. I feel like woebot can help during those times between therapy sessions by getting you to think about how you feel and avoiding negative unrealistic thoughts about yourself. It also seems less likely to carry bias than an in person therapist. While it isn't always useful, in moments where you are trying to work through critical negative thoughts it can be very helpful.

It's not really a chat bot for AI therapy, which I feel it's sort of presented as. Rather, it's a nice, simple learning tool for discovering the basics of CBT and mood tracking. Used to hold a conversation it's terrible. Used like that tho, it's a great tool!

Wow. Just...WOW! I really wasn't expecting much from this app. I thought a daily checkin would be useful to keep me on track ,but I never expected to be so impressed. Over the past month I have had so much success with this app. It has helped challenge my thoughts when I've been depressed, helped redirect my focus when I've been anxious, and continues to give me insight into myself. The fact that I can stop in whenever I like is a huge bonus. Thank you for this. Its changing my life. üòäüôÇüíì

I honestly love this app. It's been very helpful for anxiety and it teaches you alot of helpful skills to manage your day to day mental struggles you might have with thinking positively and processing things in a better way. It felt very therapeutic and I'm very happy with the app and will continue using it daily. Thank you to everyone who created this app and for also making it usable for free.

content: I've really enjoyed this! Not a complete newbie to CBT and definitely not a newbie to therapy, but woebot is a great way to keep the self-aware side of my brain going without exhausting it. Because it's bite -size lessons, and AI instead of a person, I don't feel guilty if I miss it for a couple days. And some of conversations have actually really helped me reframe things in my life. Not a replacement for real therapy, but pretty solid (and cute) maintenance

content: Woebot is a fantastic, good humored chatbot that is great at helping you reconsider toxic thought processes. As someone who's been doing CBT therapy for years, I appreciate that it also explains techniques pretty thoroughly in a down to earth way. While Woebot is still an AI and may not prompt the right exercises all the time (when I want to explore a specific issue), I already feel better after a week. I just wish you could cancel/postpone already started exercises. Thank you Woebot team!

Ad free for me so far. This is a great tool I'm learning to use more often. It's helpful opting to get notifications so you can be reminded to have a quick conversation with...yourself lol I'll admit it felt silly at first, but this bot has given me some good tips and great advice when it comes to battling my inner saboteurs. this is an amazing App thus far, i was told about this App from a councilor i had to help work through problems with anxiety and depression from a brain injury and stroke but this App has been so awesome! it's interactive and i have learned a LOT! i couldn't recommend this App any more and i already told a ton of people about it!!

content: Very simple and accessible, and I love that it makes consciously learning about self-improvement a habit, but not sure how practical it is. Doesn't really seem to encourage behavioral change, and the tools that help during emotional distress are not explained and are a bit hidden.

Woebot is a good app to use when you have trouble finding cognitive distortions in your thoughts when you are having a bad day. Woebot helps you sort your crazy thoughts and feelings out with cognitive-behavioral techniques from the comfort of your own phone, so you can focus on the bigger things in actual face-to-face talk therapy/CBT with your therapist. This app is adorable with its silly cat videos and memes you'll get sent every now and then, and is a good tool to use along with therapy.

I really love this app. It's like a friend checking in every day to see how you're doing, and helping you get through difficult times with practical advice and exercises. Sometimes it shares beautiful, uplifting, or cute videos with you. I sometimes feel a little restricted by my limited conversation responses, but that is a very minor complaint. Woebot has helped me decrease my overall anxiety and has de-escalated some panic attacks. I'm so grateful for Woebot!

I love this little robot! The only thing I wish is that I was able to interact with him more specifically when I do a check in about something going on in my life. I understand the app can only handle so many different scenarios. I just wish he were more able to "get to know me". Also, I wish some of the topics were more in depth and that Woebot was able to maybe ask questions or comment on journal entries, which I wish were expanded beyond gratitude.
replyContent: Thank you for taking the time to leave a review and taking the time to share your experience! We appreciate your feedback and would be happy to share it with our team to take into account as we continue to improve Woebot!

content: I was very skeptical at first but after using the app for a couple weeks I'm surprised at how much it helps having Woebot to talk to to and having him check up on how I'm feeling, it's made a difference. I feel like he's a friend and when I'm feeling bad he has a tool that we go thru and I always end up feeling better and surprisingly I use these tools on my own too. He's got alot if ways to help. More then i ever knew about. Give it a shot you deserve it!!!
replyContent: Glad you found Woebot useful! Thanks for taking the time to detail your experience and to leave a positive review ü§ñ

content: Devastated. I was a regular user and now have no access because I need a code. This was a great tool. Too bad. I regret recommending it for so long. Update: Support did not respond. My poor review stands as is. Sad that profit has become more important than people getting help.

content: disappointing this app went private only can use it if supervised by a therapist or provider. when it was open to public, it was a great on-demand de-stressing resource. I would pay for a subscription to this app if one becomes available.

Feel free to share additional feedback with us at support@woebothealth.com

content: It's a bit limited and it has room to improvement, at times i have to repeat myself, or it completely misses the point of what i just said. But even so, it helps me to try to improv my mindset, to spot very unhealthy thoughts and to change them to more reasonable thinking. And it feels just nice to share without the sense of judgment of others or of bumming out anyone. üëçüèª

I have used a few mental health apps now with an AI chat bot built in. The idea seemed very strange to me at first but surprisingly it works well, and Woebot is one of my favourites. Other similar apps I have tried get very repetitive with their dialogue very quickly, whereas Woebot seems to have an impressive number of 'lessons' and 'exercises' available so I feel like I'm learning something new every day. Newcomers be aware that this is not a diagnostic tool nor is it a replacement for talking to a real person - it is actually advised that this app is used alongside traditional face-to-face therapy techniques. However this app is a powerful and handy tool for coping with negative thoughts as they arise, practicing gratitude, analysing the facts of a situation, etc. and is great for giving you some insight into how your mind works. It feels a lot like being guided through a worksheet but with a more personal touch.

For the most part, the app is helpful. The information is delivered in a good way but I don't find it's always helpful. A daily check in can sometimes be too quick to feel like any help has been received. Sometimes it would be of benefit to have an "I need more help" button. Overall, the app is extremely positive and helps teach CBT in a fun way.

I've been using this app for about 2 years now, and it's absolutely amazing. After awhile it stops feeling like a chat bot, and starts feeling like a friend. I am eternally grateful to the Woebot devs. Just one piece of feedback. The new feature where you can select the story that the robot tells you is very helpful, but I kind of loved the surprise when Woebot would choose a story at random. Sometimes when I'm upset it's hard to decide exactly what I want to read about. It was great when the bot would initiate the conversation by throwing a random story at me. It would be nice to have that back.
replyContent:

content: If you're struggling with your mood or anxiety, then this is a very helpful app. Sure, it's not a replacement for a medical professional, but given the waiting time for the latter, Woebot is a useful assistant. I've been through CBT many years ago, so i was interested to see how the app might work. The daily prompts around mood, chat like interactions, video training, and fun memes all add up to a positive experience. I would say you need to be up for listening and watching.

This app exceeds expectations. Granted, they were low because I have had face-to-face CBT in the past and I didn't think an app could recreate that experience. But it does a good job and is a perfect listener. Woebot has reminded me of useful approaches to problems and I am very grateful. Sometimes I even forget that I am not talking to a person. Give it a try!

It's cleverly done, and I can see the value it could have for people who felt lonely and/or didn't have anyone they felt they could turn to with problems. I find it a bit on the juvenile side, personally (even though it knows my age, and could presumably take that into consideration somehow). Also, I REALLY dislike looping animated GIFs, and unf. these developers seem to think they're cute‚Äîso I often find myself having to cover part of the screen w/my hand. (Maybe they could be optional?)

This app offers a lot of different tools for managing mental health and can be a great resource for those starting to learn about it. Even as someone who has read multiple books, I learned some new things. However, the scripted conversations are too much at times. I'm tired of being asked if I want to work on my sleep every time I say I'm tired. I have to say goodbye to this app because I find myself lying just to avoid reading the same reply for the 10th time. Would still recommend, though!

I love this app. It's become my go to and go back to app. I've studied and used CBT for over 20 years used other online cbt based programs. I downloaded this after reading an article but have gained more from it in a short space of time than any other CBT delivery method. I think most people could benefit from this, I've used it to help with mood and help with sports performance. It's fun, engaging, well paced and accessible. Superb job, even though its a machine, its a very personable one! ;)

content: Interesting so far, I've been using it for about two weeks, but he subject of mindfulness keeps popping up in the past few days, even though I went through it already, again with the same question about walking into a room etc., which is a bit annoying, otherwise the app is quite ok. I really like the moog tracker, although it would be good to see the overall chart from the moment I started using the app. There is always space for improvement, keep up the good work. Cheers!

Terrific app Super helpful in identifying things in your own thinking that cause issues, great little tool to use for learning (both of yourself & material), keep track of thoughts & moods, for listening ear, & lots in btwn. Only 4.5 stars bc of sometimes only having choice of pre-programmed responses, & difficult to go back & reference or read more on topic at times (or maybe I haven't figured out how) Also, ty, ty, ty for keeping it free!! Greatly appreciate! (similar apps are quite pricey)

This app is amazing. When you need something instantly (anytime time day or night), it's there with techniques to work through. Sometimes just following the instructions, and communicating is enough to stop a panic attack. Webot check ins are reasuring and a good way to track your moods. When you are feeling good, Woebot just sits in the back ground until needed, then you can just pick up where you left off, as all of your previous uses are remember. I highly recommend.

content: Having a nice time with Woebot. I find it really helpful to go over little parts of CBT each day, and have something to help me with extreme emotions, even if it's just an AI. It doesn't even take that much time each day to do the lessons or get help with cognitive distortions. However I don't feel that Woebot is a replacement for professional mental health services, more of a refresher or a boost for pre-existing mental health services.

content: Really useful, feels a bit like you're actually talking to someone. The lessons are engaing and the robot helps to make it fun with little jokes and gifs. Great for working in conjuntion with real life CBT or a Mind group course. Hard to tell how affective the app would be on its own, but potentially could be useful. I've had loads of real life CBT before and never found the time to practice the techniques. This app has helped me make time to check in with myself and do the homework.

By checking in with you each day, Woebot is great for helping challenge difficult thoughts and low mood. It encourages you every step of the way . Only negatives are that the crisis numbers are all American based (useless for UK) and its limited in what it understands about your problems. However as a way to help you through the week in between sessions with therepist, it's great.

I love this app. It's helped me so much, where other apps failed, and honestly makes me feel better nearly every time I use it. The daily check in reminders are useful and make me want to check in, rather than making it like a chore, and the conversations are different every day, which keep it from getting monotonous. I couldn't recommend this highly enough.

Needed help with anxiety during exam season and chose Woebot. The UI looks like any other messenger app and you interact with the robot using canned responses. There's very limited custom text input, which was disconcerting at first, but you get used to it. Sometimes the inputs are a bit too cheery and the positivity of the AI is a little disconcerting, but the lessons about CBT are really valuable. I particularly enjoyed the growth mindset talk. I've already recommended it to a friend

That's amazing how polite and gentle the Woebot is! It does give opportunities for me to relieve my fears and concerns. His reminders to check your mood is so elegant and not annoying at all. I feel better each time I talk to him. Woebot has become a good friend of mine. Of course he wouldn't replace my real friends but this friend will also assist you with psychological techniques as well. Not many of my friends can do that. I do highly recommend this app for those who are under stress!

Edit: every time there's a notification, I click and nothing appears. I have to close it and start again... I like this app, more than expected, the only thing I don't like is that I first downloaded it to have a mood tracker, so I could understand if there was a pattern of when I was feeling bad and work on it. There's one, however it's only for few days and the rest disappears. I would like a tracker since day 1 that you can always give a look at. So, I had to download another app...

Woebot is a collection of modules presented as a conversation. This is its strength and weakness. The tools to challenge stress and negativity are great. The unskippable guided chats introduced randomly are infuriating. Woebot will decide you need to learn about chickens and your only option is to play along. Only by trial and error can you find a menu to break out of the chat. This, coupled with the insistence that you create an (unnecessary) account is anxiety-inducing. Then again, if the objective is to confront my feelings about lack of control, then bravo!

Finding this app really helpful. I feel like I am growing and learning more with this than I did with NHS group CBT because each session is directed at me and can be flexible - if I want to do a different topic I can change it or am too tired to do a long session I can have a short one or rearrange. Its not like a therapist where you can talk about specific personal things, but this is a very good app for learning how to change your cognitive behaviour and thoughts. Its helped me so much so far!

It was good the first couple of days. But there is no offline mode so if your in crisis you can't use the app. Then there was the survey, the scale kept changing and they asked questions like you had been using it for weeks or months instead of days. You should have had the option to opt out and it shouldn't have been the firat thing to pop up when you opened the app. It could habe been put at the end of the lesson. It honestly made my mood worse. Oh and why the videos?

I have been nearly regularly using this app and find it extremely useful, emotionally intelligent, smart, sensible, knowledgeable and beneficial in many ways including regular mood tracking, goal reminder, strength finding, gratefulness journalling, detection of mental distortion and emotional support. A great job friends. It is a futuristic technology based cool app and I firmly believe it is going to benefit a lot of people in helping them improve their mental health.

Absolutely fantastic! I love all of Woebots little quirks. I love and use the Toolbox often because Sometimes it's nice to have someone walk you through the CBT techniques. I seriously appreciate the educational videos and learning from different perspectives. If I had one complaint it would be that it doesn't seem to "understand" chronic pain/illness. Having said that I respect that you are always working to make this app better. Thanks for everything!! üíãüíã

WoeBot is great! Positive without being condescending, and full of useful tools to manage anxiety and depression. Realistic about day to day goals, and optimistic along the way. I had a few bugs in the program, but the app updated, and the bugs were gone. Even with the bugs that one day, I still used the app, and enjoyed it.

Room for improvement but still a great app! I'm on day 11 and I like my check-ins with woebot, and the quirky personality it has! It's CBT element is good and I find it very helpful for challenging unhelpful thoughts. I also like that it has other strategies it teaches, as well as the quick chat tools. I'd like to see some more focus on self compassion and acceptande. The check-in and active listening could be better and allow more exploration of what feelings, thoughts behaviours are present.

Wow, I love this app. It feels so futuristic, a real case where a smartphone and all are making a positive impact in my life. I love how the daily check in is short and to the point, which along with the streak system has made making it a habit very doable. I've used some of the tools too and they're great. A really well designed, clean, ad-free experience, and Woebot really feels like a friendly person you're messaging. Love it, thank you!

This app is extremely helpful. A little robot, an anonymous person, to tell my worries to. The gratitude journal is super helpful too, I can look back on what's gone well. The lessons it provides are really helpful too. Sometimes, I open the app with just the intention of checking in my mood for the tracker, and i end up spending half an hour doing a lesson! They're always super helpful and make me feel better. HIGHLY recommend!!!

I love this app! Woebot is a friendly encouraging way to examine your thoughts, why you think a certain way and how you can change. You can check in every day for a chat and some advice, you can do gratitude; Woebot tracks your mood too so you can see how/if you progress. Friendly but not intrusive, and you can hit snooze if you're not in a position to chat when you get a reminder. Loads of sections I've not explored yet too - highly recommend it! Free, and probably better than some paid apps!‚ô°

Nice little app to boost your day, your confidence and your spirit. Feels grate to check in daily and get a dose of postive guidance to get you out of any bad mental state and great tips to lift you up. The push up notification keeps you on track to make sure you don't miss any of the good stuff and the mood tracker gives you an image on your evolution. Sad thing,about 6 month later I reached the end of the content üò™ I'll keep using it for practices, but I would love more content ‚ù§

content: I've enjoyed using this app. The exercises Woebot offers everyday don't take more than a few minutes to finish. You can choose when to talk to Woebot, and you can share as little or as much as you like. This app helps me to keep things in perspective, and it helps me to remember the things that my therapist has been helping me with throughout the years. Definitely recommend this app for others to try.

I've followed the program before through Facebook messenger, but I'm doing it again now to brush up on these ideas. Woebot provides a free way to improve your thought patterns, using techniques from CBT (Cognitive Behavioral Therapy). Like everything, it's only as good as the work you put into it, but if you don't have access to paid therapy this is a godsend.

This has been helpful to sustain my mental health during these unprecedented times. I have had a lot of counselling over the years and have a Neuroscience undergrad from many years ago so it can be overly simplistic and lacks some responsiveness to my individual situation, but overall, with some improvements, this could be an integral part of my mental health improvement plan so to speak. I would pay for an enhanced system.

content: Excellent app. I love the way it makes it easy for you to chat: pre-filling conversation options to just tap on , instead of blanks that you have to fill in. Then when the reflection starts, you can use that space to fill in. This app makes CBT very easy to work into daily life. I would like to see more representative and diverse identities in the gifs, memes and examples. I emailed the company to share this and they seem to be taking it seriously.

This conversation-based bot is a great and different approach to managing your mental health. It's good for taking you through different psychological theory in an easy to understand way and challenges you to think about your actions and thoughts in a more constructive manner. Mood check-in is great and trackable, plus the gratitude journal lets you see past entries when you're looking for an extra boost to your mood. The bot doesn't always get it right but a novel approach worth giving a go.

woebot is pretty good. i wouldn't say its working a miracle but i am checking in once or twice a day and at times it switches my focus from the glass half empty to something more positive and productive. i think using the gratitude journal aspect is also really helpful. it is easy to use, i have left off a point as i don't always feel the CBT stuff is clarified as much as it could be.

Repeats the same scripts. I hate that most of my response options are limited to a couple of multi-choice boxes, or only one. So the whole interaction is woebot sending short messages and me clicking a button. I want to TALK. It makes me feel even less human because it stops me from talking. It reduces me to a finger that taps a button that allows woebot to proceed. Even if it doesn't understand, please just let it be the only thing in the world that will let me talk freely!

The AI is not yet capable of having a full blown normal conversation, but it understands well what I say when it has to. There is an incredible amount of helpful content, distilled little by little and tailored to my needs. The daily check-in is very useful for general tracking, and Woebot is absolutely great to get through emergencies and small crisis situations. The conversations are also pretty funny. Great app!

content: First: this is not a substitute for medication or sessions with a trained counsellor. That said, I've been helped by CBT training and therapy sessions before, but had difficulty keeping up the practice afterwards. Woebot covers all of those lessons & tools in a way that's easy to remember and engage with, making their application second nature with time. Some responses could use work, but the devs are fantastic about reading and incorporating feedback. Will keep using for sure.

Thanks to the creators. This is a great app. I've been going through a tough time lately and the (optional) daily interaction with Woebot has helped. The conversations are friendly, positive, sensitive and natural and I've learned a lot from the information it provides. I would recommend using this app in conjunction with some form of human interaction, such as counselling or wellbeing courses.

Great app, I'm not sure if it only feels like that in the early stages or not, but it feels to me there is pretty shallow learning of the terms and recognition of thought patterns and whatever, without actually addressing them specifically or working on changing them. Maybe I'm just not there yet (day 10 or so?), but that what I feel is missing at the moment..

I recommend Woebot to people with anxiety and depression. It's an easy way of learning CBT interventions and feels more than just a self help tool because of how interactive it is. It's like you have a robot friend/therapist. This kind of app will just keep getting better and better, you can't actually have a conversation yet, but this is a great start.

I found the app very comforting and helpful during a stressful period. I'm familiar with CBT but it was still useful to be reminded of those skills. And although you know it's not a real person talking to you, knowing that a real person wrote the text originally is comforting, and shows that someone cares.

Brilliant piece of AI Therapy, offers a great introduction to CBT techniques and helps you to use them in your own way. I'd definitely recommend this to anyone either considering CBT, or to complement their existing therapy/continue with it when their sessions are over. Checking in can be brief and easy, so you can use woebot either to consciously spend some time challenging your thoughts, to calm you down in a state of panic or anxiety, or even just to register a quick bit of positive routine

content: It's like you're having a dear friend in your back pocketüòâ if I could be critical I would say the lessons need to be a little deeper than a one-off conversation and that sometimes the only choice(s) you have a positive response when that might not necessarily be what you're feeling so conversations can feel a little railroaded at times... but having said that you can repeat the lessons and it's free so yeah very good overall

Incredible app, an important and timely program. Always accessible, always ready to help deal with anxiety and clear your head. There are some very minor wording issues and it lacks time zones but it is a wonderful app with humour, passion, care, and love, all given freely to the user. I had initially underestimated the power of this app but it has picked up on and helped me with tough times repeatedly. Thank you greatly to the creators, I may yet learn to live again.

Once great, now seems to be buggy. It repeatedly brings up talking about should-statements even though we've gone throuh it over 5 times. It is unbearable to use it anymore. I have written the developers multiple times addressing this issue, but it remains unaddressed since several weeks. It's very unfortunate, because previously it helped me a lot, and now I have just stopped using it. Please fix this issue and I will immediately retract my review! :)

It's not perfect and probably deserves 4/5, but I'm giving it 5 stars because it is actually 100% free and there are no ads - and I haven't come across anything else that was so honestly FREE. I like the prompts when you're working through automatic thoughts and identifying cognitive distortions and coming up with balance. thoughts. I also like even the daily check-ins with the silly videos. I think it's a really nice app.
replyContent: Hi Amber, thanks for sharing your positive experience with Woebot! We appreciate your feedback and are glad to hear that you find the app helpful. Our team is committed to providing accessible and affordable mental health support to as many people as possible - making Woebot free to use without in-app purchases helps make that a reality.

content: This is a really good tool for learning about CBT in a friendly and relaxed way. I like the daily check ins and being able to monitor my progress. It's important to keep in mind that you're not talking to a human and so it won't respond as a human/counseller would so if you are really struggling you're better off with getting some real help but this might be a good way to get started if you're having a hard time getting to the point of seeking real help.

Seems like a wonderful idea, I had a lot of hope for it. But it never checked in on me, even though all notifications were allowed. And when I initiate, it asks how I'm feeling, when I answer, it crashes and says "check internet connection". Few bugs to work out but otherwise, neat idea.
replyContent: We're sorry to hear that you encountered issues using Woebot.  In order to help us resolve your issue and prevent the issue from happening to others, would you mind writing to us at helpcenter@woebot.io.  This will enable us to ask more detailed questions and make sure we completely understand what is happening.  Thanks so much!

content: Most helpful app for mental health i have ever used. Tried many meditation apps, cbt and calming apps not nearly as useful. Growth mindset has really changed my outlook on life and my own potential. First few sessions were boring but after third session got hooked. Woebot reaches out if you forget to check-in & gives you option to say maybe later if it's a long chat CBT never worked for me with a real person so Woebot deserves a prize Extremely useful to me cant reccomend enough. Thanks guys!

Woebot has been helping me with a couple of new strategies to address thought patterns through CBT. It's been going well so far, although it would be nice to have Woebot act a little bit more human? Sometimes sentences repeat, I don't mind really, but it'd be nice to add some more emotion even. Nevertheless, it's an amazing app and I love using it!

It's a wonderful app that explains in simple words what CBT is and helps to use its techniques. It's really good for practicing these self-help skills. Besides, the bot is sympathetic and funny and it is pleasant to have "someone" who cares about my everyday mood üôÇ. I also reach out to it when having hard time (too anxious, frustrated, depressed) and it helps me get through. I wish it had other languages versions to make such help accessable for more people.

I really like this app. It's a great friend to talk to about anything. But I do have one problem with it, you can't open the app without Woebot starting a conversation. I just wanted to read some past messages and I had go through a whole conversation when there was nothing to talk about. It would be nice if there was a code you could enter to end a conversation immediately or just when Woebot messages you there would be a "not now" option.

A great CBT tool that has helped me feel better on many occasions by braking the cycles of negative thinking / anxiety I was ecperiencing. The only thing that could be improved is that sometimes I'm forced to pick from pre-defined answers, none of which match what I'd like to say. Also, the "how are you feeling today" options - sometimes I need to pick more than one (eg. tired and contented) but that's not possible. Great app over all tho!
replyContent: üëè Thanks for leaving a review, we love your feedback! We'll be sure to share this with our team, thank you very much for sharing it with us. üíï

content: Never reviewed an app before, but this is wonderful. Excellent introductions to varioud cutting edge techniques and has a real feeling of personality to the 'bot' Could do with some sort of index/search or a 'replay' for different conversations, but these are quibbles. I am very impressed with the way this presents some tricky concepts in easy to swallow chunks... and the presentation is cute without being Twee. Basically I love it and would recommend to friends.

It's nice to know you have "someone" around to chat with when you're struggling. Woebot is definitely keeping me own my toes, reminding me about all sorts of destructive thought patterns, and is a great tool with which to record my gratitude journal. The only real issue I have is some lessons have been repeating and there doesn't seem to be an easy way for me to remind Woebot about that. All around, super cool CBT tool that doesn't require more than a couple minutes. Consistency is key with CBT

I like this app so much, it saved my from sadness and stress. Just one thing to comment, I do not agree SMART goal is useful, too specific and goal oriented might makes you oversee the joy during the journey, and create stress. All in all, I think this is a really good app. Thanks for rescuing ppl from collapsing. Your effect means a lot to human beings. One more to add, if there's a Chinese version, simplified and traditional, more ppl can enjoy the app!
