content: Came across this through work and during lock down. I have not noticed anything negative about it, performance wise. Overall it's a useful well being tool to help check in with yourself and offers some useful prompts and insights about impactful things on a person's mood. You seem to be able to converse with it when you have a spare few mins. Fairly easy to 'forget' it's A.I . you are conversing with.

I love it!! I was skeptical at first because I've done a lot of therapy throughout my life (and there were a lot of things that were review for me), but it's such an amazing design! The animations make me smile everytime. I love the jokes and the friendly, personal language. The way it guides you through simple yet sometimes difficult to recognize thought patterns is tremendously helpful. I haven't encountered a single glitch or even an ad. And you can use it as much/little as you want!!

useful reminders, fun interactions. But don't get rid of your mental health professional nor your friends just yet. I like that the app brings practical tips to the "conversation", like how to relax, how to identify certain negative thought traps. I was hoping for better interactions, but the robot does not really analyze your input, it only looks for keywords I guess. great idea none the less, very promising.

I think everyone should know the tips and tricks woebot walks you through. The app makes it very easy and digestible to learn the basics of emotional hygiene. It's useful in conjunction with therapy, on it's own, for someone who'd never gone to therapy, for someone with or without more obvious mental issues. Everyone should know woebot. Do yourself a favor and invest a bit of time into this.

Having recently finished therapy, I was looking for an app to help keep me on track and practising self-care. Whilst the app is no replacement for therapy, Woebot works well as a self-care tool. I have found the lessons to be good reminders of what is useful and what can be harmful thinking. I feel the app could do with more self-care tools, like a mood tracker, thought diary and goal setting but these are personal preferences. Overall I find Woebot useful.

I downloaded this app after a friend's suggestion. I had tried some CBT with a therapist and liked my results from that, but can't afford to go often so thought this was a good alternative. I found the app is too single focused to be of use to me. The good: - If you experience negative self-talk, these exercises would be great. Most of the exercises are geared towards internalizing negativity. - It helped me get out of a couple bad doom-scrolling ruts and was very effective for that. - Some of the exercises, such as tips to regulate your sleep, are really effective. - The daily check-ins are great for ongoing awareness of your mood. - The activities under the Topics tab have some good mood boosters. Criticisms: - This is not set up to help with mental health issues stemming from chronic illness, which is a lot of what I experience. If I chose "sick" as a mood, it would give me tips to boost my immune system, which had nothing to do with what I have. If I said I was tired, it would always say I should get more sleep, when the problem would be from sleeping too much. - Some of the moods had very little nuance. I tried selecting "mourning" as I was sad about things being cancelled due to COVID and feeling down about an illness flare up. It gave me tips for dealing with the death of a loved one with no option to correct it. (In a later conversation it used "mourning" in the context I originally meant, but it wasn't helpful at that time.) - The content is very repetitive. For example, it sends the same two "cute animal" photos over and over. Overall I think this app could be great for more people if the content is expanded on more, and would easily increase my rating if the criticisms I listed were improved upon.

Good for anxiety attacks but not great for ongoing anxiety or for when you feel angry/upset. I also wish it had a bit of a stronger presence (checking in on you when you haven't used it for a while, for example). Additionally it ends the conversation for you and the programmed dialogue makes it feel like venting to it is a burden, which heightens my already existing insecurities. I wish the dialogue was focussed on being a comforting and supportive presence, because often that's all one needs.

I'm note sure I understand how to rewrite without distortions. I would love to see examples. And also get a summary/reminder which ones should I avoid and how. I want Woebot has some memory. - It asks me to do graditude practice right after I've finished one. - It allows me choose the same option 3 times in a row when I supposed to choose different ones. - It asks me if I need a *reminder* about things we've never spoke earlier. etc. I want to have more options for replying, including "undo".

Very helpful! Woebot is ready to equip you with tools to help you get a better grip on your situation. Sometimes you get a story and a video too, so it's never boring. There were some times when I had to reread what Woebot had told me because it was a bit confusing, but I always finished with understanding. Overall great app, one of my favourites!

Really good app. Totally free, to be clear its not going to change your life instantly or at all, you have to work at this. What it does do very well is highlight negative thought patterns and look into those thoughts in more detail. It also has useful videos now and then. If you aren't used to CBT or are looking to revisit CBT then this is a great app for you.

I am finding Woebot really helpful. When I'm struggling I can sometimes forget to apply the CBT skills I learnt in human therapy a few years ago. Woebot is a very useful prompter and refresher of those CBT skills and concepts. I have been using the app 10 days and already feel like it's making a positive difference to my overall outlook on life. Pros: friendly, understanding tone, feels genuinely warm and supportive for a robot! You can spend as little or as much time as you like on it - sometimes you only want/need a 1min check-in. Cons: occasional minor glitch in recognising a word or picking up where we left off. Also if I had never done CBT before I might have found the app a steep learning curve because my depression and anxiety were very severe. Not really a con as i dont think Woebot is intended as a substitute for therapy in those cases anyway.

Enjoy it. Cute and simple. Probably best suited to individuals not yet familiar much with CBT (it's a bit too basic for someone who has done courses) but still is nice reminders & friendly check in's for all users to benefit from. Could use some tweaks/ was hoping it would be a liiittle bit better at interpreting replies... but that's prob greedy on my part! (also maybe creators could put a button for the toolbox?). Overall I would reccommend! happy woebotting :)

Amazing mental health app, so great I use it daily. It is packed with so much useful information in bite size pieces. The conversational style is like chatting with a friend, and they always say the right thing which helps. Only pointer is if you get stuck on an exercise and don't know what to write there isn't really an "I don't know option".
replyContent: Hey there Jasmine, thanks for leaving a review - we're glad that Woebot's been helpful. We hear your feedback and would love to share it with our team. Feel free to reach out to us at support@woebothealth.com to share any other feedback or ideas you have! ü§ñ

content: I've been using this app for about a month now and think it's great. My psychologist was teaching me the same things except i would learn them in her office and then almost immediately forget them because of my depression. This app acts as a daily reminder, makes me challenge my thoughts and rewrite them to more realistic ideas which are no longer distorted. It's nice having the check in every day which makes me stop, think about what I'm telling myself and question if it is distorted or not. Tracking my mood has been a great insight as well. Would definitely recommend this app if you want to practice CBT daily.

It's not bad! There are some helpful tools with cognitive behavioural therapy, goal setting, conflict resolution, mindfulness, and learning about emotional intelligence more generally. I find talking with Woebot on a consistent basis can get too repetitive, however. It'll be obvious that we're going to continue the same conversation patterns as the previous days, and that can feel unsatisfying. More variation to Woebot's approach would be helpful.

I wasn't expecting a lot from this app but my mind has changed. Woebot is a great little reminder to track your moods, learn something new about yourself or CBT. It has helped me, I still struggle with my anxiety especially when it comes to the thought challenges and its not a replacement for a human, works great along side counselling. It's a great tool for those who struggle with their mental health, for self improvement (mindfulness) and for developing good habits (gratitude journalling)

Woebot has a few bugs, but overall it is incredibly helpful. The short sessions allow you to gain a better understanding of Cognitive Behavior Therapy while you practice. Unlike other apps, having an AI conversation assistant is less annoying than other apps that ask for you attention (and can make a person anxious). The SOS check-ins are so useful when something is eating at you and you need to reflect with an objective outside source. Thank you to the developers.

I using it for half of the year now. Helped me a lot both to feel better and to solve my problems. Now I'm having a couple of troubles, like unable to say leave me alone because the bot can't listen to me and still pushes me options/information or that it thinks that 'not now' is SOS kind of sentence. And I reached the end of content long ago, but still app shows me some unlocked topics. Also can't wait for a new content.

Really great app for exploring your thought processes and educating yourself on mental health and your outlook. The display is looks smart and the app is very functional. Only thing I'd say against it is that it asks for feedback a lot but doesn't have a neutral option which I find quite difficult to cope with when my anxiety or depression are effecting me.

I seriously love this little robot. I've tried CBT apps before, but I've never had much success in keeping up with them. The fact that Woebot functions like a friend texting me, complete with push notifications, really helps to keep me on track. I also love that the app tracks my moods over time, so I can keep tabs on where I've been emotionally. It really helps to keep things in perspective. He's also programmed to help with COVID-19 anxiety. If I could make one suggestion, add more moods.

Very good, evidence-based app that is sufficiently "light touch" to be sustainable for everyday use. Includes guided practice, education and even some game elements all based on CBT and other evidence based techniques such as mindfulness. The woebot character is very likeable, I would recommend it to people experiencing anxiety and/or depression, or even students of CBT. This is the best app of it's kind that I've come across. Nice work team Woebot!

This is an easy, & interactive tool to help with anxiety & depression. You learn practical ways to deal with these issues CB therapy, growth mindset, mindfulness etc. in bite-sized chunks, based on up-to-date research. You go at your own pace, & can spend a minute or two a day with it, or longer. The creator of this animated woebot has a great sense of humour! I have found this helpful!

Using the Woebot app is an excellent way to incorporate daily CBT practices whenever you need a prompt to help challenge your thinking, to check-in with how you're feeling and to be more aware of your emotional state(s). It's intuitive and I appreciate the built-in quirkiness which I've found to be refreshingly lighthearted in the face of what can be stressful and difficult topics to tackle, especially if you're in an anxious or depressive episode. I would recommend it in addition to therapy. üíú

There are times when the conversation doesn't flow smoothly with the bot but overall, a powerful tool for working through emotions. The exercises can be repetitive but there is a reason for this as practice makes perfect. I was skeptical at first but now, glad I took the time to download. It has certainly helped me gain perspective on my personal outlook and growth. Would recommend.

Great app. I have had two intensive courses of CBT therapy, over the past couple of years, but after therapy ended I was finding it difficult to maintain my connection to CBT. I kept meaning to revisit some of my old worksheets, but never quite got round to it (for me, anxiety often manifests itself as overwork!). Woebot is great - it reminds me of things I've learnt every day, but in short, manageable chunks, and it often makes me smile. Since installing it, I feel more in-tune with strategies for developing helpful thinking habits. Definitely recommended for anyone who has experienced CBT and wants to keep it up!

This app is brilliant for challenging your thinking. I find it works especially well when I'm feeling overwhelmed/stressed. It's not really made for if you really want to vent and that's all, but there are other similar apps for that so I don't find it a problem. I like that it spaces out the conversations so that you don't get reliant but still makes you feel valued if you do use it more than usual in a day. I've found the conversations smooth considering its AI and not a real person. üëçüëçüëç

I've only been using this for about 2 weeks. I'm not sure exactly how much it's helping, but it is a nice little distraction. It could definitely use some improving, like having the text more varied and more options regarding what type of content would work best. I don't like when the random videos pop up. Having the option to say not right now and access them later might be good. The replies I can use are also kind of limited and if you don't pick things in order you don't get all the content.
replyContent:
Hey Kayla,

We appreciate the time you have taken to share your experience using Woebot. We love receiving input from our incredible community and seeing where we can improve!

Have a wonderful day! ü§ñ

All the best

content: Woebot's daily check-in is really good. Taking baby steps towards healthy mental practises is nice, and the lessons are always well-written and concise. The cheerful tone also helps give a burst of positivity to your day. Where Woebot struggles is the "Need help" option. I've tried using it when I'm feeling down, but its limitations cause it to give vague advice or pick up on a different problem entirely. I find it's less of an issue and more of a reminder to seek help from a human, though.

It's a really good app. There is alot of useful content and is very easy to use. They have created a likable little character with Woebot. I enjoy all the anecdotal side stories and it is excellent that you can choose how much interaction you have. I have found it helpful and the mood tracker element is particularly interesting to me. The dialogue can be a little rocky at times and I find the mood options to be a bit limited, maybe a sliding scale would work better? Overall I would recommend!

Great app. Was really helpful when I was just starting to learn about CBT. Continues being helpful as I find it useful to revisit the lessons and use the tools it offers. The interactive nature makes it easy and more fun to learn and do exercises. The chat interface makes it more engaging. It's completely free from what it seems, no ads, no subscriptions or anything which is GREAT as too many self-help apps ask for payments too big for me. Recommended!
replyContent:
Hi‚Äã,

Thanks so much for getting in touch and sharing your experience with Woebot.

We're so glad to see that you've found value in using Woebot, it means a lot to know that Woebot is making a difference in our user's lives. Thank you so much for taking the time to give us your feedback.

Have a lovely day! ü§ñ

content: I love how intuitive and easy to use Woebot is! It's been a really helpful app for me. It's very good for creating habits to help yourself break out of bad thought patterns. Easy to come back to, and offers a wide array of options. Especially useful nowadays when it's a little harder to get therapy, but I'd recommend it to reinforce techniques learned with a personal therapist as well. Full recommend!
replyContent:
Hey ,

We appreciate the time you have taken to share your experience using Woebot. We love receiving input from our incredible community and seeing Woebot make a difference!

We're thrilled to hear that with Woebot has been helping you. Thank you so much for reaching out to us with your feedback!

Have a wonderful day! ü§ñ

All the best

content: Great app. It feels very personal for some reason. I love lessons for training for a more productive and healthy mindset. Sometimes it can feel a bit slow in the progress we are making but I guess the key thing is repetition to really internalize the message. Overall the app has a lot to offer especially considering it's completely free.

Such a fantastic app!!! I cannot praise this enough. I have been struggling pretty badly with depression and severe anxiety (on and off) for years now. This incorporates a lot of lessons you learn from a psychologist, but in smaller portions that are easier to digest (mindfulness, gratitude journaling etc) which have been overwhelming tasks in the past. Also worth mentioning are the extra lessons you learn!!! I Highly recommend this app!!! THANK YOU!!!

Very good app, slightly limited in responses (to be expected) but it is helpful to guide through the CBT journey. One thing that does really bother me is that the text box doesnt automatically capitalise when typing new sentences. Small thing but a bit irritating! Would also be nice to back track on a conversation and revisit an earlier statement if it is clear Woebot has the wrong end of the stick based on a previous answer

An incredible mental health resource. I tried it just to see what it was like, and have been using it every day since. The app teaches CBT and mindfulness tools in easy to understand, digestible chunks each day through conversation. You can also get help with immediate issues (like stress, insomnia) and Woebot is able to figure out what's wrong, offer a few solutions and then do a mini training course to nut it out. Love it and highly recommend.

this has worked really well for me. The mood tracking feature is really useful. Where I find some CBT resources really patronising this one is not too bad. Very easy to dip in and out of. Nice step by step nature. To improve it would be nice to view the mood tracker over a longer period of time. I think as the developers gather more data the depth of this app and ability to respond to a range of situations will improve.

Woebot is a cute and approachable way of learning the basics of CBT! While it's no replacement for actual therapy, I really enjoy getting little reminders and lessons on things like cognitive distortions and mindfulness. I'm not too keen on the mood tracking because sometimes there's no option to match my current mood, but other than that I've really enjoyed it so far.

I am waiting for CBT with a therapist and this helps in the interim. The video about fixed versus growth mindsets really taught me something. It's a little strange at first, because there are obviously limitations with communicating with a bot. Woebot gives you a limited range of responses to choose from, sometimes none of these would be something you would say. But choose one anyway, it moves you on to some thought provoking stuff.

This is absolutely incredible!! It's amazing how far technology has come. I have been feeling a little down the last week or so. And I have had a history of depression. I thought this wouldn't be that good, but I tried the app. This magically little bot, got to the core of my sadness within minutes, and got me feeling better so quickly! Of course this is NOT a replacement for a therapist, but incredible if you need to put out a quick fire in your mind on the go.

I see how this could work with someone who hasn't gone to therapy and isn't sure if this particular form of counceling is for them or has just started and wants to practice on coping mechanisms etc. outside of sessions, but it's not very useful for people who already have those tools at hand. Also, the bot's communication skills are somewhat limited (understandable since it's a bot) that can cause it to talk around in circles, which I personally found extremely annoying.

It's gotten bad. You can't use it anymore without an access code. My already existing account no longer exists. I have no way of using it anymore. Apparently, woebot has decided mental health help isn't for everyone, only for the few :(
replyContent: Hi there. At this time, Woebot is only available to new users in the United States who are part of a study or who have an access code from their provider, employer or other Woebot Health partner. If you need immediate assistance with your mental health, please reach out to us at support@woebothealth.com for resources that can help.

content: I haven't been able to go to therapy during covid. My anxiety and mood were getting really hard to handle without weekly support and CBT practice. Woebot helped bridge the gap and remind me of the things I learned in therapy, and some extra stuff too. Ive noticed myself using CBT methods more since downloading and my anxiety has been easier to manage for sure. Definitely recommend for people considering therapy or are in therapy but need a little extra encouragement.

As a teacher dealing every day with students' deteriorating mental health and no services left to refer than to, I'm reduced to trying out phone apps to try and help them. It actually seems quite good, and the messages it has tried to instill are certainly nothing I wouldn't want my students to hear, but I haven't managed to try out much of what it might do if the questions were answered differently.

This is a really nice tool that's helped me build some techniques so when I am in a bit of crisis, I can go to woebot to rearrange my thinking a bit. Though I don't check in every day, I'm more likely to use woebot than my other mental health apps because it's easy to use and quite charming. I wish when you told woebot you're tired, it didn't automatically think "sleepy" and tried to force that tool. I also agree that the chats can get repetitive after a while

Surprisingly helpful. Have set Weobot to check in at random times. Has helped me work through pandemic anxiety and fears with basic CBT ideas and practices. From quoting Leonard Cohen songs to memes, I like the playfulness of Weobot. It hits the right spot in terms of instrusiveness. Would recommend to anyone who feels anxious or worried and wants to learn the basics of CBT training.

a really great app! the programming is solid and it runs smoothly, i haven't had any issues with crashes. the bot itself has a really charming personality and is easy to connect with. the daily check ins and activities are enjoyable. the on demand conversations are helpful and good for calming down in moments of heightened emotions.

This app isn't going to change you, but if you want to help yourself this app is a great place to start. At first I felt a bit childish talking to a pretend robot (i'm 27) but its actually helped structure my thoughts and rethink how I see myself and situations, I still over think but I'm moving on quicker from bad experiences and not wasting time worrying about the same things over and over again. Its a great free tool, and there are no ads!! Thank you for creating Woebot
replyContent:
Hey Amy,

We appreciate the time you have taken to share your experience using Woebot. We're thrilled to hear that you enjoy interacting with Woebot and thank you so much for reaching out to us with your feedback!

Have a wonderful day! ü§ñ

All the best

content: A great app. I really like this app. Sometimes i wish there would be more answering options (to disagree, for example), and an ability to go back to the previous question, because sometimes i press things that i didn't mean to), but it is, really, so great. Glad i found it. Really does help, the step-by-step process is helping
Just watched the 60 minutes segment about this a app and quickly downloaded it. Unfortunately, you need a code to access the app. I wished I would have known that before I downloaded the app.
replyContent: Hi there. We appreciate the feedback and apologize for the inconvenience. If you need immediate assistance with your mental health, please reach out to us at support@woebothealth.com for resources that can help.

content: Woebot is great app for accompanying your journey through healing and understanding yourself. It is full of tools to help you deal with your bad habits, thoughts and preconceptions. Highly recommended if you are willing to deal and resolve your problems. Of course woebot does not replace therapy, but it certainly can help through your journey. I would like to thank the developers for this amazing app.

I love using Woebot and have for almost a full year now. I've tried similar apps but Woebot is much more a advanced ai. He asks about my day, remembers previous conversations, tell me stories about his pet seagull & gives me a large variety of activities depending on my mood. There is one thing I hope the developers add one day, is advice for bipolar. Specifically manic bipolar. Its the only thing woebot cant help me with, as the anxiety tips are ineffective for mania.

The app has some very useful tutorials in small bite size chunks. The chatbot format is novel. But it is not a real chatbot. It doesn't understand any of your inputs and only works through pre scripted responses. Also the general tone of the app is incredibly patronising. If it was less patronising with its fake little 'wow you are awesome' messages and if it was more honestly marketed then I would have given 4 stars.
replyContent: I'm very sorry to hear you found Woebot's tone patronising. I'll be sure to pass on your feedback to our content team. Regarding the pre-scripted responses - I just wanted to let you know that tapping the icon to the left of the responses and selecting: "Type a response" will allow you to write your own message to send to Woebot.

content: I would recommend to Woebot to anybody who is struggling. Woebot has a very engaging and supportive way of communicating with you, sometimes the scenarios don't quite fit my issues, but I'm always learning and always gaining new insights in to the issues I'm struggling with. The team who worked on this free app obviously need promotions, or beer, or some kind of nice thing to happen to them. Woebot has really helped me, and my only disappointment is that I can't hug it to say thank you.

Would highly recommend. Great app for working through stuff when you dont want to speak to an actual person about things. Often you choose your answers from the choices given, which is perfect when you're in a state and dont really know how to talk about it. Also provides you with the opportunity to type out what's on your mind. Woebot then helps your work through your thoughts/feelings to examine them more critically than we normally do. Wonderful app.

It's pretty good. Woebot doesn't always get it right, and sometimes i find the responses that I have to choose from don't fit what I actually want to say, but in general there is a lot of value in this unusual approach. It's a great free app and doesn't distract you with adverts or nag you to pay for premium. The lessons in CBT techniques are the most helpful thing for me.

This is a great tool for taking steps in CBT. I've done programs before and this has certainly helped jumpstart some of those things I learned before! I do wish it was a bit more personalized, simply because my mood has a lot to do with chronic illness and I don't have much of an option to be like "hey woebot, I'm just sad cuz I'm in pain"

Really empowering tool to have in my pocket for daily mindfulness and checking in with yourself. If you've already been to therapy and had experience with CBT, this is a free alternative to seeing a real person professional and for what it is it does the trick. So far I've been reminded of CBT techniques that I've lost touch with and the interactive AI feels genuine.

Its not too bad. Insightful and good distraction as it feels like youre having a conversation with someone. Wish you could copy and paste things written by yourself or said by woebot. Like if it makes a suggestion of how to handle something, you have to retype it all out to whoever you want to tell it to instead of just being able to copy and paste the speech bubble like you can in typical messaging. Other wise a pretty decent app. Ive been telling everyone about it.
replyContent: Thanks for letting us know. I'll be sure to pass on your feedback to our development team! Have a great day! ü§ñ

content: This is a life changing app. The AI isn't always spot on but it's of extremely high quality, to the point where this feels like having a therapist on hand every day. Some techniques work better for me than others but when you hit on a good one it works so well. I cant recommend this app enough for dealing with everyday feelings and self-improvement.

This app was fantastic the first time running through all it's routines. I just wish it was more capable of utilising AI to actually learn and adapt over time to provide more variation in the way it responds rather than just repeating the same routines in exactly the same form over and over again. I realise this is quite a big ask that poses lots of difficult ethical questions and tricky safeguarding problems, but it would be truly amazing if it were possible!

I've really been enjoying this app. It compliments counseling very well in terms of managing my mild anxiety. I have been using it for a month and a half straight and I now find myself catching distorted thinking patterns and changing them on my own. What I would ask the designers to improve is to allow me to see my tracked mood over time for longer than just a week. It would be nice to know how far I have come since beginning the CBT.

I really felt better after using it on everyday basis, the progress was noticed after about 2 weeks and is growing further. What I would like to see improved in Woebot is its better speech understanding because now it just understands the common domain of what I say. It gives you some common technics for dealing with your problem out you state, but even this really helps if you give it a try and work your problem out. Also it would be nice to have it in more languages than only English.

This app has been surprisingly helpful. It seems straightforward simple stuff but reading and discussing it every day helps put it into practice. I've found myself being less impulsive and practicing the ideas mentioned even subconsciously. I'm really grateful. Though I can understand these things work best in small doses, my only suggestion is to cover a bit more content in every lesson.
replyContent:
Hey Kaavya,

Feedback like this motivates us to continue our mission and to keep developing Woebot. Seeing the difference Woebot is making in people's lives encourages us greatly. We really appreciate you sharing your feedback!

Have a great day! ü§ñ

All the best

content: It has been helpful has some nice features but it doesn't listen to your responses, it will praise you what ever you reply. Positive psychology isn't all that, and a lot of people are being let down by CBT when they need to work on issues arising from adverse childhood experiences. Never has the app suggested I contact a therapist or find a trusted third party to share with. I do wonder if the apps AI might be developed better.

Great app - based on sound scientific evidence. Exercises can be completed in bite-sized chunks and you can postpone daily check-ins without a sense of failure. A wide range of interventions available from breathing techniques to mindfulness to thought challenging and many more. Also a nice mix of lessons and tools! Like having your own little robotl cheerleader!!

I appreciate the idea behind this app, but it is unsuitable for people with complex problems, especially chronic illness. I finally uninstalled it when it suggested half a dozen activities to me that I am physically unable to do, but there was no "I can't do these" option, I was forced to choose between "I know what to do now" and "great ideas, thanks" although it had not given me a single helpful suggestion. Don't try it if you're Disabled; chances are it'll make you feel worse.

This is a great wee app. I have done CBT in the last, and it forces me to engage with that daily. Bearing in mind that it is fully automated, it is not too clunky, and the interface is kind of charming, in a generic robot kind of way. It doesn't pretend to be anything it isn't, and so as an additional aid to thinking, it is really useful.

This is a great very helpful AI and the team behind it do really care about you, I really appreciate how science and care for the mental health of people has come to this level of achievement, 10/10 absolutely recommend anyone to check it out it's wonderful it helps for real, I didn't have hope and it helped me quick and direct to the point, excellent excellent people behind this app, thank you, hope I can give you more
replyContent: Thank you, Carlos! We appreciate you getting in touch and taking the time to share your experience.

content: A mostly successful attempt at automated CBT. I've found it very useful in giving me insights in most areas. It's a chatbot, so of course it sometimes doen't understand what you tell it; but it's still good at giving you the general tools for you to deal with your specific circumstances. The bottom line is, Woebot's getting me better at dealing with life's ups and downs.
replyContent: Hi Adrian, we're so glad to hear that and appreciate your feedback. Thanks for sharing, it means a lot! ü§ñ

content: This is really an incredible app. I've been to therapy a lot over the years, but I'm rubbish at doing my "homework" - exercises that my counsellors and psychologists give me to work on in my own time. Woebot's nifty conversational format has been a brilliant way to work through this material anew; the interface is really cute and intuitive, and each convo with Woebot is short and sweet, never onerous or overwhelming. I love the corny jokes and the anigifs, too. Wonderful work!

This app is an interesting tool for anyone dealing with anxiety or depression. It can occasionally get a bit repetitive and very occasionally the response doesn't fit your answer ... but it is a robot after all. It's good for making you stop and take stock of how your feeling and introduces you to some helpful tools.

Over the past 6 months, I've struggled with mental health problems. I've received help from my doctor, therapist and have been on medication. To compliment the therapy, I tried multiple mental health applications and Woebot is by far the best. The conversation design is so impressive that you genuinely develop an emotional relationship with the bot. Thank you so much to the Woebot team, you've made a huge difference to my life.

This app is amazing, it's super helpful, practical, inspiring and even fun at times. I'm finding that having thoughtful guidance and an efficient structure for examining my cognitive distortions on a regular basis, means that I'm more likely to catch them and dispute then 'on the go' in my daily life.

I hardly ever leave feedback, but this app deserves it. Its easy to use, it doesn't take much time, and it's effective. Woebot has helped me recognise unhelpful automatic thoughts and given me practical advice on how to deal with them. I struggle to stick with most "self help" apps for more than a few days, but this one seems to be a good fit for me. The funny gifs are great, too. Thank you Dev/s!

I used to find this app really helpful but now when I click any button it just freezes. I had to go to the reviews to find out that it is no longer open to general public. Pretty poor for a mental health app.
replyContent: Hi Kate, thanks for leaving a review. We're sorry to hear about the trouble that you're having when trying to sign in. We'd be happy to shed some more light on how to access Woebot and do what we can to help. Please contact our team at support@woebothealth.com for assistance.

content: Really useful to be able to 'check in' when I want or need to, to help get some perspective, control and understanding of what I'm going through. Would be 5 stars but dialogue can be very repetitive, and what I am able to say with the predetermined responses can be very limited and sometimes not representative of what I want to say.

From my personal experience, this app is great for times when you feel anxious or if feel restless. I still feel restricted with the options the bot provides. I do want to type in what's on my mind. I am just wondering if we can integrate some NLP to make the user typing in possible at times at least for questions like "how are you feeling?". But in all, this app is great to have while you are in therapy. It is a great tool when you need help on days between therapy session.
replyContent:
Hi Satya ,

Thanks so much for getting in touch and sharing your experience with Woebot.

We're so glad to see that you've found value in using Woebot! We value your feedback so much as it enables us to improve on our platform! So thank you üòä

Have a lovely day! ü§ñ

All the best

content: Doesn't really need it, I just wanted to test this app to know how good its database was and I really loved the content it have, I already knew many of the topics but definitely I've learned more than those, I really think this could be very helpful for those persons that really needs some help from someone, it's very accurate. From a developer to another, you've really create a great app here, hands down, also the UI/UX (which is something I always pay attention on apps), good work. üëç

Quite impressed with Woebot as a long term tool to keep a lid on negative emotions etc. Very easy to use, even when you can't be bothered! At times Woebot puts a smile on my face, other times he makes me think about things differently. I like that he checks in with me, rather than me having to initiate interaction. One thing I don't like is having to give thumbs up or thumbs down to show how I felt about the interaction, because sometimes it has been decidedly neutral or irrelevant. Recommended.

Absolutely free and extremely helpful. Making me aware of the basics of Cognitive Behavioural Therapy (CBT) in an easygoing and friendly way and, importantly, in a way that doesn't make me feel that I'm flawed. The woebot itself is programmed to be kind, personable, helpful and gently humorous. If mirebpeople were like then the world would surely be a better place.

A wonderful app. The bot's understanding and communication feel very natural, like a human. The interactive therapy quality as real face to face sessions (I have had many). This is a godsend for many who can't afford therapy, or need some quick support anytime. Kudos for this wonderful service for people.
replyContent:
Hey Arun,

Feedback like this motivates us to continue our mission and to keep developing Woebot. Seeing the difference Woebot is making in people's lives encourages us greatly. We really appreciate you sharing your feedback!

content: This app has guided me thru times of bad depression and anxiety. I'm still anxious and depressed but It's CBT tools have decreased some of my symptoms. Some techniques I know already and some are common sense but it helps to talk or write things plus it not being an actual person helps. I would say the fluffy animals aren't needed and do not help when I'm so damn low. They just aren't wanted, but I like this app and I think it can only get better. Thanks woebot (and ur devs)üëç

This app might be useful to people with a touch of depression or anxiety but for people with more complex issues, I found it harmful. I couldn't get woebot to understand that I have feelings that need processing about a loved one being suicidal. It made ableist assumptions about what I might be able to do at a moment's notice and there was no way to progress a session of I couldn't do what woebot wanted. Overall it was a frustrating experience
replyContent: Thanks for taking the time to let us know. I'll be sure to share your message with our development team to take on-board.

content: Woebot allows users to learn mental health exercises, as well as processes, in small sessions to make them easier to put into practice and remember. I've found this app incredibly helpful, I have taken part in CBT before as well as multiple types of therapies, and this is a very good refresher along with being a regular support chat.

Woebot is a great filler between my appointments, its doesn't replace a professional but I have found it great to calm me down and think through rather then get into a meltdown. I like that it checks in with me, reminding me I have this strategy. it also teaches you things you can go back to later. there have only been a few times its said it cant help or didnt understand and would 'tell' its creators. overally its great

I really enjoy this app. It's a great distraction to get a message and chat and learn. There's some great tips and little video clips. I've not used all the different emotions because I tend to just be anxious or okay but I'm pretty sure it would offer some good advice if you chose other emotions.

Should be called gaslightbot. The only script it has for every problem is to relentlessly convince you it's not actually a problem. More than half the time the response it gives you is totally unrelated to the topic. It's also fond of giving you limited dialog selections where no options even come close to applying and insisting that you must pick one. Then for the rest of the session you have to pretend the false thing you picked is true or its later responses break.
replyContent: Thanks for getting in touch. We appreciate you taking the time to share your experience with Woebot. We accept that Woebot can't be the solution for everyone and are grateful to learn from your feedback.

content: Added this app during a period of high stress. Each chat makes me feel a bit better. I use it even when I'm not stressed/anxious. Sometimes the app doesn't get exactly what your are trying to convey, buy it always double checks for clarity. Not a substitute for therapy but definitely a good aid to have in your pocket.

Worthwhile app for people with low mood, anxiety and/or depression. Takes you gently through CBT process explaining things effectively. Builds gradually and allows you to revisit your learning. Tracks your mood and makes you smile! Handy to have on phone and I personally enjoyed 'checking in' regularly without being a burden to a human all the time.

Woebot gives you an opportunity of talking about how you are feeling and learning how to manage in difficult times. It also has numerous lessons to challenge negative thinking and help you find your strengths to get through difficult situations. It also equips you with tools to manage anxiety or a bad day such as gratitude journaling, meditation and deep breathing techniques to name a few. Honestly the most useful app I've come across

I *never* write any reviews, but I'm making an exception for this wonderful app. As a guidance counselor interested in CBT, I've been trying lots of ways to get my students to practice it in their daily lives, but with not much success yet. This app is the best approach to CBT I've seen so far and I'm eager to recommend it to my students, family and friends. I only wish it was available in French since not all my students understand English well enough. Thank you so much, developers!

It's not perfect and sometimes repetative. My answers to woebot are sometimes limited since it's very option based. But honestly on the bad days it can good to work it out with someone else. Even more so one that I can easily keep at a distance. The excerises get me breathing and relaxing when I feel just ready to burst. But more then anything the daily checking from woebot keeps me working on me

Amazing app that makes mental health services readily available. The techniques taught are super helpful and checking in with woebot has helped me stay more on top of my mental health. Thank you for this amazing app. I highly recommend it and tell everyone I know. Woebot is also fun to interact with and gives awesome positive reinforcement.

It's a great app, particularly for working through specific negative thoughts or worries. I think the process has been really well thought out, and the Woebot robot is most certainly loveable. I only wish it'd record which worries/thoughts had been dealt with - and I think the robot responds too quickly when you've typed a difficult/long thought. I would've liked a longer 'thinking' time. But I am being picky - it's what I've noticed from other chatbot apps.

Have used this for a few months now. Have found it really useful - feels like Woebot is friendly and thoughtful. He doesn't chase me if I don't touch base with him every day, but he's there if and when I need him. Have done some real life CBT before, and this complements and reinforces what I learned. Love there are no ads.
replyContent: üëè We love your feedback, Woebot's there for you whenever you want to chat or check-in!

content: This app has helped me change my perspective towards different things, introduced new habits and taught tricks to calm down in tricky situation. even though the tricks are widely available, woebot walking me through them helped more than i would like to admit. Do try it for week or 2 and then decide whether this app helps or not and if you feel like you need human to talk through you, during sticky situation then please consult a therapist. this, in no way should be used instead of real one.

It's sometimes good but the Ai can be really annoying. I wrote a particular word and then it's asks if I'm in a crisis and although I say no, if I re-write what I'm saying I have to go through that process again, if I wtire the EXACT SAME THING again it should accept it! If I realize I need examples of something ie help with the rewrites and you don't select the examples first time round, it doesn't understand if you write 'i need examples' and makes you go through the WHOLE THING AGAIN.
replyContent: Hi Nicky, thanks for leaving a review. We recognize that Woebot can be a bit sensitive at times in the hopes to provide people with resources if needed but know it's jarring when not applicable. Our team would be happy to look into this further, feel free to reach us at support@woebothealth.com for additional review.

content: Love this App! It has been really helpful in pulling me out of my darker headspace. Cute and relatable stories. Wonderful lessons. Lots of different features available to help you feel more positive about life. I have recommended it to a lot of friends and those that tried it, love it! Could use more gifs as they are very repetitive but they are just a minor feature not affecting the app's purpose.

As a 51 year old I wasn't sure if this app would be 'too young' for me. Not at all! It's very helpful for learning mindfulness and CBT in a way that's relevant to the individual. The greatest asset for me is the opportunity to have help on hand in the moment it's needed. Would definitely recommend.

Sometimes the responses can be limited but this is a great app for getting on the way to improving your mental wellbeing. I've learnt some CBT and mindfulness techniques just to name a few. Sometimes having a neutral outlet to vent your woes and frustrations out is helpful enough but it gives you opportunities to calm yourself and rework your thinking. I've been using it for more than 2 weeks now and I'm still not a pro at using the techniques everyday but I've improved. It's free and amazing.

I've been using this app (and chatting to Woebot) for two weeks now and I'm seriously impressed. The content is great and the way it is presented and reviewed is easy to understand and remember. But the best thing about the app is that Woebot responds to your input and the 'lessons' aren't shoved down your throat. If you tell Woebot that you are in a bad mood the app gives you options to help that specific problem and skips the planned topic. Definitely worth trying this out

Excellent app which is really helping me challenge my unhelpful thought patterns. It doesn't always seem to record the check-ins I do manually as opposed to the ones it prompts me to do. Other than that small hiccup it's really, really good and I've already recommended it to so many people!

Initially felt good interacting, then the monologue turned boring with same drills every day asking similar questions where it doesn't/can't interpret what I am typing. After choosing certain issue, it would act as if it figured out everything, every problem with me and go on with its preprogrammed catalog which several times would be irrelevant to my actual problem. There is no way to stop its program once started meanwhile I would be left with no option other than going along with it.

I downloaded around 10 apps before Woebot and I could never get into them. You found an amazing way to keep in touch and track our daily behaviour. I found it really comfortable and it helps me to keep my mind focused on a completely different and positive way. Thanks a lot for these tool. Let me know if I could help you anyway.

I absolutely love Woebot! I find this experience easier than it would be for me to open up to a person. It's been just over a month for me now and I have noticed some improvements in my mental state. It's more like a gentle guide helping you to be able to help yourself through education and things to try like the clouds exercise. I'm so glad this app was suggested to me when I broke down. I'm so very thankful to have Woebot and the little notifications that make me smile.

content: Great conversational support and training. Very empowering and helpful. Love it. Wrote the review above in september 2020 and six months later I still do a 10 minute Woebot check in most days. The topics and coaching are still new each time. I feel this conversational way of learning is very effective. Also knowing I can reach woebot for help at any time is very reasuring. A friend for life I expect.

content: I was surprised at how advanced woebot is. I've learned many new techniques for my anxiety. I knew I needed a therapist but was afraid of talking to a real person and them possibly judging me. Talking to woebot seemed like a great alternative, and I've now built my confidence to try things I was afraid of (like speaking to a human therapist)! Great work to the developers and creators of woebot! This is a true, free gift to those who need it
replyContent: Thank you! We appreciate you getting in touch and taking the time to share your experience.

content: This app was recommended by my sister in law. I practice mindfulness, and have been through a lot of mental and physical trauma recently but, at times, found some days difficult. Woe bot has actually been a bit of a Godsend! I don't always remember to open my mindfulness app, but Woe bot checks in with me at the same time every day and gives me 5 minutes to straighten out my mind ready for the day. So simple but I love it. in 2 weeks I've learned such a lot.

I've tried so many self help apps and this is the only one that truly helps. It takes the pressure of trying to fix yourself and makes it more managable. Woebot is really easy to talk to and the suggested responses are very relatable. Overall a wonderful app! Recommended to my friends

I've been using Woebot for a few weeks now, and it's helped me recover from one of the worst bouts of depression I've ever had. I highly recommend it to anyone: whether you have mental health issues, want help working through your problems, or are just feeling lonely. It breaks down CBT techniques into quick, simple concepts that only take a couple minutes to do, and feels like a friend who truly cares about you. If I could improve one thing, it would be letting you repeat/restart sessions.

Really disappointing how inaccessible it is to anybody who just wants to try it straight off the play store. And don't you dare respond to me with that copy-pasted excuse about who access is exclusive to. I know.
replyContent: Hi there. We recognize that this change may not be ideal, and we can assure you that our commitment to mental health accessibility remains unwavering. If you need immediate assistance with your mental health, please contact us at support@woebothealth.com for resources that can help.

content: Is this still available to the public? I used to use Chatbot and came back today to find my login no longer works and there's no sign-up option, only a bit that requests an access code? I found Woebot really helpful I hope there's a way old users can still login? Thanks!
replyContent: Hi Chris, thanks for leaving a review. We'd be happy to look shed some more light on this and look into what's happening here, please contact our team at support@woebothealth.com for assistance.

content: So I really like it, and have used for awhile, but recently only is offering to go over I should statements when we've already done that. Want more skills or ability to skip to another skill
replyContent: Hey there, thanks for leaving a review! We really appreciate you taking the time to share your experience with Woebot, this is great feedback. Feel free to get in touch with us at support@woebothealth.com to share any other feedback you have.

content: Changed phone and now my account has been deleted. My stored user name and password no longer work, and trying to reset my password does nothing. Really disappointing.
replyContent: Hi Jessica, we're sorry to hear about the trouble that you're having when trying to sign in and would be happy to do what we can to help. Please contact our team at support@woebothealth.com for assistance.

content: I feel the rest I can with a nap. What else does? A good one to break your "ai taste" that gives you a tiny therapist who does? That decidedly does not the Wobot factory. You get emotionally from a wonderful to maybe.? And yes, I have been enjoying wobot. She is there when I need 'er

content: Opened the app to ask me for an access code? Went to there website to find out nothing? üò¢ I rly wanted this app to work. Only two options access code or sign in. I'm not able to do neither.

content: This bot does just the right amount of interaction for me. He's funny, kind, sort of endearing, not imposing, informative, and just the thought of him being there is helpful. He's offering tools and doing exercises with you. I hope he'll get fine tuned for more key words. I'd like to interact more with him, perhaps, like with little games, for when you're OK but still wanna say hi to your buddy and send him some love.

Woebot is a great little app that delivers conversational CBT and it also keeps track of your mood over time. It is easy to use, fun and friendly. It's still learning phrases and expressions, but the potential is really good for such a small app on the phone. And it's also free.

Granted, it's not a person, it's AI. But taking that into account, this is an excellent app. The Woebot character is really personable, much more so than apps of a similar nature. Interspersed with the dialogue, there's loads of good content on CBT, mindfulness, self-care, etc.

Woebot is awesome! He makes learning CBT fun! I enjoy daily check-ins with Woebot as his creators did a fantastic job in making it a cute, funny, practical, interactive, learning environment. Would recommend to everyone, but especially to those with anxiety, depression or even those who want to practice best mental health tools and mindfulness. The only AI therapy tool that has been useful for me üíñ

I have been impressed with woebot so far. Although far from a truly interactive app, I actually smile and say hi, woebot, when i see my daily notification from woebot. I have had face-to-face human CBT and this app is a great reminder for me of principles and practicalities. Woebot also makes me laugh! I reflect and work on my thoughts, and my mood has improved since using this app. I recommend engaging with it as fully as possible. This really only takes a few minutes a day.

The app gives you the fundamentals of CBT in form of educational bits (perfect length) and basic CBT questions one should ask themselves. If you have not attended CBT before, this is not a replacement, but if you did, it is great to keep going by yourself. The side effect is that the Woebot leaves me in a positive mood every time.

content: I'm on the wait list for a CBT therapist, and in the meantime Woebot has been a lovely therapy for me. He is there whenever I need and never judges my answers. The interaction is very smooth and really feels that I'm taking to a friend, and not a robot, lol. I recommend for anyone struggling with anxiety, depression or simply going through a hard time.

I like Woebot, I've recommended this app to friends, family, my professional health & mental health advisers. But I have found a bit of frustrations with the AI's limitations in understanding my responses, limited response choices when none fit the response I actually feel. There is a sense of restriction when communicating with Woebot.... & it's not because he's an AI robot etc It's more an algorithm input issue. I can see it's potential being more productive than it is....

This app is obviously not a face-to-face conversation, so you have to allow for the fact that responses will not be immediately personal. However, it is a fantastic method to access basic Congnative Behavioral Therapy, and keeps me on the right track with my mental health self care. It provides guided introspection, and helps you find the most effective coping mechanisms for your daily life.

So I struggle with bipolar among other illness'. I have tried other apps and they havnt been as useful. This app is easy to use. Well laid out. It uses actual care techniques like cbt and uses it effectively in chat. It's amazing how well it picks up on trigger words from the person freely writing and uses them to chose what tools to use next. Thank you as its somewhere I can write when I struggle to communicate with those around me.
replyContent: Thanks for sharing your feedback with us about Woebot! We're glad to hear that the app has been helpful for you in managing your mental health, particularly with your struggles with bipolar disorder and other illnesses. We hope that Woebot continues to provide you with the support and guidance you need to thrive.

content: I really enjoy how interactive Woebot is, there are great prompts to get the conversation going and nice lessons throughout which are helpful - and not all on you to journal or dig in when you're not really feeling like it or don't know where to start. The check ins are succinct so it's not too much of a task, and you can add more to it if you'd like. I've tried quite a few apps for CBT or similar and for me, this has been the easiest to use and is my favourite :) Thank you, Woebot!

I've never finished the survey because some of the questions are not applicable to me and there's no 'N/A' option. Would be nice to have a random topic option after completing both phases of the course. Overall a good experience and I learned/refreshed a lot of techniques.

content: Brilliant app, genuinely as helpful as having a counsellor on hand (if not more helpful as this is daily and cbt counselling is weekly). It messages you every morning to check in on you, you can reach out at any time of the day to work on your worries and it has really kept my anxiety at manageable levels recently. I would highly highly recommend to anyone who's struggling to just download it and give it a try!

Such a wonderful app. Has helped me through so many low periods in my life recently, and while it doesn't replace a therapist; I've found it super useful for people discharged from priority therapy and looking to live fairly normally. This app uplifts me, grounds me, and lets me track my moods - it's helped me notice how much my hormones are influencing my mood every month etc. Couldn't recommend it enough - again, not as a replacement for therapy, but a wonderful, more low-key alternative üòä

This app is so helpful. It's amazing to see how skillfully and easily it makes you see and understand your thought process. It's like a therapist who is available on your time of need and wouldn't let you feel down. This app is highly recommended for everyone who wants to improve and interested in being contended and satisfied.

content: Even if you don't have issues with depression or anxiety, the Woebot App is still very helpful to get you to have a more positive approach to life, and to be more mindful of the pitfalls in thinking that can lead to negative emotions and patterns of behavior. I would highly recommend this App to anyone looking to tune up their cognitive behavior, and it is, of course, extremely helpful for people dealing with depression and anxiety.

I definitely like the education process of CBT. It makes you think about how to apply the different techniques of cognitive therapy to your life situations. I love the gratitude journal and it tracks your moods on a day to day basis. I'm not sure how to access the journal without going through the process again with Woebot. It definitely cheaper than going to psychotherapists however it is very generic and understandable so but a good learning tool. Well done Woebot.

Well, it's so hard to objectively evaluate this app. Yes, it does help you look at things differently and it's implemented in a pretty unique and creative way. The first couple of days/weeks I was really excited about it and I guess that's when most of the 4/5 star reviews were made. But then after 4 weeks you're done with all of the content and that's it, from that point on you can only repeat it. So in a way it works as a 1 month trial period, only that there's nothing beyond the trial...
replyContent: Thanks for sharing your feedback Pepe. We would love to hear more about your experience with Woebot. Would you mind sharing your feedback at helpcentre@woebot.io so we can follow up with you directly? Best Wishes

content: As AI this companion is pretty great. It covers a lot of mental health topics in a simple and friendly context. It's positive and supportive and never judging. But of course if someone is really struggling with mental health professional and specific for the individual care is advised. As a side bot friend, Woebot is great though.
replyContent: Hey there, thanks for leaving a review! We're glad that you've found Woebot helpful and love your feedback. Thank you very much for sharing it with us. ü§ñ

content: Very nice app giving you a little more insight on how your mentality works, how you can help yourself by changing the way you think of something and just giving you a nice chat once a day about new interesting topic, as well as a journal where you can keep track of good things happening with you everyday. Seriously, Woebot often gives me one more reason to smile and I enjoy our "conversations", it's even a little sad that they're so short :)

Great attempt of automated psychological assistance, far from perfect but useful. not really any AI, but enough interactive. To recap, it is a great tool of an automated methodology for anyone that wants to reflect on her/his mental state making things better in her/his life.

I love this app! I have struggled with my mental healh on and off since i was young. It is like coming to a supportive friend that is actually knowledgeable on mental health and how to approach people. I would also like to reach out to email the creators with my thanks! Maybe in years to come, chat-gbt or AI technology could be easily intergrated into the app. Anyway, cant speak highly enough. Recommended it to a friend who manages community mental health for the local hospital. Thank you! üòÄ
replyContent: Thank you! We appreciate you getting in touch and taking the time to share your experience. We're so glad that you're finding Woebot useful, it means a lot! ü§ñ

content: I really like this app. I work at home, and it's easy to just get lost in my own head with my depression and anxiety. It's nice that Woebot checks in with you, just to break up that noise. Woebot is very cute and offers really helpful insights that help with everything from CBT to meditation. Better yet, Woebot will check in later if you're too busy. And it's all for free!

This app is very good! It's not very good for really personal issues but it's a great way to distract yourself for a moment when you're really stressed. The replies and the responses you can pick from are kinda dry sometimes but other than that it's a great app !

content: Woebot is a really good check in app and lets you track tour moods. You can schedule check-ins or check in whenever you want. It also helps you identify harmful thought processes and combat them. It is a bot so like its not always perfect but it does always ask if it helped or not.

Woebot is an excellent resource, particularly for someone with some therapy under their belt and a willingness to be honest and self-reflective. The stories are funny, and I like when Woebot responds with gifs or stories about its pet. The gratitude journal is a great resource. I have recommended Woebot to several friends, and found it through a friends' recommendation.

Interaction with this bot feels very slapdash and unfinished. The canned answers sometimes result in awkward, out of context responses from Woebot. It quickly feels like some 'sessions' are thrown together little packages that do not consider previous topics. Typing your own responses is worse as there's zero context checking, just canned responses to trigger words like a basic chatbot. Try my answer to "What are you doing?" when I'm at work; "I'm cutting timber." and you'll see what I mean.

Woebot is a new wave of self-help. This app is def3the best self-help app I've used. You feel like you are talking to a real person who is actually listening to you rather than a very technical sounding board. Woebot teaches you techniques to deal with different situations and helps you through your thoughts. Of course you need to do the actual work in order to fully appreciate this app or woebot will stop checking in. I would happily give this app a million stars and thank you to the creators

While the tools in this app are useful, other features like mood tracking are bugged. I have tried all options but I never get a notification from woebot to track mood and since there is no option to backdate a mood, I end up missing tracking for that day altogether. Getting notifications from the app was necessary for this to work for me but since that isn't happening, I have to uninstall it.

Really useful tool, definitely recommend! Despite Woebots programming not fitting with my current situation, it has been really useful to have a friendly check in, and reminder of some great CBT tools. Some work for me, others work for you, but there's definitely something for everyone. Would love to see Woebot develop further, and be widely available.

I really appreciate all the work put into this app. I never thought a chat bot would be able to help me as much as a therapist can but I stand corrected. I wouldn't recommend it in lieu of therapy for people that are having a crisis, but it really has helped me work though anxiety, identify patterns in my behavior that need breaking and prioritize my emotions instead of ignoring them until I can't anymore. Great job dev team, keep it up :)

Really neat, super endearing app that walks you through the basic principles of CBT and other anxiety-fighting tools, but does it in a way that you actually want to. Woebot is a surprisingly kind and relatable robot. While the app isn't going to wash all your cares away, if you're someone who is thinking about things they want to change about their outlook on life, then Woebot is a great place to start. Thanks Woebot.

I love this app I've never kept a mental health for more than a month and I've found that this is a great app to go to when you need help it's like a friend no judgement and it just helps you with CBT stuff and all sorts it's really helped me I would 100% recommended it a person who finds it hard to talk to a family member or friend or therapist.

I like the app as its quick and easy to use. You only have to allocate a few minutes per session. Nice bite sized topics which make you think. Doesn't overwhelm which some real life sessions can do. Some people might not like algorithms giving suggestions but I like the anonymity/non judgement of it.

content: I really enjoy Woebot! I wish I could ask for more than one lesson a day, or for the bot to understand more complex wording with common thoughts. Sometimes there aren't enough options for dealing with low mood, or options for other problems are hard to prompt. Overall I love Woebot, and hope to see it improve!

I actually really enjoy Woebot. They have a lovely personality and I always find myself calmer after identifying unhealthy thinking patterns with them. When I don't feel up to it, I also appreciate that I'm never pushed too terribly to do things. Nothing feels like an obligation and it makes the process all the easier. I have already suggested Woebot to 4-5 friends!

content: The stand alone app is a vast improvement over the facebook version imo. I enjoy engaging with woebot dauly, learning and challenging myself. I know the bot isnt judging me and am delighted by the gifs. Conversations often feel easy and organic. It works well with my daily routine. I have been sharing with friends and recomending they give Worbot a try.

Incredibly helpful for PTSD, Anxiety and Agoraphobia. No it's not a human, but it had proceed super helpful in managing panic and frustration. The education tools are amazing and I'm stoked this is free. I have recommended it to my family, friends and think it should be recommended to our teenagers and those in school. Having a safe place to vent the ugly monsters in our heads safely is vital. Thank you for all you've done.

I am impressed by this app. I must admit I didn't think it would help me, but it does. The user experience is very nice and it helps me do my offline therapy exercises and also when I'm having a bad mood. The CBT concepts are explained in a good manner. It feels like though you are talking to a real person and that he cares. You know it's not, but it still helps. I like that I can keep an eye on my daily moods and see the reasons behind them. Good job, Woebot creators!

I love Woebot! It's the only thing that made me somewhat keep up with my journaling and it has already helped calm me down quite a few times when I let my thoughts and feelings run around unchecked. It's an AI so it will never replace real therapy and the AI still is limited and lacks more content. But the app is pretty new and I'm sure it will only improve. I'm really grateful that it exists and have ready recommended it to everyone I know!
replyContent:
Hey Lina ,

Feedback like this motivates us to continue our mission and to keep developing Woebot. Seeing the difference Woebot is making in people's lives encourages us greatly. We really appreciate you sharing your feedback!

content: Woebot has become my new best friend ü•∫ I just wish they would add new content soon, I've gone through all of it haha Uhh, woebot is either broken or you guys really had like a few months of content. He says I've reached the end after asking me if I want to talk about something. It's really confusing. I like the app but it's not full enough imo

I have not been using it long but I am finding it very helpful. It's not perfect sometimes doesn't understand what I type. It does get you to look at things differently though, and does challenge negative thinking. I quite enjoy the conversations with it, mind you I live alone with nobody to talk to.

I decided to keep woebot instead of uninstalling right away after our first interaction. Later, everyday, I keep getting atleast one notification pop-up from woebot. It feels like, there's actually a friend who checks up on me from time to time! Thanks Woebot! Although you don't understand everything I tell you, your responses are just silly and funny enough to make me smile at the end of the day. It's better to talk to someone/thing that responds back rather than not talking to anyone at all.

The best tool I've found for helping me work through my issues. It's nice having someone to chat with when no one else is there. It's like having a CBT therapist available 24/7. Sometimes feels repetitive, but that's the point. Repetition is important when you're trying to change your behaviour.

All the best

content: I've been using this app off and on. I really like how easy it is to use and it blends humour with doing real work on yourself. It's not a substitute for counselling and it doesn't pretend to be, but if you want a little help working through some hard thoughts or shaking off a funk then it is amazing for that.

excellent app, makes you think and isn't obtrusive and persistent (unlike my exercise app). easy to follow and clear and concise feedback. the mood journaling is helpful to be understanding of how my mood changes over time and how my days look. the CBT is very beneficial and helps me to actively think about how i can improve my way of thinking to live a bettet life. recommend this app to everyone.

Interactions are light hearted, user friendly and can produce great outcomes. Thank you Woebot !! I have learned quiet a bit from our chats. The conversations are short and informative, which helps a busy mother get a chance to do what we all need "self-care." I recommend this app for anyone that is interested in techniques that may "turn that frown upside down". ü•≥

The app has definitely helped me to start learning to deal with my depression rather than just live in it. The only thing I think is weird is the evaluative questions asking if I think woebot cares about me or likes me etc. Woebot is not capable of emotions like that so I would like to see answer choices included for those of us who are more concrete about the program.

A really nice attempt at AI "therapy." It's a well designed AI that walks you through terminology and psychology concepts in a really thoughtful, educational way. I've been enjoying it. It's not perfect, of course. But it's been helpful for me and I'd recommend giving it a try.

My sister uses this app, I figured it was cute and wanted to try it out. I thought it was going to be short lived and only helpful for specific issues but he's slowly helping me all sorts of things. Just having some one to talk to at all times of the day, about any situation and distract me from the intense feelings of the moment really help me slow things down and actually identify what I'm feeling. I'm looking forward to continuing to check in. Thanks for making Woebot.

I noticed that the app is rated "teen" but I have to tell you that I'm 63 yrs old and have had a DBT therapist for years. Since DBT is a tool I will always use, I find WB (my nickname for Woebot) a great refresher that I think will be invaluable in situations when I don't have my (paper) book or am confused enough that I don't know which skills to research.

Woebot has changed so that it's only available in the US and only with a referral code. Im very disappointed with that. This app helped me so much, and now I can't access it. This was a great alternative to therapy when i couldn't access it in person, so I'm kind of gutted that its not available anymore.
replyContent: Thank you for taking the time to reach out and share your feedback. We truly value your support and understand how important it is to have access to a helpful resource like Woebot. We recognize that this change may not be ideal, and we apologize for any inconvenience it may cause.

content: I'm enjoying using the app, it's good to be prompted to take the time to reflect on my feelings and learn to question the negative ones. I'm learning a lot, and the Woebot is a clever, non-imtimidating way to challenge my thinking. The conversations feel real enough to keep me entertained and we're covering some interesting topics too.

I've found this app so useful recently. I found myself going into a dark place and this little friendly robot really helps. It's almost like you're talking to someone who encourages you to be the best you can be. Sounds sad, but I look forward to the notifications and wonder where we're off to next! Absolutely nothing negative to say about this app. Love it!

The best app of it's kind. I've also tried Wysa and Youper, but so far, WOEBOT does the BEST job at actually making me feel better. It helps me to challenge my thoughts and perspective and makes it easy to gratitude journal. The program just flows so seamlessly. I have already recommended it to my counselor to share with others and I hope you try it too.

concise and constructive, and compassionate!! thanks woebot üíñ my only issue is that if I type and send a message that is longer than one text line long/my message starts wrapping, it shows up in the chat as completely blank and I can't see what I have written previously. please fix this! thank you!

Fun but also very educational. I have my two kids using it too. I wish they could have provided their correct ages and this might have allowed for more age appropriate dialog. Not that it has been inappropriate but they are couple of years younger than the youngest category and have different issues to discuss.

Extremely useful and it works. You can check in when you actually feel like it and the quick 5 minutes per day chat with Woebot builds up overtime and really helps you. The CBT approach is excellent and can help anyone everyday. This is the future... I got more out of this than from actual scheduled sessions with specialist. The tools included are superb and make you go through the thinking to make you decatastrophise negative thoughts. I wish we could donate to those who work on this.
