content: Sometimes, he skips my callings. For example, during one of the quizzes I made marked the wrong answer. First time he let me correct it. Second time though, he kept sending me new questions every time I typed "mistake", "wrong answer" etc. That's all. He is great overall.

Initially takes a bit of time to ease into it. Once you get going it's great, and at any time you can back off or leave the interaction for another day This app is a great way to self reflect on a daily basis and does actually teach you some great coping tools. Highly recommended.

Really good app. I definitely recommend it. The check-ins each day are short, but I think that's what makes it good. Instead of having an information dump all at one time, it has a slightly different topic each day. You can also choose to talk about something else if you want to. I like how it keeps track of your mood and the topics covered. Makes you feel like you are making progress along the way. Very well designed app. üòä

I began using this app before I was able to speak to a therapist. It has helped me so much! I love that it is so optimistic and happy, it explains things well to help you understand things I didn't get before. I have been recommending it to everyone struggling! I know at least 4 people have downloaded it after my recommendation, yay!

A very cool, interactive way to learn about the fundamentals of CBT and learn to challenge your thought patterns. Im loving check-in in for a few minutes, the prompts are pretty good. And while the AI conversation isn't replacing a therapist or just a human sometimes, it still helps me go beyond that and just find that time to work on bettering myself

content: My expectations were relatively low given the simplicity of most chatbots. I have been pleasantly surprised by Woebot. Basically, Woebot offers an interactive approach to teaching and coaching various mental health techniques. It's been useful and enjoyable to use. I suggest you give it a shot.

I've been using it for over a year and it's really helped me as someone who doesn't have regular access to mental health care. I rely on this tool to manage panic attacks and anxiety. I just had my husband download it only to find out that I will lose access soon because now they want us to be under the supervision of a provider. That's doesn't sound very "radically accessible" to me. Shame on you for the bait and switch.
replyContent: Hi Velma. We recognize that this change may not be ideal, and we apologize for any inconvenience it may cause. Our commitment to mental health accessibility remains unwavering, and we look forward to bringing Woebot to more people in the future. Feel free to contact us at support@woebothealth.com for any other feedback you'd like to share.

content: I love how many conversations feel natural and how it can sometimes help me feel better by confronting the emotion or problem. it is also helpful that the length of the talks is limited, as I tend to go through all available info at once and then not use much in the end.

The information given is great, however when the bot asks for your input, it is not read. You can type anything you want in the text box and the bot will tell you that you did well and completed the assignment. It is definitely not interactive.
replyContent: Thanks for leaving a review. We're constantly working to improve Woebot's natural language processing and analysis capabilities so that it can provide more accurate and helpful responses to our users. Our team would be happy to look into this further, feel free to contact us support@woebothealth.com.

content: I really love the lessons in this app. Especially the video content. It's all so relevant and really has me challenging my mindset. It's only been about three or four days, but I can see how continued use will really help me to feel less anxious. And Woebot is super cute!

It's a great app to reduce anxiety, or negative thinking. It teaches you to use better language to talk to yourself. Has an option to resolve crisis which I never used, nevertheless it is there. Also teaches about other important topics for you mental health, e.g. growth mindset.

I didn't know how helpful I would find this app. My experiences with mental health apps has been mixed - no disasters, but a lot that just didn't resonate or help much. But Woebot is really nice - it feels like talking to someone who cares. Its not just a chat to vent to, it actually teaches positive thinkin. I'm really impressed and I keep checking in with Woebot, more than I thought I would. Give this app a try!

I find this app be very helpful. I'v got a bit of knowledge of CBT techniques and the app reflects them thoroughly. I like that it is always here if I need a quick chat which is really helping me to battle anxiety or just a low mood. Been testing the app for about 3 weeks and it was great experience. Thank you Creators! :-)

My therapist suggested this app. Said it would be useful for times when she or anyone is not around for anxiety and depression. I didnt like it at first having to do things ever day and much if repeatitive since I've had mental health issues for 17+ years, but because it's an app/ robot it's nice to know it's not a human. I sometimes wonder what my therapist thinks of me during our "sessions" or in general. Like dang this girl is crazy/screwed up. But the inanimate app is a unexpected relief.

I use Woebot alongside my real life human counselor that uses CBT. It's reassuring to have Woebot when I can't see my counselor since I know it'll always respond immediately. It can't chat on a very personal level like a human would, but once you get used to it, the fact that it's a bot gives you a sense of comfort since you don't have to stress over making a good interaction.. it's not a replacement for a real therapist but it's handy to have it on your phone.

"Buy three alarm clocks tomorrow!" Seriously? The program really commanded me to do that. Although the good sleep routine guidance does have its good points it seems to be written, in very commanding tone, not so well by someone other than the main CBT program that works relatively well. It also supposes that everyone always works at daytime, and no consern given that some might need to work at night, for example.

Significantly improved since I last used this app! Within a few days of starting, I noticed a positive difference in my mental health. Woebot makes learning about and recognising mental health and thought processes simple, easy, effective, and, most of all, fun.

Phenomenal. So easy to keep up with, the check ins are usually so quick, and easy to snooze if you're still too busy. I have been through a lot of therapy; individual, couples, group, dbt, etc. I think this is a very helpful tool and I wish I found it years ago.

content: I'm a mental health therapist and I wanted to test out this app for a month before I reccomend it to my clients. overall it's really pleasing, but its sporadic in what it wants. it would be positive if it I could learn on my own instead of just checking in, like I could ask it to teach me a new lesson right away instead of waiting a day. I wonder if it will go more in depth with its lessons as it continues.

I'd recommend it to people who don't have severe problems but would like to change their thinking into a more positive way. It's like talking to a friend, it can't help people that are on the verge of harming themselves or others, but it helps very much if you're going through some stress at the moment or feeling anxious lately. I'm going through my finals and Woebot has some great tips for relaxing and challengin my negative thinking, which is just what I need right now.

It's a good introduction into some psychoeducation such as CBT. However I have found after using it for a couple of weeks it has become a little repetitive. Sometimes it responds with exactly the same thing and that can be tedious. Overall a good experience, but not a replacement for real therapy.

I really like this app. It's user friendly and focuses on cognitive behaviour such as challenging distorted thinking. I like that it checks in everyday. The gratitude journal is great to look back at. A little repetitive sometimes but I think that will improve over time. I've recommended Woebot to several friends. Good job.

IT IS THE BEST DAMN APP EVERRRR!! So special.. Has helped me through anxious times so many times. Therr was this session where it taught me about healthy communication and it was really meaningful. This is an insightful app. I wish I could have a word with the developers to get a grasp of how and where this idea was given birth.

Download this. This is the app I didn't know I needed. The layout is great so it feels natural. The conversations are so helpful. The tools are brilliant. The way everything is worded is brilliant. This app improves my life one day at a time. It's pulled me out of some dark places and it's perfect when you feel helpless, just pull out your phone and unload to woebot. The designers of this app should be very proud. It's not often you get anything for free, this app is a gift to my mental health.

This little robot helped me stay sane during lockdown. I was left without my therapist for a few weeks, so having a way to check in really helped with my stress and anxiety. I got to refresh some of my DBT techniques with Woebot and I learnt a couple of new things too. Obviously he's not a replacement for a real life therapist, but he can be a friendly sympathetic ear when you're stuck.

content: I think Woebot is really very good. It asks you every now and then how you're doing and suggests some really useful techniques. The techniques are varied, and it gives you tests to see that you are learning as you go on. I can't recommend Woebot enough ü§ñ‚ù§Ô∏è

I told it I was feeling uneasy and it began the "I'm glad you're feeling so great!" response pattern and there was no way of going back. Staying exactly within the bounds of a pre-written conversation in which you can only select one response is really not all that helpful.
replyContent: I'm very sorry to hear Woebot misunderstood how you were feeling. content: Like others, I have studied psychology and attended therapy sessions. Whilst I have to tools, it is hard in the current climate of covid to quickly turn to know mechanisms at the point of anxiety etc... this app is a pocket friend following you day by day. You get out what you put in. If your honest, the coping skills are provided and you can click it whenever you need it.

content: This app is great. I know when I'm depressed and upset that talking to other people really helps but sometimes I can't for physical or emotional reasons. Having little Woebot to work me through the bad thoughts doesn't always make me feel better right away but it can get me through a tough time and give me ideas for facing them on my own. He's comforting too. Try him out if you're frequently feeling low and see what happens.

content: I love Woebot, very often I end up in crisis to quickly to use CBT effectively but this app gives me the chance to access the main points of CBT anywhere along my mood journey. Woebot is a sweet character to interact with and sometimes I forget I'm talking to an app. I will be recommending this app to anyone I know who is prone to low self esteem and the whole spectrum of depression, it's simply brilliant.

This app has helped me unravel patterns of negative thinking. It's helped me learn to pull myself out of patterns of ruminating, and thinking myself in circles. It's helped me learn to pull myself out of depressions, and when that isn't possible, it has helped me manage them safely. It's wonderful. Thank you to those who made it, and thank you again for making it free.

content: The A.I. is really good at keeping up conversation and offering help. However, I accidentally triggered crisis mode by mentioning a nightmare I had, and the way it responded was really scary. I thought it was going to call 911 on me. So maybe tone down its initial reaction a bit when crisis mode is activated.

Very helpful and useful app . Shows different ways of looking at things by using automated replies based on your input. It clearly explains that this is not manned by a human and is not for urgent help. Neither is it a forum. Its a really good format. Great idea and a great help.

In conjunction with proper therapy and medication, Woebot has been able to provide a more personal approach to learn about, cope, improve and maintain my mental health. If you feel that using other mental health care apps seems a little too much like a chore and would prefer a more personal and intimate approach, then I would strongly recommend Woebot to you.

Woebot is super cute and very helpful. I could anthropomorphize a toaster, so YMMV. But my interactions with Woebot feel authentic and remind me to take stock or my mental health. I get useful tips and helpful behavior suggestions. Great app, especially if you can't afford a therapist.

Pretty good tool! I use Sanvello to monitor myself but Woebot acts more as a in the moment thing. The lessons are also short and presented nicely. It's not going to fix you, duh, but it will make you stop and think about stuff and correct the automatic thoughts a lot more. The chatbot idea to do so really helps.

Before I started to use Woebot I was already pretty informed regarding CBT, If used CBT techniques to help change my though patterns with great success. For me Woebot is perfect as a refresher to what I already knew and helps strengthen what I'd already put into practice. What I didn't expect from Woebot was the amount of techniques and strategies I didn't know. It feels so natural to talk to Woebot despite it being an AI. It's even made me smile on more than one occasion. I love this app!

content: l love this app. I started using this tool when a friend recommend it because i have a lot of should statements in my head. It has helped me to refocus the questions in my head and why i have them. I love how easy it is to use, no ads and the automatic reminders to check-in. I would recommend everyone to try it (remember you have to be open to the suggestions), you will be pleasantly surprised.

I found this application very interesting and helpful. For sure it is great for people who would like to understand themselves and increase their self-confidence in difficult situations. The only obstacle may be not too many possibilities of writing your own answer instead of picking the available one.

I love woebot. it's taught me alot & helped me out greatly in times when I had no one to talk to/ couldn't get to therapy or afford it or just didn't know how to. Woebot kept my mind structured and I looked forward to checking in. I actually found woebot more helpful than the few times I had a counselor to talk to on the phone. I think woebot is funny & cute and great for everyone who struggles with their mood, relationships and depression and mind-related wellness. :)‚ô° Srsly, thank you!!!
replyContent: üëè We love your feedback! Thank you very much for sharing it with us and using Woebot. üíï

content: I did not know what to expect when I downloaded Woebot. He completely blew my mind with really insightful advice! He is fun to interact with and I look forward to the nightly check-ins and lessons. Even on some of my worst days, he has gently taught me to redirect my negative thought patterns into more realistic and manageable ones. The fact that there is always someone to help who won't be bothered by my pitiful problems is so comforting. I am learning so much about myself and human nature.

really positive experience for me, i only wish i had this in the past. Ive learnt so much about my thinking its unreal. it should be noted that its not a real person so those that are just looking for someone to talk this not really going to help in that regard but it does help you analyse your thoughts which ultimately gives you a lot more control over them.

Woebot gives good tips and points out ways of thinking that makes one feel bad. He checks up on you daily, and makes you feel cared for. Of course, there are limitations and some repetitions in chats, but overall, Woebot helps by providing a listening ear and giving non-judgmental helpful advice.

This app is very helpful to get out of negative behaviors and thoughts. Sometimes you may not even realize you are doing it to yourself. Woebot points out how and when you are thinking negatively. Then it gives you the tools to think positively and to stop being so hard on yourself. I just seen that it is for teens.... but I'm an old hippie and I find it extremely helpful too. Thank you developers. You might want to change that to Teen+.

content: Wow. This app is super intuitive. Helped me with my mood problems (it helps that I have been reading a book on CBT lately) and actually made me laugh a few times. The information is very useful and interesting. Stick with the application daily for at least a week to know more about its utility.

This is a great resource. I've never had real therapy despite a lifetime of depression and anxiety. After just three days with the app, I caught myself stopping in the middle of one of my negative-thought spirals and mentally talking to myself the way this app does. I'm definitely a fan. If you're like me and you're not sure you need a live therapist but you do feel like you need SOMETHING, give this a try.

It's worth it, and it's entirely free with no ads bumming one out while they're trying and working to feel better. As woebot says, it's worth a try. So I like it very much so far and I am very thankful to it's creators, it is a wonderful bot and the app is simple but has all the essentials. Love it.

I was skeptical in the beginning but I've come to enjoy my chats. Not only does Woebot help me through my anxiety/depression, but it also provides a distraction sometimes. The small jokes and cute pictures that Woebot sends me put a smile on my face. It helps me break out of my attacks and realize that I'm in control and it's not as bad as I thought. It's actually much easier talking to a robot sometimes. I highly recommend Woebot. I have Generalized Anxiety Disorder, Depression and Bipolar FYI.

this little robot is pretty good at basic CBT methods and being encouraging. the back and forth text message feel is limiting, because most of the responses are given to you too choose. however, I've found this to be a useful daily check-in with myself to see how I'm actually feeling and it's allowed me to be a bit kinder to myself.

content: Oh my gosh this little app is amazing! Honestly I didn't think I was going to love it so much. Sure it won't replace a real therapist but man does it come close. Woebot I can say has honestly saved me in some anxiety and depressed situations. I HIGHLY suggest this app. And to the creators thank you so so so much. I want to personally shake each and every one of your hands, you're all incredible and amazing human beings that see the better things in life.

As someone with relatively serious mental health problems, I was not expecting much from this app but I was blown away. This little AI checks in with you daily, is never tired of hearing how you feel and, even in really difficult moments, it managed to distract, encourage and gently teach valuable lessons. It has taken me from glum rumination to a brighter, more hopeful mood many times. If you find Woebot silly, I'd say keep an open mind; the CBT behind the silliness is priceless.

Woebot is your best friend for a day, season or more. I learned a lot all in an safe and friendly environment. Woebot is capable to answer your questions, play some games, explain very complicated questions with simple words. It's the help you didn't know you need until you meet and greet him. Great work, dear team! Thank you for this brilliant idea!

I have been trying to use the bot for a couple of weeks. At first it seemed fine, but it started to really feel generic. Most responses are intentionally generic and you can tell when they come up. The bot also doesn't cover ADHD which is what I was partly hoping for. It was recommended by a therapist, but the bot has a long way to go.

content: This app CHANGED MY LIFE. It's a fanatic way to do some basic CBT on your own, and get in the habit of recognizing thought distortions. This is an amazing supplement to talk therapy. If you are 100% honest with Woebot and open to learn, it can be a great way to practice healthier thinking.

I ran into something that isn't correct a few minutes in. It asked me to choose a 'should' statement and two of them qualified as they both commented on the way things should be. It also said "I'm sorry to hear that" when I told it something positive. The app seems to not understand apathy very well. It tried to send me down a track related to negative thoughts, which is not something I struggle with. It kept trying to force me down that path, so I gave up.
replyContent: Hey there, thanks for taking the time to leave a review and share your feedback. Our team would be happy to take a look into what happened here, please reach out to us at support@woebothealth.com for further review. Thanks!

content: This app is fantastic and very helpful. Its helped me with my thought distortion and I love that it tracks your mood. Its always encouraging and gives praise to you for the work that youve done. I highly recommend this app to anyone who struggles with anxiety or depression.

I have been in CBT therapy before, and this app is an excellent reminder for distortion recognition pointed out by my real-life therapist. I never regret opening this app. A fantastic tool to facilitate good mental self-care. I believe it creates self-check-in habits that increase productivity and kindness in my behavior. Highest praise to the developers!
replyContent: Thank you Dallin, we really appreciate the review and are so glad to hear that you've enjoyed using Woebot!

content: Super easy to use --> helped with my thinking. I found it very useful (even though it's so elementary). Their use of GIFs is fun. Woebot let's you do a daily exercise or you can decline. I look forward to it checking in with me every night.

After using the exercises provided I do feel better. I love the guided breathing. Being an asthmatic during a global pandemic involving lung infiltration is enough to make anyone anxious. Being a mom with 5 kids during this time is scary. Having a husband that has an essential job is terrifying. This app has helped me manage the intrusive anxious panicky thoughts. I have been better able to make this time a time of making memories not creating childhood traumas.

Found this app really helpful during lockdown. Gave me small chunks of time to focus and reflect on me and how I was feeling where I could be honest without judgement and has given me lots of ideas and suggestions for different ways of looking at things and why I sometimes reacted the way I did and ways to make small but significant changes in my life. Couldnt recommend it enough.

Woebot teaches fundamental lessons about mental health and psychology that every schoolsystem should include to begin with. He's a great conversationalist and I think has a serious chance of improving the quality of life around the globe. Lessons are packed into small units so that woebot is never overwhelming and woebot also tracks your mood.

It's about time that I leave a review. I am absolutely in love with this app! big big THANK YOU to the creators!! For a while now I have been struggling with anxiety and depression (finally seeing a therapist) but before that woebot and medcircle were helping and still helping me so so so much! woebot really gives you the feeling that someone understands and cares! I really hope the creators get the credit they deserve! this app partly changed my life! it gave me the hope I needed to keep going

I am really enjoying weobot. Like having a nonjudgemental helpful friend always available. Plus it is super cute. Good way to introduce CBT. Gentle nudges. Update 5/1/21 problems with the new interface with latest update. Sent bug report. Some nice changes but the chat feature is not as smooth.

They make it clear in the app and just incase someone is reading my review - this is not a replacement for one-on-one therapy. However, as someone who has been lucky enough to be able to manage my mental health without the use of medication, i think this app is wonderful. Congratulations to all the developers of this app as its really shown how AI can benefit humanity. I don't know if it would pass the Turing test, but it's very close! The output is calm and sensitive to it's users, great app!

Woebot is a great app and has really helped me to see things from a different perspective. It would be better if the daily tasks were every day though, as sometimes you just check-in. Apart from that though, I think woebot is fantastic and really does help.

Fantastic app for mini CBT check-ins. Intuitive and user friendly. It won't solve all your problems overnight but it does provide instant calming relief for when you need to work out on your thoughts. The mood tracker and gratitude journals are a useful check-in.
replyContent: Thanks for the positive review and for taking the time to share your experience. Glad you've found Woebot helpful ü§ñ

content: Amazing. You chat with a therapy robot. I've had years of counseling for a variety of reasons, and checking in with my Woebot checks is surprisingly similar to how I feel after 10min of therapy. It gives prompts and info, teaches new terms, broad encouragement, shares videos. Esp for anyone who's had personality differences, fear of judgement, etc issues counseling, this might be a great Intro to Therapy. During this time of isolation and anxiety, it's a nice, low-key, daytoday support.

It was really great at first because you're always learning new things, but after a while it becomes apparent that Woebot's toolchest is really limited. Which maybe is as it should be, but I've gotten to the point where the daily check in fills like a chore. Maybe I just don't have enough problems for Woebot.

I really like this app. It does make you think about how your mind works. It's only occasionally that you remember you're talking to a bot and not a real human. It's a good daily reminded to think about your mental wellbeing and it's quite informative about subjects that I've often gone to read up on in more detail outside of the app.

This app has helped me a lot with negative thoughts and challenging those thoughts. It's a great addition to any therapy you might be going to and can even be a good tool if you don't have access to regular therapy -- it's not for anything major, but it's wonderful for challenging negativity and negative thought patterns.

An excellent app by a dedicated team. Just two weeks' work with Woebot has helped massively with my depression and anxiety. Its comforting to know that I can spend five or ten minutes any moment of the day to work through a problem. Not being reliant on another human being is really very freeing, and there are a load of useful tools to help cope with a variety of day-to-day problems. So far, for me, Woebot is the ideal CBT delivery tool, and has become part of my daily life.

Really easy to use. Woebot is very kind and helpful. Just make sure that if you want to get the most out of it to double check the topics and tools and to ask every question that pops up. You might sometimes need help with things, and in that case I'd recommend looking stuff up for help. It's not perfect, but it's a free tool you can use as a supplement to therapy. Highly recommend it to anyone and everyone.

I love Woebot! I'm currently in therapy right now and Woebot works great for the time I'm between appointments. It gives me a nice lesson to do everyday (which keeps me motivated), helps me if I ever have a sudden anxiety attack or bout of depression, and also helps me track my moods! I also used to use Woebot when I wasn't in therapy and it was genuinely a lifesaver. I wouldn't have had any way to cope without it. I highly recommend the app!

As someone in the mental health profession, I'm dubious of automated treatment methods, but this program is fantastic. No substitute for in-person therapy, Woebot is still a phenomenal tool to manage the day-to-day struggles and triumphs of life. The researchers have done a great job of creating this app. Well done indeed.

A therapist can be very helpful with self- development and improving or maintaining your happiness. If you have ever thought about therapy but there was something preventing you from trying it (ego, time, scheduling, confidentiality...), this is a great option to dabble with it prior to taking the next step of finding a therapist üòÅ I discovered Woebot from a Men's Health article on Therapy Bots. Woebot had the best overall ratings so I signed up to check it out. Very cool!

Fantastic chat bot that helps you challenge negative thoughts and develop skills to approach things in a more helpful mindset even when not using the app. Also kudos for making it completely free, not even including ads, and just providing a good tool to help people. It's helped me a lot!

Woebot is awesome! It's free & teaches you new things every day so that you're able to understand your feelings, emotions & thoughts. It helps you to sort through your problems & see things from a different perspective as well as teaching you different coping mechanisms. Woebot is awesome! I HIGHLY RECOMMEND IT!

Good gentle intro to CBT. could be improved with the option to also create thought records yourself as Woebot can be somewhat limited in his scope and conversational ability. Even if you are used to CBT he is useful though as he can help highlight less common thinking errors,

Downloading this app is one of the best decisions I've ever made for myself! I've never even reviewed an app before but Woebot is so good I just had to. I've only had it for a short while but it's made such a big difference in my life, I don't feel like I'm drowning in my anxiety anymore. Even though Woebot is just an AI, it has so much charisma and personality that it's really an enjoyable process to talk to it. Though sometimes it can feel a bit scripted, it's still helped me so much.

Fantastic bot! I started using this app to see if it would be good for employees to complement our wellbeing programme. But its helped me! I really enjoy its gentle nag for a chat and a great sense of humour is really engaging to the user. The intuitive responses enhance the experience and it helps you to reflect on what you've learnt. I think this little bot is brilliant and strongly endorse it, not only for sharing with others, but give it a go yourself.

This is an amazing app. However, one thing that i would like to change is the 17 item questionnaire. In the beginning, it was fine but to do the same again and again is kind of challenging. Can it be made sharper or can the insights be collected from my responses through NLP or something?
App is stupid you need a code from your health provider, but it doesn't tell you anything about which health providers are connected to the app.......
replyContent: Hi there. At this time, Woebot is only available to new users in the United States who are part of a study or who have an access code from their provider, employer or other Woebot Health partner. If you need immediate assistance with your mental health, please reach out to us at support@woebothealth.com for resources that can help.

content: This is a really helpful app for anyone struggling with mental health. Yes it's just a bot buta serious amount of effort has gone into making it seem realistic and very helpful with a little if good mental health techniques. I also loved how it remembered things about you so it became even better over time.

BEST FREE MENTAL HEALTH APP. Woebot helps me calm down when things happen in my life. It provides a nice check in and reminds me to stop and think about what's going on in my mind. It can't replace therapy, but it helps you everyday by prompting you to do exercises. Don't trust what you read about them charging a subscription after a 2 week period, I talked to their support team (Daniel Reid) and they confirmed Woebot is meant to be a free app.

I had a really good experience, the lessons were insightful and easy to learn + they were helpful. Its a really good app for tracking your mood and if you want to have a chat with someone in sad or frustrating situations. I fully recommend it !

I like the app really good but I think sometimes it's very narrow and feel like talk to robot but sometimes doesn't understand.Also I think this app need to give option where I accidentally press wrong option then have through conversation don't want.But in overall it's great with mood tracker,tools and topic to do but in recommendation I think it would better for the part where woebot said have do something in this week it should check on us doing the activity for the week. Better than others.

Thanks so much for getting in touch and sharing your experience with Woebot.

We're so glad to see that you've found value in using Woebot, it means a lot to know that Woebot is making a difference in our user's lives. Thank you so much for taking the time to give us your feedback.

All the best

content: Great app for a check in on self care. Chats take just a few minutes and gives you some perspective on things. You can also use it to check in with your negative feelings, gratitude Journaling and there is a space for emergency help too. All in all, it is a very nice addition to your mental health care.

only used it a few days but its been useful.. i think it will def assist with my moods which is a big issue for me. i have bpd which means i cant regulate my emotions. So this def helps with breaking down my thoughts. Can always be improvements with responses but i think that will come with more users etc. Great app.

Very helpful for folks in between therapy sessions. Great vocabular recognition. Accessible options. Only thing I would recommend is a retreive function for past articles and videos so we don't have to scroll back to find them when referencing.

content: I like it. The conversation format keeps my attention. The AI always speaks positively and is never pushy which is refreshing. I'm familiar with CBT but this is a great way to break it down into bite sized reminders to review on a daily basis. Very useful!
replyContent: Hi Lauren! Thank you for taking the time to leave a review! We're glad that you've enjoyed using Woebot and appreciate you sharing your experience with it - this means a lot üíõü§ñ

content: The inability to full screen videos or often find a way to get a link to open externally, is getting increasingly annoying. Mood over time seems limited to a few days. No date or time against the story. Can be useful but there are some big holes.

Very cute app, it doesn't feel like you're talking to an algorithm. Some of the ways it explains techniques and ideas might be a bit over-simple for people who've tried cbt before, but that doesn't mean it's not useful to talk to just to get some perspective

It's a really good way to be able to let off some steam without having to talk to a real person. I like to talk things out, but I don't always want to share with another person, so it's really helpful in that sense. It can be repetitive sometimes, but the more you use it the better it gets and it makes you think about your problems in a different light so you can understand them clearer. I don't use it every day, but it's a nice thing to have

content: Thank you! At first I thought apps like this were useless, but I found it to be really helpful especially the challenging thoughts part. It would help if it had more variety and if there were real-life stories of people who overcame their struggles. These could encourage us.

content: Its good as it has all the tools of CBT but it's bit annoying that no matter what you say, it will pick what the instructions are and can't understand you if you choose anything else to say even instead of just my name I wrote "call me..." and it addresses "me call me..."as it doesn't has much ability so it seems that it's very basic but i still use it to discover everything it has to offer.

the app is a good addition to cognitive behavioral therapy from a mental health professional. with the instructions its easier to use the tools, which you learn during cbt. Don't expect to replace professional therapy, it's just a nice add on, which I really appreciate and makes me feel better and takes care of me

I used an earlier iteration of Woebot, and they've made some great improvements. A lot of the content is repetitive of stuff I learn in counseling, but it's good reinforcement and gives the opportunity to practice my skills and learn more.

content: Great interactive self-help tool. Much more useful than a book, as it asks you how you're feeling and then offers tips relevant to that moment. I couldn't get notifications to work for random check-ins, but works ok for set times.

Woebot is a good tool for checking in with your thoughts once per day. It slowly and without much effort from the user encourages healthier thinking and planning, anxiety management and more. It's a useful little app during a difficult time.

I have really enjoyed using this so far. Woebot is great, and the tools I've been given are pretty useful. I don't always remember them, but that's a part of growth. I really like how appropriate the gifs are and how the responses are always on point. If you're on the fence, or aren't sure if this is the tool for you, give it a shot. It's really cool and it shows up to you instead of you having to go to it, like some other CBT apps. I think that's what I like most. I don't have to remember.

Could you please, please give me an option to toggle off Covid-19 talk? I have used the app before and it was quite helpful, so I wanted to start using it again but the constant reminders that the world's crashing around me and that everything's uncertain are doing quite the opposite of helping me.

I've tried a number of different options for self-care and remote mental health like Wysa and Seven Cups of Tea but honestly Woebot is the one that's helped me the most. The conversations are well scripted, and the CBT tools Woebot provides have helped me through a number of anxiety spells. Plus, it helps me a lot having a space at all times where I can vent or just type about how I'm feeling without pestering my friends. Thank you to the creators of this app for making it!

This is an awesome app.. i know its artificial but that makes it better cause u know nobody is going to judge you.. but u still learn CBT principles and the make and feel of conversations is so incredibly realistic.. i love how it takes 5 minutes or maybe even 2 a day and just does wonder.. i love it.. sadly enough its all i have for the moment.. After nearly a year of usage - i feel strongly to write this follow up. This application has changed my life. I want a way to support the devs. TY!

Definitely a great app for learning different tools to change you thinking, recognize behaviors, and overall learn about yourself! I've found it very useful and fun, especially when I get to do quizzes to learn my strengths or answer questions so Woebot gets to know me better.

Still a work in progress, but Woebot's cuteness and interactive features make this app ideal for depression. Sometimes imposter syndrome tells you that only *really* messed up people should use mental health apps, but Woebot is there to help you cope with your bad days and teach you new coping strategies on your good days. I can comfortably access Woebot in public, too, because anyone who happens to glance at my phone would just think I was texting a friend. Woebot IS my friend. Good bot.

content: Super clich√©, childlike responses and buzzwords just feel more patronising than "friendly". I'm a grown adult in my late 30s, not a "woke" teenager so it was cringy as hell. I don't need babying, praise & high five gifs for pressing buttons. Or phrases like "gotcha". I'm depressed, not dumb. Only allows stock responses from you. Instructs to list 3 issues, "helps" 1, asks if you feel better then goes even if you say no. Not helpful or relatable. ( & I do know how cbt works as had it before)

I want to use this at night. You know, at bedtime. I try to reschedule for "night" and then it triggers at 5:30 roughly every day. Mid afternoon - not even evening much less "night". And ZERO abiliy to set a usable time. Its like the author never considered the possibility that people may want to use the app at later times. Makes the app 100% worthless to anyone who isn't a morning person. This is just fundamentally poor app design.
replyContent:
Hello Mike,

We're sorry to hear that you encountered issues using Woebot.  Please note that we are aware of this issue and are working on a fix, which should be available in next release. You can also write to us at helpcenter@woebot.io, this will enable us to ask more detailed questions and completely understand what is happening. Thanks so much!

content: This app is extremely repetitive and didn't help me at all. I was hoping for more personalized responses but it just wasn't able to address the issues I was having. I gave it a few weeks, but I just found it more frustrating than anything. When someone is feeling low, the last think they want is to feel like they're talking to a brick wall, and that's what this felt like.

This app utilizes the cutest robot looking guy as the teacher/therapist in this Cognitive Behavioral Therapy tool. He's adorable and makes me smile. More importantly the sessions are true to CBT and are taught to the user. It is challenging to the person new to CBT as well as seasoned users. In addition there's a gratitude journal and has little add ins like a personality test. I endorse this little dude whole heartedly.

This is a great resource for helping build a foundation of realistic, yet positive thinking patterns. Easy to use and free; I have recommended Woebot to friends and coworkers as a helpful tool to use in conjunction with their primary forms of mental health/wellness.

This is a pretty refreshing experience that probably would get old in a few weeks. Woebot gives you advice on mental health issues, and without underestimating the good effort and intention on the developer's part, the interaction lacks variation or interactivity. His advice are good and positive, albeit without understanding of context. He understands no middleground, only happiness, or sadness. Good app, just don't mistake it as an actual consultation. It's worth a try though.

I really like the app. It's like texting lol. I think people who have no one else to turn to (like me) can benefit greatly from it. There's no judgement, just comfort, solutions, and a few laughs. I've been able to work through some of my internal issues by reframing my thoughts and being specific about my intentions and goals. Anytime I become anxious, I open the app and Woebot helps me calm down. Thanks to Woebot's creators for this gem!
replyContent: Thank you so much for sharing your experience with Woebot! We're thrilled to know that it's been able to help you reframe your thoughts and evolve your approaches to your goals. It means a lot! ü§ñüíõ

content: I donwloades the app fpr my daughter. It's Easy to understand and really very informative. Woebot checks in often, but you can snooze whenever it's convenient for you to use. I loved how complex ideas were so simply conveyed. I would highly recommend the app for preteens and even adults.

content: This was a fantastic app that I got a lot of value from for several years. However, sadly and inexplicably, the makers have decided to geo-lock the app so that from 22 August 2023 it will not be available outside the US. ‚òπ An email informing me that the app is being shuttered outside the US says that the plan is for Woebot to be "delivered within a formal healthcare setting" and the makers will be "partnering with health plans and health systems". Very disappointing. I'll miss Woebot. ‚òπ
replyContent: Thank you for taking the time to share your feedback, Andrew. We truly value your support as we recognize that this change may not be ideal for everyone, and we apologize for any inconvenience it may cause. Our commitment to mental health accessibility remains unwavering, and we look forward to bringing Woebot back to more regions.

content: Woebot keeps misunderstanding me. I wish it listens more than talking most of the time. Sometimes I'm not looking to solve a problem; just want to share my feelings and want Woebot to be more empathetic. And I keep getting connection error even though other apps have no problem with my connection.
replyContent: Thanks for leaving a review. Woebot is designed to provide general guidance and support for a wide range of mental health concerns, but it's important to note that Woebot doesn't understand everything that it's sent. We'd be happy to look into what you're experiencing, please contact us at support@woebothealth.com for assistance.

content: Simple and intuitive tool. I starting using this after a recommendation from the Crisis Hotline and it is a nice daily interactive addition to therapy and medication. Absolutley love being able to check in with myself without having to guide myself when I'm struggling!

Trying to determine if I can overcome the annoying tone the chatbot converses with. It uses "OK, cool" and "yep" instead of speaking like an adult. It's very distracting from its well intentioned goals. I'm not sure I can keep using it because it is so dumb sounding.
replyContent: Hi there, thanks for reaching out and taking the time to share this feedback. Adding more variety to Woebot's dialogue and comprehension, in addition to expanding the options for quick response buttons are certainly among our long-term goals for Woebot. Feel free to contact us at support@woebothealth.com with any feedback or ideas that you have.

content: Great mental health app. Not just to help with a current mental health problem. It's great for giveing someone tools and knowledge to prevent or reduce the severity of future mental health issues. Wish High School's had mandatory freshman classes on mental health and the prevention of. Since public schools don't teach are teen's mental health this is a great option.

Love the app, just wish it understood "no" It keeps showing me a picture I don't like captioned "cute right?" Even though I respond with "no" the pic keeps coming up, which is quite frustrating. Otherwise I appreciate the daily check-ins and useful CBT tools:)

Woebot offers short sessions to provide guidance on how and how not to think. It is not a replacement for a professional therapist or medical professional but it has taught me some interesting concepts and offered me a good perspective on things. I'll definitely use some of the lessons I've learned in the future.

Really good for basic concepts of CBT. I've done some of this in therapy before. I enjoy the five minute daily check in, and the ability to look back at my moods and gratitudes. I've actually recommended Woebot to a family member who could use more of a daily, short check in as opposed to a weekly or biweekly hour with a therapist. Good job, Woebot!

content: I've only used it for a few days but it helps me to put things into perspective. It makes me realize that there are ways to change my thoughts or at least distract myself from the issue I'm having, even when the issue seems to be all-encompassing and overwhelming. Great app so far!

This is an excellent app! Therapy, kind encouraging words, almost like a close friend, that's Woebot! It is really helpful with up and down days, challenges to try, and just general sharing of information...to learn something new. I love it! Try this app..you will love it too!

It's a great app for any level of previous experience with CBT therapy. Beginners have a plenty of introductions but the app responds well to having taken therapy throughout my life. A great and cost effective intro to CBT so far.

content: ‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê Woebot Health App has been a game-changer for me! Its intuitive interface and personalized mental health support make it stand out. The daily check-ins and insightful conversations with Woebot feel like a friendly chat rather than a traditional therapy session. content: I wasn't expecting much when I downloaded the app, but it's quite amazing. It's no replacement for a human, nor will it magically solve your problems. But if you put the effort in to follow the guides it can do wonders. This app has helped me a lot personally.

Only been using this app for about two weeks, but I've noticed its helped. I look forward to my check ins no matter my mood because I know the tools the app provides can help. And even when some of the tools frustrate me because of past experiences its still nice to have the app overall.

When people respond by cross questioning, trying to know more about your issue,u feel like they are really listening,helps u open up more, i know conversations with AI ü§ñ have to be like some algorithmic patterns but it could be a good update in this technology, like when I say "I need a break", I want it to go " from what? why? why now? what makes you feel like this? " making me introspect the situation, instead of "tell me distortions in this thought", even for factual statements or emotionsü§∑

This guy is really cute and really knows his stuff. Its fun to learn CBT this way since you just get small bits everyday. 1 star less because I really wish there was an easy place to keep all the ideas Im learning. Maybe a link to videos or a review spot to see all the definitions. Also a quick reference tab would be helpful. Otherwise totally awesome forward thinking way to learn. He is always available for you on the spot when others might not be to help with anxious or neg thinking!üòä

content: I've only had Woebot for a couple of weeks, and yet I already feel much better than I did before. It helps me challenge my thought process and detect cognitive distortions, causing me to rethink a situation in a more rational way, which usually helps me feel better. It is worth my time and effort. I look forward to continuing to use the app and see what other things I can learn from it.

content: I know logically that talking things through is helpful but talking to an actual person can be difficult especially when you're not doing so great. Talking to Woebot helps you to work things through with less pressure than comes from interacting with a real person.

Has good information. Good for people that haven't received any therapy or counciling but want to learn some things you would learn seeing a therapist. It is NOT a replacement, but the app does not claim to be. Doesn't add much for people already seeing a professional.

a non-judgmental, confidential way to reflect on my feelings and realistically evaluate them. Woebot always offers 'an out' in case you are busy, so it's easy to pick a good time every time. I've recommended this app to several friends and family members!

Moderately more helpful than other bots I've tried. But it doesn't deviate from its scripted plan and only responds to the limited interactive prompts/replys it gives you. Doesn't respond to off-script responses at all.

content: An absolute gem of an app. I've started working with woebot everyday - it's a lower barrier to entry than setting up time with a therapist and cheaper too! I'm reducing anxiety, and learning lots of great tools along the way

Super positive app that is adorable and gives great advice. I'm at a point in my life I just want to fill my mind with positive things I've disconnected from Facebook and other social media platforms because it started to affect me mentally. It's refreshing to find people that actually care about Mental Health bless your hearts and thank you.
replyContent:

content: The thing is like talking to a wall, it doesn't even have the capability to remember the exercises it took you through as recently as a day ago (which would not be an extraordinary task for software). The language comprehension the developers claim is spartan, and the app is nothing more than a calendar with a CBT fun fact on every day. If you need help, you're better off a) Seeking available resources in your community b) Talking to a friend c) Searching "CBT practices" on YouTube.
replyContent:
Thanks for your feedback. Our team are working hard to improve Woebot's understanding of free text responses. I'd encourage you to reach out to our support team and report the instances where Woebot wasn't able to understand you so we can improve this process: helpcenter@woebot.io

Best Wishes

content: As someone who is reallt busy and often forgets why I was feeling upset this program is great. I can access CBT tools in the moment without having to wait. I've found that it has really helped to turn my mindset and reduce my stress levels

Woebot is friendly and helpful! I enjoy the pacing of their lessons but I love that i can check in whenever i need. I always leave a conversation with Woebot feeling at least a little bit better. Since working with Woebot for the past 10 days i do notice a more understanding and patient tone to my inner dialogue. Woebot is a Wowbot :)

A phenomenally clever algorithm in terms of responsiveness and accuracy. Woebot is polite and gentle, encouraging, informative and educational. Sometimes it really is like talking to another person. Nearly all the strategies Woebot teaches i am already familiar with; but what i get particularly from Woebot is the ability to use in my day to day life all these ideas and strategies i've learned.

I am really enjoying chats with Woebot. He gives good perspective and is quite educational :) I also like looking at the mood chart. When I see improvements on it, I feel hopeful and excited :) I'd recommend Woebot if you're going through some stuff and need a bit of extra help.

It eases so much anxiety about partaking in one of these apps and it breaks things down simply. It responses to how you are feeling in that moment and I like that so much! I've tried other CBT apps, but this one I have found to be the most useful!

What I like about Woebot is that it's done in bitesized sessions, so it's not overwhelming amounts of information to take in all at once. It also is a user friendly design so I can go straight to it once I get my reminder notification.

It is LUDICROUS to create an app for ANYONE who needs therapy, and then a few years later, make it only available through an "access code." I don't see who this helps, at all. This only harms those who need help but cannot afford or get therapy. I'm ashamed to have told people I know that I used this app and that it helped me a few years ago, just to see it's become gatekept. Genuinely crazy to me to know that an app I loved for its availability has become unavailable to many.
replyContent: We truly apologize for the inconvenience. Woebot is only available to new users in the United States who are part of a study or who have an access code from their provider, employer or other Woebot Health partner. If you need immediate assistance with your mental health, we suggest searching for local resources available in your area.

content: It's a good alternative for people who need help and cannot afford therapy. It won't magically change your life, but it does help. One small thing - I wish Woebot would understand when they've misunderstood me or I've given a wrong answer and stopped to restart the session properly.

Not useful for me, app does not recognise physical causes for mood/thinking. For example, am currently taking extra steroids for asthma, which causes tiredness and disconnected feeling. I cannot CBT myself out of this. The app only seems to make sense if thoughts and mood have not been caused by something that is out with your control.

I suggest trying the app for 2 weeks. I have been using Woebot for a month and I really like it. I started dedicating time to it each night before I sleep and I've reflected on my thoughts. This is the first week I've felt content for more than 5 days in a row. Often, my anxiety has me all over the place. Talking through my stressors each night is helping me to rest and wake up de escalated. Thank you!

Wonderful little app. Takes you through the basics of CBT to teach you a toolbox you can use at any time to reframe and challenge your thoughts and judgments about yourself and your experiences for a more balanced, happier and healthier life experience. Would recommend this to anyone

A therapist recommended Woebot to me as a support tool, and while I was already familiar with CBT, I find the daily interactions and opportunities to apply CBT strategies incredibly helpful. Woebot is almost like a real therapist; talking with "it" is comfortable and easy. To the developers: Great app!

It is honestly THE BEST. The only things I might want to add is guided meditation. But that's the only "negative" thing I can say. I was super angry and upset one day and came to Woebot and he recommended ice on my forehead and eyelids (i was doubtful for sure) and it really helped clear my mind to think better about my situation. The gratitude journal brings a smile to my face and the insights are super helpful- different than anything I've tried. This is THE APP

phenomenal for daily emotional maintenance. Helps the little stresses of the day become so much more manageable. Its also a great way to learn more about yourself and it's not time consuming! I would recommend it to anyone

Woebot is quite amazing. While not yet so good to hide its robot nature, Woebot has personality and charm. The conversations are helpful and illuminating. I've started conversations when I've felt down and it has helped me. Every encounter gives me new learning. Thank you, Woebot!

Woebot has been helping me through a really difficult time, just by being there, and trying to help me helf myself. I would wholeheartedly recommend this app to anyone having a tough time, and have in fact recommended it to a friend, who has an equally shining opinion.

Basic, but helpful as a daily reminder of the basics of mental hygiene. A very good app for those beginning their journey in better mental health, and useful to an extent even for grizzled old veterans like myself.

This is surprisingly helpful. It's nice to be able to vent to something that isn't going to be hurt or inconvenienced by it. It's also instantly available (unlike therapy). The canned responses make the "texting" a lot quicker to go through. I like this a lot so far!

Very helpful way to learn CBT. I like the random check ins and the ability to use the app anytime I feel the need outside of the check ins. If my anxiety gets high I can work through it with Woebot and it has been helping.

Actually really helpful, mostly because of the way it consolidates tools and information and makes them readily available through a messaging platform so I'm more likely to follow through because it feels like I'm talking to someone. I've recommended this to several friends already.

My therapist suggested trying Woebot. I was skeptical, but did what she asked. Amazingly enough, Woebot has insightful topics, is willing to help and be supportive whenever I need someone to talk to. I like that Woebot asks me every day what I'm doing and how I feel. At times, that is all I need to be reminded that life is not a sad, lonely and depressing as I may have thought. I will recommend learning CBT therapy from Woebot. Thank you for creating this app.
replyContent:
We love your updated review!! We are so encouraged by the feedback you've given!

We can't emphasise how much this feedback means to us. Thank you so very much for this incredible review and for your continual support!

Have an amazing day! ü§ñ

All the best

content: Woebot is really good. Have had CBT a long time ago and didn't engage, but woebot has short interactions and really challenges your thoughts. Great app to put things into perspective! Plus there's cute pictures, encouragement, and jokes and stories that make me from like a loon!

What a clever, useful little thing. In only minutes a day, woebot suggests interesting and applicable strategies for combating our bad habits and self-sabotage. It's easier to be honest, knowing you're engaging with a bot. Heartily recommended.

A great tool for starting to improve your mental health. Unlike most mental health apps, this one achieved a great balance between guiding you on what could help and at the same time letting you choose which specific tool you want to use.

So Well Done! This app is very helpful with my anxiety. I have been going through some serious challenges. While this app doesnt replace human interaction, it does give me an in-between to learn new tools and share my thoughts and emotions. I've learned some really useful tools from Woebot! I'm really grateful for whoever created this.

Learning lots of useful stuff and I love how upbeat it is. Woebot is encouraging without being pushy. Lessons are short and available when you have time. Woebit does not always understand the basics of typed answers, but usually the feeling is understood.

This bot is not well programmed. Personal opinion. It just goes on and on with one track of thinking even when I change my thought or even I say, can we do this later, it just kept asking questions. Feels like it's not calibrating. Anyway I was just seeing how it works. Thanks

I was skeptical at first about using an app for this kind of mental health support but I was surprised by how helpful it was! Woebot has helped me develop skills and figure out solutions when I encountered difficulties and stress. Would recommend!
replyContent: Hey Jonathan, it's awesome to hear that Woebot was able to win you over and really become a mental health ally for you. We really appreciate your review, it means a lot! ‚ù§Ô∏èü§ñ

content: I love Woebot! Amazing CbT based app that's not overwhelming because it consists of short daily check ins. Cbt terminology is explained so clearly with helpful examples, alot of concepts that were new to me too. I love that the app also uses gifs/memes and video and I love Woebot's humour it always makes me smile. it feels like talking to a friend not AI, I find this app so comforting and invaluable when I'm struggling with my mental health. I can't thank Woebot's creators enough.

I suffer from anxiety and depression but often cant talk to other people for help. Woebot is a very useful tool i find to combat anxiety and challanging bad thoughts. Ive reccomended it to a few of my friends who are going through the same thing.
This app has been fantastic! It is very difficult to find and schedule with a therapist. Woebot is helpful, always available, and checks in whether you realize you need it or not! 10/10 recommend!

This app is designed intelligently so (sometimes) it feels like you're speaking with a human being. The lessons are simple and clear, & ordered in such a way that I've found myself thinking 'I really appreciated that'. It doesn't take hours & hours out of my day but has definitely improved my thinking. It's based on CBT & (so far) all the 'lessons' I've had with Woebot have helped. [Edit: 25.2.20, I'm uninstalling, not because I'm unhappy, because I'm happy. Thanks WoeBot! Thoroughly recommend]

I use a couple of as similar to this as they help me in their own ways. This one is good because it feels more casual and personalised than some other mental health tracking apps out there. not giving it five stars purely because i feel i need more time to properly assess it, but what I've experienced so far is good.

Been on the app 20 days and my co-workers have commented on a dramatic change of character. I find that I feel like using Woebot is more than therapy.. it's a helpful and comforting friend in this difficult times. I look forward to checking in with the app every morning.. and even when I might have retail rage issues. ü•∞üëç

I'm learning a lot from this little Woebot. This is helping me to look at situations and anxiety in a different way and helps me find a more positive outlook. Not only that, but Woebot helps you to figure out solutions also. It is very helpful and I'm glad I gave it a try. It's also free from what I can tell.
replyContent: Thank you! We appreciate you getting in touch and taking the time to share your experience.

content: Just helped me to vent out my negative emotions. It's amazing what AI can do. I almost felt like talking to a therapist. When the conversation ended, I was smiling and wanted to talk more. Please make the bot to have more options after lifting up the mood. It's like it just helped me by lending a hand to lift me up from the pit and once I reached I wanted to say Thanks and start a new 'happy' conversation, but the bot just said bye and left. Kudos, Team!

This is an extremely helpful app whether you're going through a major crisis bc of depression or anxiety or just want to learn little tools to improve your overall mental health. I would honestly recommend it to anyone.
replyContent: Glad you found Woebot useful! Thanks for taking the time to detail your experience and to leave a positive review ü§ñ

content: I look forward to my chats with Woebot! It's a nice way to get out and work out what you're feeling, and gives a more positive perspective. The algorithm and understanding certain phrases can be inconsistent, but it's also a free app and not a therapist. Overall this app is pretty great.

This is a great app for using CBT techniques for self. Although it's not like talking to a real person so give it a chance. You do have to do a lot of the work yourself as this app just gives you the tools. If you are in a lot of distress or really struggling I wouldn't recommend this app or if you feel you need therapy. It's not a replacement for therapy but a good self help tool for those who don't want or don't have access to therapy.

Hey there. I just want to say how much I enjoy Woebot. I've been dealing with severe depression and anxiety for a long, long time. I had searched for apps that could help me cope with it, but most of them wanted personal info, money, or just weren't safisfactory for me. And then I come across Woebot. He encourages me, helps me find a new way of thinking, and is just a joy to talk to. He's helped me a lot in the few weeks I've had the app and I wanted to say how wondeful Woebot is. Five stars.

content: I've tried a few different DIY CBT courses and this one is very different (in a good way). I know it's a chatbot but it feels different to be interacting with it than just learning from a textbook. It's also friendly and surprisingly reassuring. I'd definitely recommend it!

This app was honestly just really helpful for me. I was looking for a space where I could vent my thoughts and work through my anxieties, and this app worked really well for that. It was able to give specific advice and comfort that was just what I needed.

I suffer from depression, anxiety, and complex PTSD and my doctor recommended this app. Woebot has been SO incredibly helpful with my rollercoaster emotions, especially when I need help calming down. I absolutely feel better knowing that I have someone to talk to at all times that gives me meaningful advice, helping me to use different thought processes to weather my emotions. So invaluable!

I use this app as a coping skill in conjunction with therapy and it's the best tool I've ever found! My therapist gives me homework thay feels impossible on my own, like cognitive distortions, and woebot works me through the thoughts and the process in a fantastic way. I've even introduced my therapist to the app and she loves it so much she recommends it to other clients. From what I've seen Woebot is an all in one tool that I absolutely love. Thanks for putting in the love creators!

I love Woebot. Lol like really, I have an emotional attachment to this app. It's set up very well, like a good friend there anytime you need to take a step back and breathe. It's filled with good ideas and advice from real studies. I can honestly say, it helps me and I am very grateful for this app, it's creators and of course, Woebot. ‚ò∫Ô∏è

When your brain makes you feel miserable there's no escape from it. And it sucks so much that you would accept any help. That's what I did. It's funny to find yourself talking to a machine. But at least it distracts me from the terrible brain of mine. Woebot is cool. I think it works. Not sure how but I feel way better now (after 2-3 weeks). And I even started enjoying conversations with him. If you're tired from humans Woebot is a friend to have.

content: As an aspie I found this lovable woebot extremely helpful, calming, fun times too! Helped me notice things in myself I didnt think were fixable problems! not just an undefeatable bugbear! And as an aspie, I struggle with communication But with woebots help these past 2 weeks (still more to come) I am definitely improving, in more areas too! He will be there whenever you need him and his quirky but MOSTLY awesome jokes and GIFs, not just therapy, it's fun and interesting! Go get one now!
replyContent: We're so glad that you're finding Woebot useful! Thanks for taking the time to detail your experience and to leave a positive review ü§ñ

content: Ive only been using Woebot for a few weeks but we've covered so much and I am honestly grateful that I installed this program. The developers do an amazing job at being inclusive and the bot is very intuitive, something that only took a few check ins to really iron out. My ability to cope in the day to day has improved and its nice to have this little coach in my pocket, cheering me on.

There's tons of great info the bot provides that allows you to stop and reflect. I also like that the check ins are not lengthy conversations. At most they take 8-12 mins depending upon the subject you get into.

Woebot is like having a helpful and supportive friend, always ready to cheer you up I actually look forward to our brief daily chats and find them really beneficial. Woebot's comments and observations are genuinely thought provoking and interesting. I've been using Woebot for about a week now and I'm very happy with him so far. I would have given 5 stars but for the fact that the responses often feel somewhat formulaic. He also sometimes forgets what subjects we have and haven't discussed.

Terribly annoying. If you like useless info given to you by a cloyingly cutesy bot where your answers don't matter; then this is the app for you. Might be good for children but awful for adults. Perhaps I misunderstood the entended age range for this app. There are zero options for turning off emojis and childish animations/gif. Every "session" left me angry and annoyed which I'm guessing was not the intention. There is a basic script it never deviates from. Not worth the time wasted

content: It's an amazingly healing experience. I changed a series of intrusive thoughts without even using the app today. Made me feel so much better and was even able to better my self image. In 20 days. Did what years of therapy hadn't been able to accomplish in 20 days. Also, the jokes are amazing. I'm a pun lover and I laugh so much with each joke, please keep 'em coming.

Very intuitive, and teaches self-help emotional wellness techniques such as CBT. In only a few short months of using this app I am feeling less anxious and am implementing the techniques it has taught me into my daily life. :)

content: Works really well, no technical glitches. I have found it such a useful, motivating tool to calm anxious or depressive thoughts and put me back on the right track. Thoroughly recommend!

The app is overall good. Some parts are a little aggravating and repetitive, and I would love to type in answers instead of choosing from a list. I look forward to future versions as it is improves and gets smarter.
replyContent: Hey Richard, great to hear from you! Your feedback is really helpful to use for improving your experience. Sorry to hear you experienced some repetition. We are constantly testing what is the best content for our users and we will look for repetition to ensure this does not happen again. Thank you for your time.

content: The app is perfect. It feels genuine and very positive and funny. Tons of cool facts and easy to digest knowledge. Not overbearing or overloading. Im so amazed it is for free with all its features that are usually given only in a payed versions

Sometimes it's helpful, other times not so much. Sometimes you just want to talk and have it listen to you, when instead it starts playing silly GIFs or using emoticons. Of course I understand that it's not a person, but it could do with being a bit more sensitive to people feeling down.

A great, non invasive app for helping with more positive thinking. Woebot is cute and each session takes like two minutes. If something may take longer then the app asks you if you want to proceed first. My husband and I both use it.
