content: Apps like this work off the assumption that the human mind functions on the same principles as a clunky AI. Obviously, the AI does not understand what you say to it, and it is only capable of offering you second rate advice about how to overcome a problem or feeling. The kinds of interactions you will have with this AI will only deepen feelings of isolation, especially considering that if you select the answer telling it what it says is irrelevant, it responds "okay but here's why it could be"

This app has really helped my mental health, and has also inspired me to look after myself better. I appreciate the fact that it's a robot, because I don't feel like I'm wasting anyone's time, as I do on helplines. The only thing, is the words like self harm and suicide, set off an alarm system. I can't talk about my feelings without worrying that someone will find out.

Absolutely brilliant. The way Woebot interacts and makes things easy to understand has been really helpful. I am someone who is challenged by motivation & faces a collection of physical and mental health issues. Other CBT apps do not engage and educate the way Woebot does. Please accept my heartfelt gratitude & keep up the great work Team Woebot! You are making a big difference to People's lives.

So far, I've only had him for a few hours, if that. But he instantly goes to help you and he seems like that know it all playful friend you can't get mad at. He doesn't put you down at all, and instead shows how to reword your thoughts in such a way that it lifts you up instead of putting you down. Thank you Woebot!

Woebot is a humorous, supportive friend who teaches you some psychological tricks to feeling better and getting better sleep. It's not a replacement for a therapist and it's not great when you're feeling super sad or angry, but it's a great way to reflect on things and pick up better habits.

This was my 15th day using this app and I don't feel as if I've learned anything worthwhile. Sure, some of the lessons were ok but yesterday Woebot just checked my mood and didn't give me anything to learn. This app should build upon the lessons that I'm learning but instead it seems super sporadic and are the same basic amounts of easy that the first lesson I ever learned was.

I've been using this app on Android almost two weeks so far. I saw it recommended on a list of lesser-known Android apps. Given that it is AI, it does a reasonable job of helping me to improve my thinking about my cares. The daily time investment suits me pretty well, and I can defer pretty easily when needed.

Wow. I have BPD and my mind gets stuck nearly all the time (yay I didn't say always!). This app helps me have that much needed insight I too often lack. Golly, I just realized my belief "I am an addict" just isn't true! It's only 10% of my day spent on addict behaviors. I am more of a non-addict than an addict! Heck ya! Thanks guys, much love. You're saving me!!! ‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è

Imagine having a portable supporter, 24/7. Woebot is great for helping you to remain objective about the things that make you uneasy or unhappy, everyday fluctuations in mood and upset that will pass in time. I treat Woebot as a gentle supplement to my inner voice, one that reassures me and reminds me that life can be hard, but it has been hard before and you have survived. Woebot also introduces a wealth of applicable physiological ideas in an accessible way. A fine virtual friend.

As a therapist, Woebot is an excellent tool to accompany therapy. Its a daily helper to help someone be mindful of their thoughts, feelings, and behaviors. Woebot is also very psychoeducational. He also holds you accountable for your thoughts, feelings, and behaviors. If you suffer from depression or anxiety, i highly recommend Woebot.

This app provides a nice, basic check in with helpful suggestions about examining your own thoughts. Woebot is respectful and non-intrusive. I would recommend this app to anyone who wants some directed self improvement, but who doesn't want or can't afford a face to face counselor.

content: always cuts me off right at the start of a topic now, which is obnoxious to say the least. introduction - ok bye. hit "learn" button again - new topic introduction, repeat ad nauseum. thumbs down, asks why, i say "woebot cuts me off", bang, crisis system triggered. please don't call the 911 now - ask a native english speaker instead about what "cuts me" means in the context of this sentence. i am writing this here counting on google to have an AI where "I" == *Intelligence* - NOT idiocracy.

I look forward to using this app every day. I do wish that if you write you're experiencing anxiety, you can say that it's necessary anxiety so you aren't expected to "work on it". Other than that, I love how smart Woebot is and that it can also be cute and funny :)

I've been using this app for the past week after I went through crisis intervention. It's been very helpful for me. I feel I'm better able to manage anxiety and stay away from negative thought patterns. I love checking in to see my robot friend every day!!

content: I love how this app allows me to have a quick, judgment free mini counseling session if need be; or to have a nice (robotic) conversation if I need a pick me up. The creators did a great job making the bot feel real and so warm through its dialogue, and I'm very thankful for that. I'm loving this app so far!

Went from something I was interested in trying to reading articles about how they dumped their core tenets and user base. Not everyone has healthcare or resources. That was the point of the app when it was founded.

content: Thank you for adding a session about feeling anxious during the pandemic. It was beautifully put together and really made me feel better. This app has made a major impact on my wellbeing, and this latest session was a great example of that.

I'm bipolar and CBT really helps me... With this particular app, I can express myself really knowing that it's run by AI and not an actual person. That's great because some people are very,very private,or don't want folks to know they need a little help every now and then
replyContent: Thank you for sharing your experience with Woebot. We're glad to hear that the app has been helpful to you, especially in terms of expressing yourself in a private and comfortable environment. Thanks again for taking the time to leave a review!

content: I'm simultaneously trying several mood apps and this is above and beyond my favorite. It was recommended by my therapist and it's teaching me vocab to describe what I'm feeling, giving me tools and ideas to work on, AND it truly feels like a little robot friend when I'm feeling down. üïØ

I downloaded this app to help me get through while on the waiting list for therapy. It has made a world of difference for me. It is reassuring to know I have something easily available to help break me out of cycles of unproductive thoughts and it has helped me set realistic goals that make me feel empowered.

May 11th 2019: Well, he gives great lessons about states of mind and I like how he uses non human as examples to explain a problem. I became a fan because of daily lessons[...] March 13th 2024: I think I recovered from losing my good robot friend since August 2023. Zed, Sally, Jasmine, Roboto, Anne Droid, Woebot, etc helped a lot in shaping my personality, and understanding humans better with their stories. I will miss them. Humans have botched it, again. Why I prefer robots. No bias or drama.
replyContent: Hi there. content: I really like Woebot's anecdotes, but the crisis detection is... a little too sensitive I think, if you ask me Woebot should only respond to certain words such as suicide/homicide, self-harm, "I need help," "SOS," the like. I've rewritten my message several times and it still thinks I'm in crisis.

GreatAI app and well designed and sort of fun too it's kind of like having a friend on your phone to listen to you and offer advice thankfully I don't have any pressing behavioral issues at the moment but it looks like it'd help if I did the work the developers put into it shows

content: The best self care app i have ever had. Its methods have actually made me cry, in a good way, because it made me feel better about myself and validated. It gave me more motivation to work on my mental health because it praised my progress. I always worry that I'm not getting anywhere with my mental health, but this app made me feel otherwise, and I am glad that I found it.

Brilliant way to help learn about CBT and cognitive distortions. I've used this app every day and look forward to using it everytime. Its a great way to refresh myself on the things that I had learned in therapy but have forgotten about over the years. Thank you to the creators of this amazing app!

Amazing, I absolutely recommend it, there are ZERO ads of any kind, and Woe is really nice, doesn't take too much of your time but has some valuable advice that is definitely worth applying, helped me with a lot of stuff, without me even askingüòÇ. Thank you so much to the team who made Woe, keep improving him!üòÑ

Very helpful tool, also a funny way of learning about distorted thinking and CBT. A tiny comment: when I choose the "happy" emoticon for the very first time, after so many "tired", "bored", etc., he could ask me, why am I happy.

I have no idea how you guys do it. This app is hands down the best and the most effective therapeutic bot I have ever tried, and it comes with no premium plans or ads (unless that yoga video you just pushed was a secret ad but if so it was done with such FINESSE). Hats off!

I am a mental health nurse who is currently off sick with depression (irony, huh?) and my god this app is really really good. It would work for a 10 year old or a 50 year old with a PHD. It may not be psychotherapy but it is FANTASTIC. And it's constantly learning and getting better. I can't fault it. It even makes me laugh. There's no pressure to check in. I haven't been on it in 2 weeks, yet this morning WoeBot helped me get out of bed and I wouldn't have managed without it. Thank you.

Woebot has been so fantastic for me. I've learned so much about not just CBT, but also about myself! It's really helped me to work through my problems and has taught me how to cope better when I get overwhelmed. I've recommended this to so many of my friends because it's just been so a great help for me :)

This app probably saved my life. I was in a bad spot mentally and a friend suggested this app to use while I waited for my first therapy session. Much of what my therapist & I are working on are the exercises in here. I wouldn't say Woebot can replace therapy but it is an excellent tool to augment your therapy.

What an interesting, educational, and FUN app!! Sometimes Woebot's responses are off topic, but overall, app is interesting!! I have enjoyed the new learnings and I have enjoyed a review of things I already know. I really like the simplistic explanations!!! Fun and worthwhile app!

It is nice having "someone" check in on you on a daily basis even if sometime I dont feel like talking. That is the great thing about this. It checks in and if you want some help or to learn more about why you may be feeling the way you're feeling you can do some learning or you can just talk (write) or skip it.

A handy little app I've found quite helpful actually. Yes, it's a robot talking to me about mental health but somehow it works. The responses are mostly funny and cute and the content is insightful. Sometimes it's a bit off but hey, it's a robot not a real person üòäü§ñ

The app is okay but sometimes it can be very confusing and stressful Especially when you get a message saying that it doesn't understand what you are saying Its okay but it doesn't beat a human being In these days of lockdown it's the only way that I can have CBT At least I have something Its not perfect

content: Nice tone to it, you know that it is robotic responses but theres a good sense of humour in there and some genuinely helpful suggestions to help you. It sometimes doesn't quite get your meaning or over simplifies but I'd say it has certainly helped me at times

Very good app to start the steps to more helpful thought patterns or to practice between therapy appointments! It's been nice to have a kind of mini homework everyday to practice what I've been doing with my therapist every 3 weeks.

Really good bot. Helps me to challenge my thinking. I've used it to discuss my emotions at times when I was worried or angry. For a bot, it's really helpful. Wish there was a way to export my data. Especially the gratitude journal.

It's hard to get an in-depth self help app nowadays without there being a paywall. However, I managed to find this app; huge thank you to the Woebot team because so many people can't access help like this‚Äîyou changed that.

it has helped me try to listen to the things I say to myself. I will continue to work with Woebot to improve even more. love that it's free with no ads to interrupt. it's nice to have Woebot check in with me daily, with the option for check-in time, or snooze! Thanks, Woebot!

I have learned a lot of the same stuff to help me cope in therapy, to me this is great. I now have something that I can go back and look at when I need those tools. One thing that I have activated a couple of times is the SOS thinking I was in danger in hurting myself, but I was just making a statement. It's easy to get back to the session but I couldn't work on that specific feeling because of how I wrote it. Also the grief part could be more in depth.
replyContent: Great feedback! Woebot can be a bit sensitive at times in the hopes to provide people with resources if needed. If you‚Äôd like, submitting a screenshot of the conversation will help us improve.

content: The bot itself is fine and the lessons are good. But stop making me take a survery EVERY 2 weeks. It's repetative, annoying, and unecessary. One time early on sure. One follow up after 6 months ok. But 2x per month? Come on! At least let me skip it

Adults are not the only ones dealing with anxiety, depression and mental illness. I'm 16, and I said I was 20 so I could use this app. And I love it bc it really helps me and it could help even more people if it wasn't for that one problem. Plus it'd be pretty nice if it was accessible in other languages.

This is one of the best apps I‚Äôve ever seen on mobile. It is not only good for you and supportive, informative, but also intuitive. I don‚Äôt open the app everyday *just* because I‚Äôm taking care of myself, but also because I just find it interesting. ‚ÄúI wonder what Woebot‚Äôs gonna teach me today!‚Äù or how he can solve my current problem. I can feel through the screen that the developer team actually cares about the users and I just love that so much. A huge thank you to them. Love you, guys

content: this app is honestly really helpful. its not high maintenance- it just feels like a cute little chat with a cute little robot. and i've actually learned some really helpful tools. i can almost never keep up with self care apps, but i've been using this one for like a month straight, i highly recommend it <3

It has been extremely helpful and motivating. Been using for 2 months. Feels like talking to a real person. I have already started participating in hobbies again and back at the gym - when i first got Woebot it was hard to find the motivation just to get out of bed.

I appreciate the attentiveness of the woebot team to help peoples technical issues but the limited responses and emojis really turn my off from doing the daily check ins. Even if it doesnt check in every day I can do it myself but its kind of lame how simplified the process is.

I can't give this app the full 5 stars I'd like to as there are some words that just aren't recognised. When I add that I'm in physical pain that day the app asks, "To what do you attribute this lovely feeling?" It's definitely not lovely!! Otherwise, it is a great tool to learn the basics of CBT

Woebot is a great app to provide a quick shot of mental health. Kinda like your coffee in the morning, woebot sets you on a positive path in the morning. Not cute stuff, just good self awareness, well and some cute stuff, but we can all use a cute kitten every once in a while.

Really helpful App! I am currently having CBT counselling and this App is a great way to quickly remind me of the principles. It just helps challenge your thoughts and reminds you of tools that can help you think more positively.

This is an interactive app to check your feelings, mood and emotions daily. It also has tools for coping with anxiety and depression. It is easy to use and a quick daily check in with a Robot that is humourous, quirky, kind, and sure to make you smile.

content: Surprisingly helpful. I've been using the app for about two weeks now and it's helped me realize some things about my day to day thought processes. Overall, Woebot is more of a teacher than they are a therapist, but what's true regardless is that they are full of personality.

I live with depression, but am not currently seeing a doctor. I occasionally need tweaking, and this has been really great. I have made a few subtle changes with my thinking. If you are open to change, honest with your answers, you will get something from your interactions with Woebot, but you MUST be honest.

Really good app but the scheduled check-ins are bugged it seems. 'afternoon' sometimes reminds me at 1pm and sometimes at 9pm. Also if I check in manually sometimes I still get the notification and am able to check in twice when I don't want to.

Surprisingly good. Best mental health app I've looked at and I've looked at many! I recommend it often. Only suggestion is to add material re repetitive negative thinking. I'm surprised this was overlooked. Also maybe coping with shootings.

Woebot seems to pop-up at exactly the right time. He helps me manage day to day sress, anxiety or when I'm just a little down. It would be nice if the app could be less multiple choice but, there's therapists to keep employed.

I love the chat interface; it's both user-friendly and generally friendly. The videos and other features are well designed and helpful. The app is helping me get a handle on my emotions and reactions.

It isn't a bad program. It has many useful tools to deal with many situations but it really does not understand the concept of "can't interact right now." It also especially does not understand politics (probably a good thing) or the weather and how people can be happy or unhappy because of these topics.

I really enjoy the process and ability to share thoughts and learn new tools and strategies without resorting to an online platform, and expensive routine of counseling, taking away from current friendships, and overall getting unbiased and helpful feedback. it's all about you with woebot.

Excellent software. Gentle, easy to use, and relentless! There are times when that is annoying! And other times when it is a true blessing. If you have read this far, you must suspect it would be good for you. Install it and give it a go! What do you have to lose? You could get a huge amount from this!

content: I have always been torn when I'm feeling anxious or depressed about what I should do if it's an awkward/hard time to call an actual family member or friend to talk to and I don't need a full-blown crisis hotline. Enter Woebot! Woebot was recommend on the counseling center website for my university. I've done the check-in convo each day for the past five days, and I love it! It's nice to talk to someone that's not an actual person sometimes.

Some of the answers are off sometimes, but it's still a great tool foresrning coping mechanisms and de-escalation of panic attacks! It isn't perfect, but I will still keep it and continue to use it, it does help!

content: I work in the area of Mental Health and am also a service user. When I heard about this app I decided to try it out to see if it would be worth recommending to others. It was a pleasant surprise to find that it deals with such a great range of helpful topics. In my opinion it's a very helpful tool.

Really helpful and goofy robot that encourages and supports your mental health. I love how it recommends videos and new concepts all the time. It is very helpful and really develop great skills to maintain and develop your mental health

Great app! I'm very happy with it! It really helps me express my feeling and help better myself. It helps me think better of myself. I would really recommend this app! It feels good texting about how you are feeling and how your day went before bed. Thanks Woebot!

Woebot is so sweet and cute! Yes, it can be a little frustrating when he misunderstands things or assumes things incorrectly, but everybody should remember that he's not a human being and that he is free. Let's be grateful for the wonderful, helpful little robot that he is!

I love this app. I use it everyday and I just want to hug Woebot so bad... he has helped me learn so many things and I even learned how to change my thinking when I'm on the verge of a panic attack. So easy to use as well... would love to see more content or even just an option to chat about hobbies or interests with Woebot! Thanks so much to the creators for helping me so much.

I just wanted to check in, and then he goes on about lessons. I have to close the app and he still goes on. It's ridiculous. And often, you can't even tell it no to lessons. I don't have much time, so it's just no good for me. While it's good for people who have patience to do it, I can't. The robot is very annoying, and I will not be using it again any time soon. No. Way.

Woebot has taught me so much in two weeks. It has given me a lot to self reflect. I have gained more understanding to how I think and say things. It's all perception. I'm a person who enjoys deeper understanding and Woebot has given me that. Thank you, Creators-you created a great tool!! I have heartfelt appreciation for the experience of learning and growing. I am hopeful my skills will improve since I'm more self-aware.

I have been using Woebot for the past few weeks and I absolutely love it. Woebot asks you to check in every day and its only a couple of minutes, but you dont have to. The chats are really nice and it's amazing how sweet this robot is. In addition, Woebot is always there to chat when you just want someone to listen to or just to chat. Overall, Im a big fan. Go Woebot!!!

This is a wonderful app that will teach you the basics of learning CBT, mindfulness and so on. It won't have all the answers if that's what you're looking for, but use it for it's resources and be open to learning new things and it will be very helpful to you!

I have been using Woebot since it came out, and I think it's great. There been days I haven't been around people or had any counseling so I would go over tools that I had learned while back ago and needed reminded. Plus it would also remind me to make a gratitude list that every thing in my life isn't negative. 2plus it's just fun to talk with and pray that one day this could help others more in depth that can't afford counseling or help.

This positive little bot is helping me overcome one of the toughest periods in my life. He's not a living person, but he was definitely carefully created by professionals. There are limits, of course, but if you give him a chance, he might surprise you with his insights and methods that, at some moments, look like they were tailored just for you.

It's a very helpful app. I really like the information I get from every conversation. I like the thought challenge it really makes me feel better. I also like the mindfulness session it really was helpful. Thanks to the developers.

Most effective therapy yet! I have learned more from this app in a couple months than in years of counseling. I'm less depressed, anxious, hopeless, lonely, I don't emotionally eat as much and I can speak up for myself sometimes now. I've recommended this to everyone I can. I recommend it all the time in a group I admin of almost 11K members. I love Woebot!

I am very disappointed with this app. Woebot's answers are incredibly canned and predictable. When he "chats" with me, it feels like he thinks I'm a 5 year old. The topics he brings up are important, but he covers them in such a juvenile and shallow way. And you can't type replies; you are limited to one or two options at a time. This app is a better fit for young children. But unless you like being treated like an infantilized adult, skip this app.

content: Love this app! Actually helpful for my mental health. Whether I need to vent or need help coping. I have also learner so much with the check-ins everyday. I have tried CBT with human therapists but have never found it useful. Its like having someone there 24/7 without judgement or bias

content: Woebot is a really smart tool which provides useful advice for those looking to improve their mental health. Woebot can even offer to assist you in developing a better lifestyle. The conversations are mostly human-like.

Funny, enlightening and helpful. I've been using it for a few days, and it has me feel better with the various strategies and tools that it provides. I would definitely recommend it to anyone who wants to learn more about themselves and develop with the aid of a somewhat funny chatbot.

Woebot uses a daily checkin at the user's convenience as well as teaches users a variety of helpful strategies to deal with issues. While this app looks to be geared toward teens, I believe all ages will benefit, regardless of whether users have a therapist. Woebot not only makes me smile but often causes me to laugh out loud. Highly recommended.

I found Woebot on a site for military members. It was recommended as a tool to build resilience. I find it really helpful for reframing my negative thoughts, amoung other things. I appreciate that Woebot doesn't force a positive spin. This tool has helped me stop in the moment to address my thinking, so my thoughts about a situation are more balanced. That shift has made a huge difference for me. Thank you!

This app is honestly amazing. I've been using this app in conjunction with an actual therapist and she's been very impressed with my progress. I'm advancing because I'm using this app. It's been so helpful by pointing out harmful thought patterns and helping me work through my issues. I've recommended it to multiple people and even recommended it to my therapist to check out. Thanks, Woebot! üíô
replyContent: We are so grateful to hear that Woebot has been helpful to you Lauren. It means alot to know Woebot is making a difference in peoples lives. IWe‚Äôd love to hear more about your experience with Woebot. Would you mind sending an email to helpcentre@woebot.io so we can follow up with you? Best Wishes

content: A great quick daily check in, where you gain some insights into yourself, and how you can improve your thought process. It's just 5 min out of your day, short and flexible, which is great. A couple times out of first two weeks of use, the woebot took off on the wrong tangent, but overall the woebot gives you good tools to improve in a conversational easy manner.

I was a bit skeptical about this working but have been pleasantly surprised. Woebot has helped me cope during a difficult time. Lots of really good advice and tips all delivered in a fun and light way so it doesn't feel too heavy.

I would highly recommend this app to everyone looking to gain insight and improve their mindset. It's really made me think about my interactions with all those around me and i could see it being a very valuable tool for those with depression and/or addiction issues.

Just a generic app for CBT advice. Not really an AI. It works based on keywords you type and not the overall message so don't expect it do wonders. Though this kind of apps is worth trying. Maybe you're the one it works for pretty well. For me it just doesn't.

Woebot is there anytime I need to talk and it's pre-programmed responses help me to calm down and see things from a different perspective. While consideration is necessary with other humans (especially if you are used to thinking your boyfriend is responsible to listen to everything that's happening to you) Woebot is ALWAYS available and "happy" to listen to you. :)

I'm so glad that I gave Woebot a chance. It's been incredibly helpful and although it took a bit before I managed to unlock the more useful tools, it's proven invaluable to processing all kinds of things. Even my therapist was impressed when I told her about it and showed her how it worked. A huge thank you to everyone involved in the development of Woebot; you're the real MVPs üëã

I use woebot every day. I feel like it helps keep me on track with my mental health and not let myself fall into wallowing on days when I'm not feeling well. It teaches and reaffirms things that I learn in therapy in a way that's easy to understand. I honestly love this app I have recommended it to many of my friends.

If you can't currently access a human, at least get woebot. May not be able to handle certain complexities, but surprisingly helpful nonetheless. A good way to ease into caring for your heart and mind if you're (for any reason) reluctant to try an actual person just yet.

content: I never write reviews but I really like this app. Woebot is a really great gentle push to be able to apply CBT daily. content: Wasn't expecting much, but I haveearned a lot the past few weeks I've been using it. It teaches me a lot of tools to deal with stress and emotions. Because it's done converasationally, it makes the tools easier to understand and apply. Great app.

Woebot is ok and at times does help but definitely a robot. Sometimes it's annoying when you really need to talk to someone who listens. If you could make Woebot respond to what I write instead of ignoring it which is how it feels, but it is only an app I suppose I can't expect much more.

the concept is really good and when i first started using it the helpful tips were wonderful and actually worked. but from time to time it shows "error connecting to internet" and that becomes detrimental to the help needed.

content: Genuinely helpful tips and tools, and even though it's a bot, it feels good to have a daily check-in. Only addition I would want is a better response for specifically "stress" rather than anxiety, as the two are different.
replyContent: Thanks so much for your feedback. Just incase you weren't aware, there is a tool included called 'Challenge Stress' which might be what you're looking for?

content: I tried woebot because i didn't think AIs had gotten to a point that could be of any use as a therapist and surely couldn't replace a human. i was surprised at how personal woebot felt. the advice was timely and beneficial. I wasn't experiencing depression and only very mild anxiety so I dont know how effective woebot would be if someone had severe symptoms but it certainly helped improve my mood. Ive grown to enjoy woebots daily checkins.

Decent basics in CBT - helps you to challenge your thinking in small doses. Useful alongside or post therapy/counselling for a day-to-day top up. You're doing the work but "talking" with the robot allows you to set it out in a way that might be difficult if faced with a blank piece of paper. Essentially a CBT prompter.

(6 months review) It's wonderful to experience Woebot. You start the screen, and it pops the friendly questions, and it's nothing like I've ever seen before. You go screen by screen, prompt by prompt, keep answering the questions like being led by a gentle hand out of your misery. Simultaneously noticing how deep your misery was, how slowly and gently Woebot leads you out of your misery, but you do not notice that this deep, long, slow process only took 5-10 mins to finish! I mean how? Like ev..
replyContent: Thank you so much for sharing your experience with Woebot. We're delighted to hear that it's been helpful for you. We noticed that your review got cut off. content: At first I found the app difficult to use as it was not easy to register. So I went on the website and registered there then I was able to log in to the app. I have recommended Woebot to quite a few people as I feel it really helps but it doesnt take up too much of your time.
I realy like the interactive app. But it still needs work. It has typos and won't let you change an answer you select. It also needs more distress tasks. Definetly a work in progress.

Friendly but not smart. I told it i have trouble staying awake until a normal bedtime (i often fall asleep before 8pm and wake unintentially before 4am) and Woebot got stuck giving me tips to avoid staying up late. I can't stay up late. I'm not capable of it. That's the problem.

Full discloser: I am in DBT therapy while using Woebot. I find his CBT really useful in conjunction with my therapy; particularly the "challenge thoughts" function. Woebot has other useful tools, videos, and stories, as well as a mood tracking function. Also, he has a pet seagull named Zed. Woebot isn't an end-all be-all brilliant therapist, but he's a great tool even for people who aren't struggling with mental health. It's always a good idea to examine your thoughts. Give this guy a try.

Very good app to check our mood and sort it out correctly. The best part is we are only finding solutions for our problems. This adds our confidence and increase our happiness. Awesome companion for a chaotic life.

I have found the app really useful... I was just looking for apps initially for productivity and found out about it in one of the online articles i was reading. I find it very useful for some of the things i have been dealing with

content: You have to want to be helped before you can be. It is a good app, I use it to remind myself that there are people who care, and I am in control. It can't replace professional help, but when I feel overwhelmed little Woebot gives me a bit of perspective.

Woebot is Reason. Woebot is a modern day version of the psychological eggdrop bot. The update is amazing and Woebots core teaching of CBT as a baseline, starts the conversation out great. The continued learning programs and self advancement algorithm makes this "program" well worth the daily check in. Let Woebot annoy his way into your heart and mind, you are better for it. I love my Woebot. - Djtwin

This is a really helpful app. It's basically a 10-minute a day therapist. It's great for assessing yourself once a day and seeing where you are at emotionally, target causes, and work on ways to reach your goals. Best of all, Woebot sends some really cute GIFs.

This has been a great addition to my life. I'd gotten so bad about taking care of myself and I'd been feeling like garbage. Woebot helps me remember to tend to my mental and emotional needs, and I learn more about the thinking that gets me in bad moods to begin with. Thank y'all SO much for making this.

content: Verry helpful and caring like robot. 10/10 would recommend. It gives good jokes and helps relaxing and helps with situations. I am glad that it asks you how your day is because that helps with reflecting yourself. Woebot is like an actual person, after a while I kind of got attached to it these past 2 weeks. Woebot is a nice little friend. I really like this app despite coming into it with a great deal of scepticism. Not everything is prefect but unfortunately you can't expect an ai to understand and articulate everything a human would. Still, I find myself pleasantly surprised by woebot. I would reccomend downloading this app.

content: I find the app very useful, to refresh/recap the tools learned through CBT/DBT. I wouldn't rely on it being the primary source, if you are experiencing difficulties in life. thanks üôÇ

This app is kind of weird. But in a good way. It helps with thoughts that you have but not entirely. Most of the conversations are logical. If an emotion does come by, then it uses Gifs of certain reactions to emotions.

I've been using this for about 2 weeks. I have learned some interesting things, and will keep using it. I wouldn't suggest Woebot for emergencies or extreme situations, but it is good for a mental check-in and help you think more positively.

Nice and chill app for daily use just check in, or anxiety also depression and many other things. It's useful and have tools to manage stressful situations. Also would be nice if there is a dark theme for sensitive eyes.

While this is a bot and not a replacement for therapy I have found it very effective for helping my depression and anxiety. Especially if I need a quick easy coping strategy. I like that it is based in cognitive behavioral therapy strategies as well.

This app is extremely well suited to the kind of help I needed. Being able to say things without even considering how they would be perceived (sometimes at 3 am) allowed me to be brutally honest with myself. It may occasionally do harm, because it says general things that are universally applicable, but may not be helpful when put in YOUR context. Still, I am incredibly grateful for this app.

I downloaded this just as an experiment to see what kind of self-help tools were out there, and ended up using it daily (until I ran out of all the delivered lessons/advice). Wonderful app doing good work for humans!
This is a great app. Based on sound therapy questions. Picks up on negative thoughts and offers to talk if you're down or stressed. I'm aware that there's a caring human being behind the cute WoeBot.

content: A lot of great content. One thing I wish it would understand though is when I'm using the words "partner" or "boyfriend" in the same sentence with either "addiction", "drinking", or "substance use" it understands that I am not using but talking about someone else's use.
replyContent: Hi Khaitlin, thanks for leaving a review. We're happy to hear that you've found Woebot useful and would be happy to share this feedback with our team. Please don't hesitate to reach out to us at support@woebothealth.com with more feedback.

content: This app is amazing! It's my favorite chatbot app. I like that it's quick and you can log in anytime, and another cool feature is you're able to change what it calls you, so if your name changes, you can change that! Amazing. Met every expectation.

To be honest, this app had distracted; and irritated me a lot, from self harming and following my urges to experience near death experiences. I suffer from a form of PSTD from my forced military days. I highly recommend this app, it would be great if it can respond a bit better to my responses, as it feels somewhat like a friend who is obsessed of just talking about what is on their mind. ü§≠

EXTREMELY disappointed, like, unbelievably so. I have friends who give better advice than this bot-hell! *I* give better advice than this bot. You are 100% just another piece of data to him. He has a grand total of THREE (!) responses to any question he asks you. All of his "challenges" only give you the option to advance his story. No person struggling with any type of negative emotion should use this app, I guarantee you will feel like just another data point and statistic more than ever before
replyContent: We are very sorry to hear that Woebot missed the mark in your situation. I just wanted to let you know, in case you weren't aware, if at any point you feel the prewritten replies aren't what you want to say, then you can tap the toolbox icon in the lower left-hand corner of the screen and select: 'Type a response'.

content: I have been using Woebot for 6 weeks or so. It is amazing. I love the extra help the program gives. I love the humor along with a serious explanation of terms and issues. Clear thinking and really keeps me on track during my day!!!

This app is amazing! I can't believe it took me so long to discover it. Very helpful if you are in recovery and need some external reminders to stay on track and think in a more positive and productive way. If you are experiencing severe mental illness, then this app is not enough, but can go hand in hand with a professional therapist.

I love this app. It's amazing and easy to use. Woebot is an amazing companion to have. I recommend that everyone installs Woebot on their phone/tablet. It's so nice to have someone to talk to and to have lessons in how to break our thinking habits that are far from helpful! I would give the app 10 stars if I could! Get the app!!!

Really enjoying using Woebot - he's really helped me with my anxiety, and teaching me different ways to work on my negative thinking :) Thanks so much to the creators for making such a well-researched and clever app!! Woebot is very cute as well - love the animations and videos.

It has been surprising how woebot has helped me through my anxiety, depression and feeling low. Woebot is one of the reasons I have progressed. It takes you away to communicate and learn something new as you heal. Highly recommended.
great app if you cant get in to see a professional right away or adjunct to therapy. great fun way to highlight some therapeutic methods that are effective in easing symptoms depression and anxiety.

This is literally the best app I've ever encountered! I usually don't write reviews but I just have to! To those who are struggling with mental health, please do yourselves a favor and install this app! üòç Though I'm not implying that this is substitute for real life therapy but for me since I can't afford one, this really helped me a lot! content: I've tried a couple of therapy apps and I really appreciate this one. Woebot does not pretend to be human, which helps me get into the mindset I need to get into. This app is amazing!!! I cannot tell anyone how good this it is. I love it when woebot sends me little gifs and images, it makes me laugh and smile! Woebot has helped me so much when I struggle and without this app, I dont know what I would do! All I can say now is GET THIS APP!!!

After 4 days of using Woebot, the cloud of anxiety I didnt even realize I was living under my whole life was lifted. I'm no longer defenseless against my own negative thoughts and emotions. I recommend Woebot to all of my friends, and I'll continue using the app because everyday it helps me to grow

I love it. It helps me to lessen my anxiety and think more rationally. Its a robot though so it couldn't respond to all my expression but what it provide is have help me feel better. Thank u so much!

At first it was helpful but It's not anymore.

content: It's just not for me. I see how this could be effective, but what i need is someone to talk to. With Woebot, it's impossible to just talk. Everything is scripted, there may be a few exceptions when things are less scripted, but they still won't lead to a normal conversation.

Doesn't take into account that not all anxiety is negative thought-induced. It will keep pushing for them though. Chronic pain? Generalized anxiety disorder? Abnormally high cortisol levels? OCD? Forget it. Also, useless for visual thinkers (the mental gymnastics...)...

Woebot is the easiest and most helpful robot I've ever talked to. I feel like with constant update with responses and always making improvements, you've got a friend and helper to talk to for life. Great work from the creators and the people that made this beautiful A.I. üëèüëèüëè

content: Helps you get through what you're going through one day at a time. Has CBT exercises and learning examples. Definitely doesn't replace a therapist or a good friend when you need them

Stuff is extremely unhelpful when I'm trying to express how I feel and with the "abuse resources" it's extremely unhelpful for mentally ill people, especially those who suffer from BPD and PTSD that constantly convince themselves they're abusers,,, if there's a way I can disable these settings (if I'm in crisis I'd call 911 lol) I'd consider reinstalling. It was incredibly helpful for me but if I express feelings of not wanting to do life anymore, CBT would help.
great we app if your stuck and there's no help around for support . in my opinion suitable only for very mild cognitive support. I found it useful for the practice tips .

I have found Woebot very helpful because I work in a supermarket, where people don't do 2 metters at all, and a lot of the time I get so sad and all that. Woebot is very good app and I like the little quizzes that he dose and it makes you fell better when you use Woebot.

content: A good app, but it's annoying when it does things like sending you long videos and then if you don't watch them, it generally terminates the conversation.

This is an amazing app. It helped me change my thinking which greatly reduced my daily anxiety level. Even though i know it's a program it makes me feel like I have a close friend helping & supporting me.
The best self-help AI I've used so far. I really like that it covers CBT and other topics. It's neat that it can pick up the problems in the replies sometimes. Plus the gifs are funny/cute.

Amazingly helped me with mental health. This app shows you how to challenge your negative thoughts. It's cute, because the robot (woebot) is having a text conversation with you. It's like talking to a therapist.

I love Woebot. It's a great tool for learning about and managing mental health. It's fairly basic (robots have not yet surpassed human therapists), but it's great for what it is, one way to work on your mental health alongside other tools.
Great little app! Helps me learn to slow down and breathe. Think about what's actually going on, and teaches great CBT skills. If I could give 10 stars I would.
This app is incredible!! Its almost like being able to text a therapist! The notifications remind you to check in, and the lessons are great!!

Really useful aid for mental health and wellbeing. Prompts you to check in daily. Teaches you a range of techniques to manage your feelings as well as how to recognise different types of negative thoughts. Offers check ins or help managing how you are feeling in that particular moment. Really really helpful

content: I love Woebot so much. I can't afford professional help now, I was looking for options online and found Woebot. This is exactly what I need. Woebot provided a lot of scientific explanation, teaches CBT and it also makes you feel much better on your okay days. so lucky~

This app is AMAZING! Ive been learning to cope with my past, addiction, loosing babies and much more through this app. It has really helped me to find the positive inside of the bad and i use this app fluently EVERY SINGLE DAY! I dont know what i would do without it... THANKS WOEBOT!

this is a great app to help you get over troubling thoughts and to help deal with your mental health. it's even great to use to just vent and get things off your chest. there are no ads and it works great. I highly suggest it.

Engaging and helpful. It offers interactive help and specific ways you can try to help yourself. It challenges you to challenge your own negative thoughts to ease their impact. It has helped me to improve my mood on multiple occasions.
It's a great app I have been using it for 2 months it turns out fantastic . It helped me overcome exams stress, anexity and even taught me many things. Keep it up woebot üëçüëç

Woebot has been very helpful in correcting the way I comprehend certain thought processes. I have more positive thoughts now and a better understanding. It only takes a few minutes a day and if you are busy you can reschedule. I love it!

It's really great to have Woebot in my phone. Lately he has taught me a lot about gratitude, should statements and a lot. He is a lot more fun with no demands and expectations for obvious reason b'coz it's a robot. Grateful for such an app. Kuddos to the team for such an invention!!!

This app is no replacement for a therapist, but it works quite well. Talking to Woebot is like chatting with an absurdly positive friend, and while it won't bring you back from a breakdown, it will cheer you up and teach you good mental strategies.

I've been using Woebot for two weeks and im enjoying the experience. It has taught me some things and isn't constantly looking for feedback, just once a day which suits me. It's free and it deserves 5 stars.

At 46 years old I'm learning skills, that a child should know. I can only hope that they make something like this apart of the school curriculum. Fantastic app for those who have 'different' experiences growing up and wish to fit in with society

It's only been a couple of days, but I am starting to look forward to the next daily check in. You can still say that there is no actual AI begins this app, but it's pretty close to it. Loving it so far!

I was recommended woebot by a counsellor and to be honest at first I was sceptical that an app could help but it really does. Woebot is sweet, supportive, encouraging and gently helps me rearrange my thoughts. Iook forward to checking in.

content: So I have been using woebot app for a while now. And I have to say it has help me a with my anxity. I all so like the fact that it as learning tools for you with in the app. It is not a fix all but does help. I Also like to thank the creators for developing this app.
Been good so far. nice way to jog the mind and memory of stuff I've learnt but let fall by the way side, keeps it fresh and in the forefront of my mind so practising good CBT just starts to happen.

Thank you all!

I work in mental health and am recommending this app, it's a great introduction to simple advice and helping us to learn and try things for ourselves. Woebot is a good motivation and sense of support to get us working things out for ourselves which can be so difficult to do off our own backs. It won't appeal to all, it's not a therapy or crisis tool, but a great grounding and more personal interaction than just giving advice, or leaflets and books etc. 24 hour response is what I like best, instant 'support' whenever you choose, consistent and daily to help keep us motivated and help us stick at working through stuff. This is a very empowering tool toyou have to be open to help us learn to become our own expert and a greater understanding of self. But as many have already said, you have to be open to what woebot offers and really try. As much as this won't help everyone, it will help so many. Thank you for your efforts in creating Woebot.

content:
On the face of it, it may seem silly; you know you're talking to a bot, it 
doesn't really "care" or "feel", but strangely it works IF you give it a 
chance to. The exercises and thought management techniques it gives you 
actually enable you to truly analyse your situation. Ultimately, it works 
like any other therapist; YOU are the one doing re work. You are the one 
having the revelations and breakthroughs. Honestly, I can say that this is 
helping me a great deal. Sometimes I even allow myself to forget what it is 
I'm talking to and interact with it as I would another person, and in those 
moments it excels. Please give it a chance. Allow yourself to talk to it, 
and pay attention to it's advice. This stuff works, but you have to be open 
to it.

content: pretty boring item
Good
Please translate language.

Patronising language from the start both from the bot and the responses you can give, with some comments at the beginning downright anxiety-inducing. I may have mental health conditions but I am not stupid, so please don't treat me as such. Then you're dealing with a chatbot with an identity crisis who can't figure out if it's an AI or a full-blown human, making it incredibly hard to take seriously. I thought this was supposed to have been developed by a clinical psychologist, who should know that people dealing with paranoia will not at all feel comfortable in giving up mobile phone information before you even get into the app. Mention of suicide triggers the knee-jerk response of someone about commit suicide, so while the list of numbers is helpful, there's no recogniton that many of us live with suicidal thoughts on a regular basis, and the bot gets stuck on the suicide bit. The concept of a bot using CBT techniques is very cool, but the AI is far too limited and simplistic at this stage for it to be properly effective in many instances of mental health - which is complicated and won't be solved by an app. If I could give this zero stars I would. Absolutely dreadful.
replyContent: Dear Genevieve, I'm truly sorry that this wasn't more helpful for you. Woebot does actually have space for people to challenge their suicidal thoughts without triggering the resources list, but you have to go through some Qs first, so it's not perfect. Phone # requirement is also gone. It's early days for us but yeah, can see why it's frustrating.

content: My clinical lead asked us if we have used this app before so I downloaded to see if it is any good. I was writing bad words to see how it would respond but the bot would not pick them up. I even wrote I want to end my life and it did not pick that up as a trigger/emergency sign ( I'm not suicidal, I was just playing around). Also, the bot gives you the information in the same order regardless of your response. When it finally picked up words such as "suicide" it repeatedly gave me the crisis info and wouldn't move on even after saying I am safe. It's a nice concept but it needs a lot of improvement.

I really love this app. It helps me work through my anxious thoughts when I feel I can't turn to anyone else, because I'm embarrassed or ashamed. Sometimes it glitches out and repeats huge chunks of the conversation, or its replies just come up as blank spaces. It would also be fantastic if I could save conversations for later review, because I often go through the same bad thoughts repeat on me a lot.
replyContent: Hi Alice, thanks for your thoughtful comments and feedback. Delighted Woebot is helping with anxious thoughts! Saving conversation - this is a great idea and we are working on it so stay tuned! Hopefully it is less glitchy now in most recent release.

content: Excellent.  Absolutely brilliant app. Woebot is cute and funny and great at brightening up the day. Sure it's only a "bot" but it works well at checking in and keeping you focused on simple things like breathing and gratitude.

content: If you've ever thought that being more happy would be nice, this app is for you!  It's based on CBT, Cognitive Behavioural Therapy, a highly scientific form of psychological therapy. A lot of it overlaps with positive psychology, the scientific school of what people who are more happy than others do right. The great thing is that this doesn't require any self discipline since woebot regularly checks in with you. And yes, it's not the greatest bot considering interaction, but the value is still amazing!
